window.CONTENT["4870"] = {"meta":{"id":"4870","code":"COMP 4870","name":"Enterprise .NET","exam":"2026-04-24T10:30:00-07:00","room":"SE12-327","format":"60 Multiple Choice + 10 Match Two Columns + 1 Coding Question · 80 marks · 60 min · pass 55%","instructor":"Medhat Elmasry","notes_html":"\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eInstructor: Medhat Elmasry · Covers weeks 7-13 (post-midterm, including W7)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eHighest weight: AI (13) + ML.NET (12) = 25 marks — 31% of exam. Cannot skip.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eMid-weight: Cache/Redis (8), File-based (8), gRPC (7), TDD (6), Aspire (5) = 34 marks\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eCoding question (10 marks): most likely gRPC proto, xUnit test class, or ML.NET pipeline\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eMidterm style (matched on final): MCQ with 5 options a-e, exact method-name recognition, fake API distractors\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eMatch column pattern (from midterm): package → file/command (e.g. React → Vite, TypeScript → tsc)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eHAND-WRITTEN cheat sheet 8.5×11 both sides: pack method names, package names, exact syntax. Not printed.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eAllowed scope: ASP.NET Core fundamentals carry over; exam focuses on W7-13 content\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e"},"modules":[{"id":"ai-ml","name":"AI & ML.NET","topics":[{"id":"4870-ai-semantic-kernel-maf-mcp-ollama","name":"AI (Semantic Kernel, MAF, MCP, Ollama)","tags":["ai","semantic-kernel"],"prose":"AI topics cover Semantic Kernel, Microsoft Agent Framework, MCP and running local models via Ollama.","cards":[{"type":"name","prompt":"What Kernel builder method registers Ollama chat completion?","answer":"`builder.AddOllamaChatCompletion(modelName, new Uri(\"http://localhost:11434\"))`"},{"type":"name","prompt":"Default Ollama local endpoint URL?","answer":"`http://localhost:11434`"},{"type":"name","prompt":"GitHub Models inference endpoint URL?","answer":"`https://models.github.ai/inference`"},{"type":"name","prompt":"Service to resolve from Kernel for chat: \\_\\_\\_","answer":"`IChatCompletionService` — `kernel.GetRequiredService\u003cIChatCompletionService\u003e()`"},{"type":"name","prompt":"What class holds the conversation context in SK?","answer":"`ChatHistory` — can seed with system prompt in constructor: `new ChatHistory(\"You are helpful.\")`"},{"type":"name","prompt":"How to add a system message to ChatHistory?","answer":"`history.AddSystemMessage(\"prompt\")` (or pass to constructor)"},{"type":"name","prompt":"Method to import native C# plugin into kernel?","answer":"`kernel.ImportPluginFromType\u003cMyPlugin\u003e()`"},{"type":"name","prompt":"Method to import prompt-directory plugins (skprompt.txt)?","answer":"`kernel.ImportPluginFromPromptDirectory(\"Plugins/MyPlugin\")`"},{"type":"name","prompt":"Attribute marking a C# method as a kernel-callable function?","answer":"`[KernelFunction]` with optional `[Description(\"...\")]`"},{"type":"name","prompt":"Variable placeholder syntax in skprompt.txt?","answer":"`{{$variable}}`"},{"type":"name","prompt":"Method to convert an OpenAIClient into an agent?","answer":"`.AsAIAgent(\"model-name\")`"},{"type":"name","prompt":"Factory method to wrap a delegate as an AI tool?","answer":"`AIFunctionFactory.Create(delegate, name, description)`"},{"type":"name","prompt":"Class that maintains multi-turn conversation state in MAF?","answer":"`AgentSession` — `new AgentSession(agent)`"},{"type":"name","prompt":"Method to stream agent output as tokens arrive?","answer":"`RunStreamingAsync(prompt)` — iterate with `await foreach`"},{"type":"name","prompt":"NuGet package for MAF + OpenAI integration?","answer":"`Microsoft.Agents.AI.OpenAI`"},{"type":"name","prompt":"MCP transports: \\_\\_\\_ (local) and \\_\\_\\_ (cloud)","answer":"`stdio` (process pipe) and `SSE` (Server-Sent Events over HTTP)"},{"type":"name","prompt":"MCP expands to: \\_\\_\\_","answer":"**Model Context Protocol** — open protocol for LLM tool/resource access"},{"type":"name","prompt":"Three MCP primitives a server can expose?","answer":"1. **Tools** (executable)\n2. **Resources** (read-only data)\n3. **Prompts** (reusable templates)"},{"type":"name","prompt":"NuGet package for Ollama C# client?","answer":"`OllamaSharp`"},{"type":"name","prompt":"CLI command to download llama3 to local Ollama?","answer":"`ollama pull llama3`"},{"type":"name","prompt":"SLM vs LLM tradeoff in one sentence?","answer":"SLM = smaller/faster/cheaper/local; LLM = bigger/smarter/needs cloud and API key"},{"type":"name","prompt":"Class used in kernel builder: `Kernel.___.Build()`?","answer":"`Kernel.CreateBuilder()`.Build()"},{"type":"name","prompt":"Chat call method that returns full response: \\_\\_\\_","answer":"`chat.GetChatMessageContentAsync(history, kernel: kernel)`"},{"type":"name","prompt":"Key difference: SK vs MAF","answer":"SK = kernel + plugins (flexible low-level); MAF = `AIAgent` (high-level, simpler agent creation)"},{"type":"name","prompt":"Which MCP transport requires a process pipe with stdin/stdout?","answer":"`stdio` — used for local, co-located tools"}]},{"id":"4870-ml-net-pipeline","name":"ML.NET pipeline","tags":["ml-net","machine-learning"],"prose":"ML.NET follows a seven-step pipeline: context, load, split, pipeline, fit, evaluate, save.","cards":[{"type":"name","prompt":"Entry-point class for all ML.NET code?","answer":"`MLContext` — `var mlContext = new MLContext(seed: 0);`"},{"type":"name","prompt":"Interface representing loaded/transformed data in ML.NET?","answer":"`IDataView` (tabular data flow)"},{"type":"name","prompt":"Method to load CSV data into an IDataView?","answer":"`mlContext.Data.LoadFromTextFile\u003cT\u003e(path, hasHeader: true, separatorChar: ',')`"},{"type":"name","prompt":"Method that splits data for testing?","answer":"`mlContext.Data.TrainTestSplit(data, testFraction: 0.2)`"},{"type":"name","prompt":"What does `pipeline.Fit(trainSet)` return?","answer":"`ITransformer` (the trained model)"},{"type":"name","prompt":"FastTree trainer for regression: `mlContext.___.Trainers.FastTree()`","answer":"`Regression` — `mlContext.Regression.Trainers.FastTree()`"},{"type":"name","prompt":"Regression metric: higher = better, scale 0-1?","answer":"`RSquared`"},{"type":"name","prompt":"Method to evaluate regression predictions?","answer":"`mlContext.Regression.Evaluate(predictions, labelColumnName: \"Label\")`"},{"type":"name","prompt":"How to save a trained model to disk?","answer":"`mlContext.Model.Save(model, data.Schema, \"model.zip\")`"},{"type":"name","prompt":"Method to load a saved model back?","answer":"`mlContext.Model.Load(\"model.zip\", out var schema)`"},{"type":"name","prompt":"Class used to predict on a single record?","answer":"`PredictionEngine\u003cTInput, TOutput\u003e` — created via `mlContext.Model.CreatePredictionEngine\u003cI,O\u003e(model)`"},{"type":"name","prompt":"Transform that collapses string category to numeric vector?","answer":"`mlContext.Transforms.Categorical.OneHotEncoding(\"outCol\", \"inCol\")`"},{"type":"name","prompt":"Transform that combines columns into a single Features vector?","answer":"`mlContext.Transforms.Concatenate(\"Features\", \"A\", \"B\", \"C\")`"},{"type":"name","prompt":"Attribute on a class property to map CSV column index?","answer":"`[LoadColumn(0)]` — e.g. `[LoadColumn(2)] public float Fare;`"},{"type":"name","prompt":"Attribute marking the target (Y) column in a training model?","answer":"`[ColumnName(\"Label\")]`"},{"type":"name","prompt":"Namespace for 2-class trainers?","answer":"`mlContext.BinaryClassification.Trainers`"},{"type":"name","prompt":"Namespace for 3+-class trainers?","answer":"`mlContext.MulticlassClassification.Trainers`"},{"type":"name","prompt":"AutoML CLI command to train a model?","answer":"`mlnet regression --dataset data.csv --label-col Label` (similar for classification)"}]}]},{"id":"caching-grpc","name":"Caching & gRPC","topics":[{"id":"4870-caching-imemorycache-redis","name":"Caching (IMemoryCache + Redis)","tags":["cache","redis"],"prose":"`IMemoryCache` for single-server in-process caching; `IDistributedCache` (Redis) for shared state across a load-balanced farm. Know absolute vs sliding expiration and `CacheItemPriority`.","cards":[{"type":"name","prompt":"Registration for in-memory cache in Program.cs?","answer":"`builder.Services.AddMemoryCache();`"},{"type":"name","prompt":"Interface injected to use the in-memory cache?","answer":"`IMemoryCache`"},{"type":"name","prompt":"Pattern to read cache with fallback load?","answer":"`_cache.TryGetValue\u003cT\u003e(key, out var val)` then load + `_cache.Set(key, val, options)`"},{"type":"name","prompt":"Options class for in-memory cache entries?","answer":"`MemoryCacheEntryOptions`"},{"type":"name","prompt":"Difference: AbsoluteExpiration vs SlidingExpiration","answer":"Absolute = hard expiry at time X. Sliding = expire if idle for Y. Combine → whichever fires first."},{"type":"name","prompt":"Property to mark a cache entry as never-evict-unless-full?","answer":"`CacheItemPriority.NeverRemove` (also Low/Normal/High)"},{"type":"name","prompt":"Registration for Redis distributed cache?","answer":"`builder.Services.AddStackExchangeRedisCache(o =\u003e o.Configuration = \"localhost:6379\");`"},{"type":"name","prompt":"Interface injected to use the distributed cache?","answer":"`IDistributedCache`"},{"type":"name","prompt":"Method to store a string in IDistributedCache?","answer":"`await cache.SetStringAsync(key, value, opts)`"},{"type":"name","prompt":"Docker command to run Redis locally?","answer":"`docker run -d --name redis -p 6379:6379 redis`"},{"type":"name","prompt":"Razor tag for server-fragment caching?","answer":"`\u003ccache expires-after=\"@TimeSpan.FromMinutes(10)\"\u003e...\u003c/cache\u003e`"},{"type":"name","prompt":"Attribute to vary cached fragment by logged-in user?","answer":"`vary-by-user=\"true\"`"},{"type":"name","prompt":"Five vary-by-\\* attributes on ?","answer":"1. `vary-by-user`\n2. `vary-by-route`\n3. `vary-by-query`\n4. `vary-by-cookie`\n5. `vary-by-header` (also `vary-by` for custom)"},{"type":"name","prompt":"Why does IMemoryCache fail in load-balanced deployments?","answer":"Each server has its own in-process cache → cache miss for users hitting different servers → inconsistent data. Use IDistributedCache (Redis) for shared cache."},{"type":"name","prompt":"Single-call cache-or-load method?","answer":"`await _cache.GetOrCreateAsync(key, async entry =\u003e { entry.AbsoluteExpirationRelativeToNow = TimeSpan.FromMinutes(5); return await Load(); })`"}]},{"id":"4870-grpc","name":"gRPC","tags":["grpc","proto"],"prose":"gRPC is contract-first RPC over HTTP/2 — .proto defines messages, tooling generates C# server and client stubs.","cards":[{"type":"name","prompt":"Full name of gRPC?","answer":"**Google Remote Procedure Call**"},{"type":"name","prompt":"HTTP protocol gRPC requires?","answer":"**HTTP/2** (binary framing, multiplexing, streaming)"},{"type":"name","prompt":"Serialization format gRPC uses?","answer":"**Protocol Buffers (protobuf)** — binary, compact, typed"},{"type":"name","prompt":"First line of every proto3 file?","answer":"`syntax = \"proto3\";`"},{"type":"name","prompt":"Directive setting C# namespace in .proto?","answer":"`option csharp_namespace = \"MyApp\";`"},{"type":"name","prompt":"What does field number represent in a proto message?","answer":"A stable wire-format identifier. Must be unique within the message. ORDER in code does NOT matter; field number does."},{"type":"name","prompt":"Service registration line for gRPC server?","answer":"`builder.Services.AddGrpc();`"},{"type":"name","prompt":"Middleware line to wire a gRPC service class?","answer":"`app.MapGrpcService\u003cMyServiceImpl\u003e();`"},{"type":"name","prompt":"Create a gRPC channel to a server?","answer":"`GrpcChannel.ForAddress(\"https://localhost:5001\")`"},{"type":"name","prompt":"DI pattern to register a gRPC client?","answer":"`builder.Services.AddGrpcClient\u003cGreeter.GreeterClient\u003e(o =\u003e o.Address = new Uri(\"https://...\"));`"},{"type":"name","prompt":"csproj item to compile .proto files?","answer":"`\u003cProtobuf Include=\"Protos/greet.proto\" GrpcServices=\"Server\" /\u003e` — values: Server | Client | Both"},{"type":"name","prompt":"The four gRPC call types?","answer":"1. Unary\n2. Server streaming\n3. Client streaming\n4. Bidirectional streaming"}]}]},{"id":"testing-hosting","name":"Testing, file-based apps & Aspire","topics":[{"id":"4870-tdd-xunit","name":"TDD / xUnit","tags":["tdd","xunit"],"prose":"public class CalculatorTests : IDisposable { private readonly Calculator _calc; public CalculatorTests() { // setup _calc = new Calculator(); } public void Dispose() { } // teardown [Fact] public void Add_TwoPositives_ReturnsSum() { var r = _calc.Add(2, 3); Assert.Equal(5, r); } [Theory] [InlineData(1, 2, 3)] [InlineData(0, 0, 0)] [InlineData(-1, 1, 0)] public void Add_Various(int a, int b, int expected) { Assert.Equal(expected, _calc.Add(a, b)); } [Fact] public void Divide_ByZero_Throws() { var ex = Assert.Throws&lt;DivideByZeroException&gt;(() =&gt; _calc.Divide(5, 0)); Assert.Contains(\"zero\", ex.Message); } [Fact] public async Task LongTask_Completes() { await Assert.ThrowsAsync&lt;TimeoutException&gt;(async () =&gt; await _calc.SlowAsync()); } } Asserts in the course Equal, NotEqual, True, False, Null, NotNull, Same, NotSame, Throws&lt;T&gt;, ThrowsAsync&lt;T&gt;, Contains, DoesNotContain, Empty, NotEmpty, InRange, IsType&lt;T&gt;, IsAssignableFrom&lt;T&gt;, Collection","cards":[{"type":"name","prompt":"The TDD cycle: \\_\\_\\_ / \\_\\_\\_ / \\_\\_\\_","answer":"**Red** (failing test) → **Green** (make it pass) → **Refactor**"},{"type":"name","prompt":"Attribute for a parameterless test?","answer":"`[Fact]`"},{"type":"name","prompt":"Attribute for a parameterized test?","answer":"`[Theory]` — paired with `[InlineData(...)]`, `[MemberData(...)]`, or `[ClassData(typeof(X))]`"},{"type":"name","prompt":"Assertion argument order?","answer":"`Assert.Equal(expected, actual)` — EXPECTED first. Swapping gives misleading failure messages."},{"type":"name","prompt":"AAA pattern stands for?","answer":"**Arrange** (setup) → **Act** (run) → **Assert** (verify)"},{"type":"name","prompt":"How do you perform setup code in xUnit (no \\[SetUp\\] attribute)?","answer":"Use the test class **constructor**. For teardown, implement `IDisposable`."},{"type":"name","prompt":"Interface for shared state across tests in a class?","answer":"`IClassFixture\u003cTFixture\u003e` — shared across methods in one class"},{"type":"name","prompt":"Interface for shared state across test CLASSES?","answer":"`ICollectionFixture\u003cT\u003e` with `[Collection(\"name\")]`"},{"type":"name","prompt":"Assert method for expected exception?","answer":"`Assert.Throws\u003cExceptionType\u003e(() =\u003e code())`. Async version: `ThrowsAsync\u003cT\u003e`."},{"type":"name","prompt":"CLI to create and run a test project?","answer":"`dotnet new xunit -n MyTests` then `dotnet test`"},{"type":"name","prompt":"Moq pattern to stub a return?","answer":"`var m = new Mock\u003cIFoo\u003e(); m.Setup(f =\u003e f.Get(5)).Returns(\"hi\"); var svc = new Svc(m.Object);`"},{"type":"name","prompt":"Difference between stub, mock, fake?","answer":"1. **Stub**: provides canned answers\n2. **Mock**: stub + verifies calls\n3. **Fake**: working lightweight impl (in-memory db)"}]},{"id":"4870-file-based-c-apps","name":"File-based C# apps","tags":["file-based","dotnet-run"],"prose":".NET 10 file-based C# apps — single `.cs` file run via `dotnet run app.cs`, no `.csproj` needed. `#:package`, `#:sdk`, `#:property`, `#:project` directives inline MSBuild config.","cards":[{"type":"name","prompt":"Command to run a file-based C# app?","answer":"`dotnet run app.cs`"},{"type":"name","prompt":"Minimum .NET version for file-based apps?","answer":"**.NET 10**"},{"type":"name","prompt":"Directive to reference a NuGet package?","answer":"`#:package PackageName@version` — e.g. `#:package Spectre.Console@0.48.0`"},{"type":"name","prompt":"Directive to use the ASP.NET Web SDK?","answer":"`#:sdk Microsoft.NET.Sdk.Web`"},{"type":"name","prompt":"Directive to set an MSBuild property?","answer":"`#:property LangVersion=preview`"},{"type":"name","prompt":"Directive to reference another .csproj from a file-based app?","answer":"`#:project ./path/MyLib.csproj`"},{"type":"name","prompt":"Exam trap — correct syntax: `#:package X` or `#: package X`?","answer":"**#:package X** — NO space after the colon"},{"type":"name","prompt":"Command to promote a file-based app to a project?","answer":"`dotnet project convert app.cs`"},{"type":"name","prompt":"Why file-based apps exist?","answer":"Lightweight scripting for utilities, demos, learning — no .csproj, no bin/obj folders, single-file distribution."},{"type":"name","prompt":"Shebang line for Linux/Mac direct execution?","answer":"`#!/usr/bin/env dotnet` (then `chmod +x file.cs`)"}]},{"id":"4870-asp-net-aspire","name":"ASP.NET Aspire","tags":["aspire","orchestration"],"prose":"ASP.NET Aspire orchestrates a distributed app — AppHost wires resources (Redis, SQL, projects) via `WithReference`; each service uses `AddServiceDefaults()` for telemetry, health, and service discovery.","cards":[{"type":"name","prompt":"Aspire builder entry point?","answer":"`var builder = DistributedApplication.CreateBuilder(args);`"},{"type":"name","prompt":"Method to add a .NET project to the distributed app?","answer":"`builder.AddProject\u003cProjects.MyApi\u003e(\"api\")`"},{"type":"name","prompt":"Method to inject cache URL into a project?","answer":"`api.WithReference(cache)` — passes connection string via env var"},{"type":"name","prompt":"Add a Redis resource to Aspire?","answer":"`var cache = builder.AddRedis(\"cache\");`"},{"type":"name","prompt":"Add SQL Server + a database?","answer":"`var sql = builder.AddSqlServer(\"sql\"); var db = sql.AddDatabase(\"app\");`"},{"type":"name","prompt":"Service discovery URL scheme?","answer":"`https+http://api` — scheme fallback + logical name"},{"type":"name","prompt":"What is an Aspire AppHost?","answer":"A **project template** (not a class) that orchestrates all resources (projects, db, cache) and launches them together."},{"type":"name","prompt":"ServiceDefaults vs AppHost roles?","answer":"**AppHost**: orchestrates everything (in AppHost's Program.cs). **ServiceDefaults**: shared wire-up (telemetry, health checks) each service imports."},{"type":"name","prompt":"Method each service calls to register Aspire defaults?","answer":"`builder.AddServiceDefaults();`"},{"type":"name","prompt":"Method to wait for a dependency before starting?","answer":"`.WaitFor(resource)`"}]}]},{"id":"web-ui","name":"Localization, Tag Helpers & Blazor","topics":[{"id":"4870-localization","name":"Localization","tags":["localization","i18n"],"prose":"Localization via `AddLocalization` + `UseRequestLocalization` middleware. `.resx` files per culture under `ResourcesPath`. CurrentCulture = formatting; CurrentUICulture = resource lookup.","cards":[{"type":"name","prompt":"Service registration for localization?","answer":"`builder.Services.AddLocalization(o =\u003e o.ResourcesPath = \"Resources\");`"},{"type":"name","prompt":"Middleware to apply culture selection?","answer":"`app.UseRequestLocalization();`"},{"type":"name","prompt":"Interface injected in a Razor view for translations?","answer":"`IViewLocalizer` — `@inject IViewLocalizer Localizer`, use `@Localizer[\"Hello\"]`"},{"type":"name","prompt":"Resource file naming convention (French, for IndexModel)?","answer":"`Pages.Index.fr.resx` or `Pages/Index.fr.resx` (depends on ResourcesPath setting)"},{"type":"name","prompt":"CurrentCulture vs CurrentUICulture?","answer":"**CurrentCulture** — number/date formatting. **CurrentUICulture** — which resx to load for translated strings."},{"type":"name","prompt":"Three built-in culture providers (in priority order)?","answer":"1. QueryString (`?culture=fr`)\n2. Cookie\n3. Accept-Language header"},{"type":"name","prompt":"Cookie name used by CookieRequestCultureProvider?","answer":"`CookieRequestCultureProvider.DefaultCookieName` (literal: `.AspNetCore.Culture`)"},{"type":"name","prompt":"Difference between i18n and l10n?","answer":"**i18n (globalization)** = design for any culture. **l10n (localization)** = specific resources/translations for one culture."}]},{"id":"4870-tag-helpers","name":"Tag Helpers","tags":["tag-helpers","razor"],"prose":"Tag helpers are reusable Razor markup components registered in `_ViewImports.cshtml`. Custom helpers extend `TagHelper` and override `Process`; PascalCase properties map to kebab-case HTML attributes.","cards":[{"type":"name","prompt":"File where tag helpers are registered?","answer":"`_ViewImports.cshtml` — `@addTagHelper *, Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.TagHelpers`"},{"type":"name","prompt":"Custom tag helper: base class + method to override?","answer":"Base: `TagHelper`. Override: `Process(context, output)` or `ProcessAsync(...)`."},{"type":"name","prompt":"Attribute to target an HTML element name in a custom tag helper?","answer":"`[HtmlTargetElement(\"toon\")]`"},{"type":"name","prompt":"Property `FontFamily` on a tag helper maps to what HTML attribute?","answer":"`font-family` (PascalCase → kebab-case)"},{"type":"name","prompt":"Tag helper to render a validation error for a single field?","answer":"`\u003cspan asp-validation-for=\"PropertyName\"\u003e\u003c/span\u003e`"},{"type":"name","prompt":"Tag helper to cache-bust a script reference?","answer":"`\u003cscript src=\"/js/site.js\" asp-append-version=\"true\"\u003e\u003c/script\u003e`"}]},{"id":"4870-blazor-quickgrid","name":"Blazor QuickGrid","tags":["blazor","quickgrid"],"prose":"Blazor QuickGrid renders tabular data in three components: \u003cQuickGrid\u003e, \u003cPropertyColumn\u003e per field, and a \u003cPaginator\u003e.","cards":[{"type":"name","prompt":"NuGet package for QuickGrid?","answer":"`Microsoft.AspNetCore.Components.QuickGrid`"},{"type":"name","prompt":"Sortable property column syntax?","answer":"`\u003cPropertyColumn Property=\"@(_ =\u003e _.Name)\" Sortable=\"true\" /\u003e`"},{"type":"name","prompt":"Pagination state declaration?","answer":"`private PaginationState pagination = new PaginationState { ItemsPerPage = 10 };`"},{"type":"name","prompt":"TemplateColumn sorting requires?","answer":"Explicit `SortBy=\"@gridSort\"` — uses `GridSort\u003cT\u003e.ByAscending(x =\u003e x.Prop)`"},{"type":"name","prompt":"Live-filter input binding?","answer":"`\u003cinput @bind=\"filter\" @bind:event=\"oninput\" /\u003e`"}]}]},{"id":"export","name":"Excel / PDF / Chart export","topics":[{"id":"4870-excel-pdf-chart-export","name":"Excel / PDF / Chart export","tags":["excel","pdf","chart"],"prose":"using ClosedXML.Excel; using var wb = new XLWorkbook(); var ws = wb.Worksheets.Add(\"Sheet1\"); ws.Cell(1, 1).Value = \"Name\"; ws.Cell(1, 2).Value = \"Score\"; ws.Cell(2, 1).Value = \"Alice\"; ws.Cell(2, 2).Value = 92; using var ms = new MemoryStream(); wb.SaveAs(ms); return File(ms.ToArray(), \"application/vnd.openxmlformats-officedocument.spreadsheetml.sheet\", \"report.xlsx\"); PDF with iText7 using iText.Kernel.Pdf; using iText.Layout; using iText.Layout.Element; using var ms = new MemoryStream(); var writer = new PdfWriter(ms); var pdf = new PdfDocument(writer); var doc = new Document(pdf); doc.Add(new Paragraph(\"Hello PDF\")); var table = new Table(2); table.AddCell(\"Name\"); table.AddCell(\"Score\"); table.AddCell(\"Alice\"); table.AddCell(\"92\"); doc.Add(table); doc.Close(); return File(ms.ToArray(), \"application/pdf\", \"report.pdf\"); Required packages: itext7 + itext.bouncy-castle-adapter","cards":[{"type":"name","prompt":"Package used for Excel export?","answer":"`ClosedXML` — `new XLWorkbook()` + `Worksheets.Add()` + `Cell(r,c).Value`"},{"type":"name","prompt":"Packages required for PDF generation?","answer":"`itext7` + `itext.bouncy-castle-adapter` (BOTH needed)"},{"type":"name","prompt":"MIME type for Excel .xlsx?","answer":"`application/vnd.openxmlformats-officedocument.spreadsheetml.sheet`"},{"type":"name","prompt":"MIME type for PDF?","answer":"`application/pdf`"},{"type":"name","prompt":"Chart rendering library used in course?","answer":"**Chart.js** (via CDN, client-side rendering inside Razor)"}]}]}],"mockExam":{"duration_seconds":3600,"questions":[{"id":"q1","type":"MCQ","topic":"AI","marks":1,"question":"Which method resolves the chat service from a built SK Kernel?","correct":2,"rationale":"Standard DI pattern — kernel is an IServiceProvider. `GetRequiredService\u003cIChatCompletionService\u003e()` is the canonical resolve.","choices":["kernel.Services.GetChat()","kernel.Chat","kernel.GetRequiredService\u003cIChatCompletionService\u003e()","kernel.CreateChatCompletion()","new ChatCompletion(kernel)"]},{"id":"q2","type":"MCQ","topic":"AI","marks":1,"question":"What is the default local Ollama endpoint?","correct":1,"rationale":"Ollama default port is 11434 and uses plain HTTP on localhost.","choices":["http://localhost:8080","http://localhost:11434","https://localhost:11434","http://localhost:3000","http://127.0.0.1:5000"]},{"id":"q3","type":"MCQ","topic":"AI","marks":1,"question":"Which factory method creates an AI tool from a C# delegate in MAF?","correct":2,"rationale":"`AIFunctionFactory.Create(delegate, name, description)` is the static factory. Wraps a C# method into an `AIFunction` tool.","choices":["AIFunction.Create(delegate)","AIAgent.CreateTool(delegate)","AIFunctionFactory.Create(delegate, name, desc)","Tool.FromMethod(delegate)","new AIFunction(delegate)"]},{"id":"q4","type":"MCQ","topic":"AI","marks":1,"question":"Which attribute marks a C# method as Kernel-callable in Semantic Kernel?","correct":1,"rationale":"The current attribute (post rename) is `[KernelFunction]`. `[SKFunction]` was the older name and is a classic distractor.","choices":["\\[SKFunction\\]","\\[KernelFunction\\]","\\[AIFunction\\]","\\[SemanticFunction\\]","\\[Callable\\]"]},{"id":"q5","type":"MCQ","topic":"AI","marks":1,"question":"Which MCP transport is appropriate for a LOCAL co-located tool?","correct":3,"rationale":"`stdio` uses a stdin/stdout process pipe — local only. `SSE` is HTTP-based for remote.","choices":["SSE","WebSocket","HTTP/2","stdio","gRPC"]},{"id":"q6","type":"MCQ","topic":"AI","marks":1,"question":"In MAF, what object maintains multi-turn history across calls?","correct":1,"rationale":"`AgentSession` wraps an `AIAgent` and tracks prior messages. `ChatHistory` is the SK equivalent, not MAF.","choices":["ChatHistory","AgentSession","ConversationContext","IContextMemory","AgentContext"]},{"id":"q7","type":"MCQ","topic":"AI","marks":1,"question":"Which MAF extension method turns an OpenAIClient into an agent?","correct":2,"rationale":"Extension: `client.AsAIAgent(\"gpt-4o-mini\")`.","choices":[".ToAIAgent(model)",".CreateAgent(model)",".AsAIAgent(model)",".MakeAgent(model)","new AIAgent(client, model)"]},{"id":"q8","type":"MCQ","topic":"ML.NET","marks":1,"question":"What does `pipeline.Fit(trainSet)` return?","correct":2,"rationale":"Fit trains the pipeline and returns an `ITransformer` (the trained model). It does NOT return the predictions.","choices":["IDataView","MLContext","ITransformer","IEstimator","PredictionEngine"]},{"id":"q9","type":"MCQ","topic":"ML.NET","marks":1,"question":"Which method loads a CSV file as IDataView?","correct":2,"rationale":"`LoadFromTextFile\u003cT\u003e` is the correct name and takes hasHeader + separatorChar.","choices":["mlContext.Data.LoadCsv\u003cT\u003e(path)","mlContext.LoadFromCsv\u003cT\u003e(path)","mlContext.Data.LoadFromTextFile\u003cT\u003e(path, hasHeader: true, separatorChar: ',')","mlContext.ReadCsv(path)","new IDataView(path)"]},{"id":"q10","type":"MCQ","topic":"ML.NET","marks":1,"question":"Which metric is appropriate for a REGRESSION model?","correct":3,"rationale":"RSquared (and RMSE) are regression metrics. Accuracy/F1/LogLoss are for classification.","choices":["Accuracy","F1Score","MacroAccuracy","RSquared","LogLoss"]},{"id":"q11","type":"MCQ","topic":"ML.NET","marks":1,"question":"Which namespace holds trainers for a binary (2-class) classifier?","correct":0,"rationale":"`BinaryClassification.Trainers` for 2-class; `MulticlassClassification.Trainers` for 3+.","choices":["mlContext.BinaryClassification.Trainers","mlContext.Classification.Trainers","mlContext.MulticlassClassification.Trainers","mlContext.Classify.Trainers","mlContext.Predictor.Trainers"]},{"id":"q12","type":"MCQ","topic":"ML.NET","marks":1,"question":"What transform combines multiple columns into a single Features vector?","correct":0,"rationale":"`mlContext.Transforms.Concatenate(\"Features\", \"A\", \"B\", \"C\")` — required by trainers that expect a single Features column.","choices":["Concatenate","Combine","MergeColumns","BuildVector","Union"]},{"id":"q13","type":"MCQ","topic":"ML.NET","marks":1,"question":"Which attribute maps a CSV column index to a class property?","correct":1,"rationale":"`[LoadColumn(0)]` maps the zero-based CSV column to the property.","choices":["\\[Column(0)\\]","\\[LoadColumn(0)\\]","\\[FromCsv(0)\\]","\\[Index(0)\\]","\\[Ordinal(0)\\]"]},{"id":"q14","type":"MCQ","topic":"Cache","marks":1,"question":"Which interface is injected for distributed caching?","correct":2,"rationale":"`IDistributedCache` is the abstraction backed by Redis / SQL Server / etc.","choices":["IMemoryCache","ICacheProvider","IDistributedCache","IRedisCache","ICacheManager"]},{"id":"q15","type":"MCQ","topic":"Cache","marks":1,"question":"Register Redis distributed cache in Program.cs:","correct":2,"rationale":"`AddStackExchangeRedisCache` uses the options callback with `Configuration` property.","choices":["builder.Services.AddRedisCache(\"localhost:6379\")","builder.Services.AddDistributedRedisCache(o =\u003e o.Host = \"localhost\")","builder.Services.AddStackExchangeRedisCache(o =\u003e o.Configuration = \"localhost:6379\")","builder.Services.AddRedis(\"localhost:6379\")","builder.Services.UseRedis()"]},{"id":"q16","type":"MCQ","topic":"Cache","marks":1,"question":"Why does IMemoryCache fail in a load-balanced web farm?","correct":2,"rationale":"In-process cache = per-server RAM. Server A has no clue about what Server B cached. Redis solves this.","choices":["Memory leak","Thread safety","Each server instance has its own cache","MemoryCache is deprecated","Firewall blocks it"]},{"id":"q17","type":"MCQ","topic":"Cache","marks":1,"question":"Cache Tag Helper attribute to vary fragment by current user:","correct":1,"rationale":"`vary-by-user=\"true\"`.","choices":["vary-by-identity","vary-by-user","user=\"true\"","authenticate-vary","vary-by-auth"]},{"id":"q18","type":"MCQ","topic":"Cache","marks":1,"question":"Difference between AbsoluteExpiration and SlidingExpiration?","correct":0,"rationale":"Absolute: expires at fixed DateTimeOffset. Sliding: resets TTL whenever entry is accessed. Combining = earlier wins.","choices":["Absolute = fixed duration; Sliding = resets on access","Both are identical","Absolute = relative time; Sliding = calendar time","Absolute applies to Redis only","Sliding expires immediately"]},{"id":"q19","type":"MCQ","topic":"FileBased","marks":1,"question":"Which is the CORRECT directive to reference a NuGet package?","correct":2,"rationale":"No space after colon: `#:package`. Space between directive and content is OK.","choices":["#: package Humanizer@2.14.1","#package Humanizer@2.14.1","#:package Humanizer@2.14.1","//:package Humanizer@2.14.1","#pragma package Humanizer"]},{"id":"q20","type":"MCQ","topic":"FileBased","marks":1,"question":"Command to run a single file-based C# app:","correct":2,"rationale":"`dotnet run app.cs` — detects the .cs argument and compiles/runs in memory.","choices":["dotnet app.cs","dotnet exec app.cs","dotnet run app.cs","dotnet script app.cs","csi app.cs"]},{"id":"q21","type":"MCQ","topic":"FileBased","marks":1,"question":"What directive selects the ASP.NET Core web SDK in a file-based app?","correct":1,"rationale":"`#:sdk Microsoft.NET.Sdk.Web` — full MSBuild SDK identifier.","choices":["#:sdk AspNetCore","#:sdk Microsoft.NET.Sdk.Web","#:framework web","#:use Web","#:webhost"]},{"id":"q22","type":"MCQ","topic":"FileBased","marks":1,"question":"Command to convert a file-based app into a .csproj project:","correct":2,"rationale":"`dotnet project convert app.cs` promotes the script into a proper project with a .csproj.","choices":["dotnet upgrade app.cs","dotnet convert app.cs","dotnet project convert app.cs","dotnet new project --from app.cs","dotnet build --promote app.cs"]},{"id":"q23","type":"MCQ","topic":"FileBased","marks":1,"question":"Which .NET version introduced file-based apps?","correct":4,"rationale":"Single-file apps with #: directives shipped in .NET 10.","choices":[".NET 6",".NET 7",".NET 8",".NET 9",".NET 10"]},{"id":"q24","type":"MCQ","topic":"gRPC","marks":1,"question":"First line of every .proto3 file?","correct":1,"rationale":"Literally `syntax = \"proto3\";` at the top.","choices":["package proto3;","syntax = \"proto3\";","version 3;","proto 3;","schema = \"proto3\";"]},{"id":"q25","type":"MCQ","topic":"gRPC","marks":1,"question":"Protocol gRPC REQUIRES?","correct":2,"rationale":"gRPC is built on HTTP/2 (binary framing, multiplexing, streaming).","choices":["HTTP/1.0","HTTP/1.1","HTTP/2","WebSocket","QUIC"]},{"id":"q26","type":"MCQ","topic":"gRPC","marks":1,"question":"Register a gRPC service in Program.cs:","correct":2,"rationale":"Two steps: `AddGrpc()` in services, `MapGrpcService\u003cT\u003e()` in the pipeline.","choices":["app.MapGrpc\u003cMyService\u003e()","app.UseGrpc()","builder.Services.AddGrpc(); app.MapGrpcService\u003cMyServiceImpl\u003e();","builder.Services.AddGrpcService\u003cMyServiceImpl\u003e()","app.MapService\u003cMyServiceImpl\u003e()"]},{"id":"q27","type":"MCQ","topic":"gRPC","marks":1,"question":"csproj item to compile a .proto for the server:","correct":1,"rationale":"`\u003cProtobuf Include=\"...\" GrpcServices=\"Server|Client|Both\" /\u003e` — \"Role\" and \"For\" are fake.","choices":["\u003cProtobuf Include=\"x.proto\" Role=\"Server\"/\u003e","\u003cProtobuf Include=\"x.proto\" GrpcServices=\"Server\"/\u003e","\u003cProto Include=\"x.proto\" For=\"Server\"/\u003e","\u003cProtobufServer Include=\"x.proto\"/\u003e","\u003cGrpc Include=\"x.proto\" Generate=\"Server\"/\u003e"]},{"id":"q28","type":"MCQ","topic":"TDD","marks":1,"question":"Argument order for `Assert.Equal`:","correct":1,"rationale":"Always `(expected, actual)`. Swapping produces misleading failure messages.","choices":["(actual, expected)","(expected, actual)","(left, right)","Order does not matter","(value, compareTo)"]},{"id":"q29","type":"MCQ","topic":"TDD","marks":1,"question":"Attribute for a test with multiple parameter sets:","correct":2,"rationale":"`[Theory]` with `[InlineData(...)]` rows. `[Fact]` = no args.","choices":["\\[TestCase\\]","\\[DataRow\\]","\\[Theory\\] + \\[InlineData\\]","\\[Parameterized\\]","\\[Many\\]"]},{"id":"q30","type":"MCQ","topic":"TDD","marks":1,"question":"How do you perform test setup in xUnit?","correct":2,"rationale":"xUnit uses the class constructor. Teardown: implement `IDisposable`.","choices":["\\[SetUp\\] method","\\[TestInitialize\\] method","Class constructor","OnBefore() override","Static Init()"]},{"id":"q31","type":"MCQ","topic":"TDD","marks":1,"question":"How do you assert that code throws an exception?","correct":1,"rationale":"`Assert.Throws\u003cT\u003e(Action)` — use `ThrowsAsync\u003cT\u003e` for async.","choices":["Assert.ThrowsException\u003cT\u003e(code)","Assert.Throws\u003cT\u003e(() =\u003e code())","\\[ExpectedException(typeof(T))\\]","try/catch with Assert.Fail","Assert.HasException\u003cT\u003e"]},{"id":"q32","type":"MCQ","topic":"Aspire","marks":1,"question":"Aspire AppHost entry point:","correct":1,"rationale":"`DistributedApplication.CreateBuilder(args)` — parallels `WebApplication.CreateBuilder`.","choices":["new DistributedApplication()","var builder = DistributedApplication.CreateBuilder(args);","Aspire.CreateHost(args)","new AspireAppHost()","Host.CreateApplicationBuilder(args)"]},{"id":"q33","type":"MCQ","topic":"Aspire","marks":1,"question":"Add a Redis resource to Aspire AppHost:","correct":0,"rationale":"`builder.AddRedis(\"cache\")` on the AppHost builder.","choices":["builder.AddRedis(\"cache\")","builder.Services.AddRedis(\"cache\")","builder.UseRedis()","DistributedApplication.AddRedis(\"cache\")","builder.AddContainer(\"redis\")"]},{"id":"q34","type":"MCQ","topic":"Aspire","marks":1,"question":"Method that passes a resource's connection info to a project:","correct":1,"rationale":"`project.WithReference(resource)` injects env vars/connection strings.","choices":[".WithConnection(db)",".WithReference(db)",".UseDatabase(db)",".LinkTo(db)",".AddDependency(db)"]},{"id":"q35","type":"MCQ","topic":"Localization","marks":1,"question":"Register localization service:","correct":0,"rationale":"`AddLocalization` with options callback setting `ResourcesPath`.","choices":["builder.Services.AddLocalization(o =\u003e o.ResourcesPath = \"Resources\")","builder.UseLocalization(\"Resources\")","builder.Services.AddI18n()","builder.AddCultures(new\\[\\] { \"en\", \"fr\" })","builder.Services.UseResources(\"Resources\")"]},{"id":"q36","type":"MCQ","topic":"Localization","marks":1,"question":"Which interface is injected in a Razor view for translations?","correct":2,"rationale":"`IViewLocalizer` is the one designed for Razor views. `IStringLocalizer\u003cT\u003e` used in code-behind / controllers.","choices":["IStringLocalizer","ILocalizer","IViewLocalizer","IResourceLocalizer","IHtmlLocalizer"]},{"id":"q37","type":"MCQ","topic":"Localization","marks":1,"question":"Which property controls number/date formatting culture?","correct":2,"rationale":"`CurrentCulture` = formatting. `CurrentUICulture` = which resx to load.","choices":["CurrentUICulture","CurrentLocale","CurrentCulture","FormattingCulture","DisplayCulture"]},{"id":"q38","type":"MCQ","topic":"TagHelpers","marks":1,"question":"File where tag helpers are registered for a folder?","correct":2,"rationale":"`_ViewImports.cshtml` — via `@addTagHelper *, Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.TagHelpers`.","choices":["\\_Layout.cshtml","\\_ViewStart.cshtml","\\_ViewImports.cshtml","appsettings.json","Program.cs"]},{"id":"q39","type":"MCQ","topic":"TagHelpers","marks":1,"question":"Property `FontFamily` on a custom tag helper maps to which HTML attribute?","correct":3,"rationale":"Kebab-case conversion: PascalCase C# → lowercase-hyphenated HTML.","choices":["fontFamily","Font-Family","FONT\\_FAMILY","font-family","fontfamily"]},{"id":"q40","type":"MCQ","topic":"Blazor","marks":1,"question":"NuGet package for QuickGrid:","correct":2,"rationale":"`Microsoft.AspNetCore.Components.QuickGrid`.","choices":["Microsoft.AspNetCore.Components.Grid","Microsoft.AspNetCore.QuickGrid","Microsoft.AspNetCore.Components.QuickGrid","Blazor.QuickGrid","Syncfusion.QuickGrid"]},{"id":"q41","type":"MCQ","topic":"Blazor","marks":1,"question":"A `TemplateColumn` with `Sortable=\"true\"` — what happens?","correct":1,"rationale":"`Sortable=\"true\"` is only recognized on `PropertyColumn`. `TemplateColumn` needs `SortBy=\"@GridSort...\"`.","choices":["It sorts alphabetically","Sorting ignores the attribute; TemplateColumn needs SortBy","Compile error","Runtime exception","Sorts by row index"]},{"id":"q42","type":"MCQ","topic":"ExcelPDF","marks":1,"question":"Correct MIME type for an .xlsx download?","correct":3,"rationale":"The modern Open XML MIME type. `application/vnd.ms-excel` is for legacy .xls.","choices":["application/xlsx","application/excel","application/vnd.ms-excel","application/vnd.openxmlformats-officedocument.spreadsheetml.sheet","text/xlsx"]},{"id":"q43","type":"MCQ","topic":"AI","marks":1,"question":"Method to import a native C# plugin class into a Semantic Kernel?","correct":1,"rationale":"`ImportPluginFromType\u003cT\u003e()` (source: CSharp\\_Meets\\_AI.pptx). Register → fake. AddPlugin exists on Kernel.Plugins but is not the preferred factory.","choices":["kernel.AddPlugin\u003cMyPlugin\u003e()","kernel.ImportPluginFromType\u003cMyPlugin\u003e()","kernel.Register\u003cMyPlugin\u003e()","kernel.Plugins.Add(new MyPlugin())","kernel.LoadPlugin\u003cMyPlugin\u003e()"]},{"id":"q44","type":"MCQ","topic":"AI","marks":1,"question":"Variable placeholder syntax inside a skprompt.txt template?","correct":3,"rationale":"Double-brace with $ is the SK prompt template syntax (source: CSharp\\_Meets\\_AI.pptx). Single-brace is interpolation; ${} is JS; @ is Razor.","choices":["{input}","${input}","\u003cinput\u003e","{{$input}}","@input"]},{"id":"q45","type":"MCQ","topic":"AI","marks":1,"question":"MCP stands for:","correct":0,"rationale":"**Model Context Protocol** — open standard for LLM tool/resource access (source: SLM.pptx).","choices":["Model Context Protocol","Multi-Cloud Protocol","Managed Connection Provider","Microsoft Chat Protocol","Memory Cache Proxy"]},{"id":"q46","type":"MCQ","topic":"AI","marks":1,"question":"GitHub Models OpenAI-compatible inference endpoint URL?","correct":1,"rationale":"`https://models.github.ai/inference` (source: SLM.docx). All other URLs are plausible-sounding fakes.","choices":["https://api.github.com/models","https://models.github.ai/inference","https://github.ai/v1/chat","https://copilot.github.com/api","https://models.githubusercontent.com"]},{"id":"q47","type":"MCQ","topic":"ML.NET","marks":1,"question":"Purpose of `new MLContext(seed: 0)`?","correct":1,"rationale":"The seed makes pipelines deterministic — same data + seed → same model (source: ML.NET.pptx). Not related to LLMs or hardware.","choices":["Seed the LLM sampler","Make training reproducible (determinism)","Set the number of GPU cores","Disable parallelism","Reset the model cache"]},{"id":"q48","type":"MCQ","topic":"ML.NET","marks":1,"question":"What is an `IDataView`?","correct":2,"rationale":"IDataView is immutable + lazy; enables streaming of huge datasets (source: ML.NET.pptx).","choices":["A GUI view of training data","A mutable array of records","An immutable, lazily-evaluated tabular data abstraction","A SQL result set","An HTTP JSON stream"]},{"id":"q49","type":"MCQ","topic":"ML.NET","marks":1,"question":"Save a trained ML.NET model to disk:","correct":2,"rationale":"Signature: `mlContext.Model.Save(model, schema, path)`. Schema is required so the re-loaded model knows its input column shape (source: ML.NET\\_VS2022\\_SCRIPT.docx).","choices":["model.Save(\"m.zip\")","mlContext.SaveModel(\"m.zip\", model)","mlContext.Model.Save(model, data.Schema, \"m.zip\")","model.Serialize(\"m.zip\")","mlContext.Persist(model, \"m.zip\")"]},{"id":"q50","type":"MCQ","topic":"ML.NET","marks":1,"question":"Class used to predict ONE record at a time?","correct":2,"rationale":"`PredictionEngine\u003cTIn,TOut\u003e` is type-safe single-record inference (source: ML.NET.pptx). ITransformer.Transform is batch.","choices":["ITransformer","IDataView","PredictionEngine\u003cTIn,TOut\u003e","MLContext","SinglePredictor"]},{"id":"q51","type":"MCQ","topic":"Cache","marks":1,"question":"Razor tag that caches an HTML fragment on the server?","correct":2,"rationale":"`\u003ccache\u003e` tag helper (source: Cache\\_Tag\\_Helper\\_SCRIPT.docx). Uses IMemoryCache under the hood.","choices":["\u003coutput-cache\u003e","\u003cfragment\u003e","\u003ccache\u003e","\u003cmemoize\u003e","\u003cserver-cache\u003e"]},{"id":"q52","type":"MCQ","topic":"Cache","marks":1,"question":"Single-call read-or-load pattern against IMemoryCache?","correct":2,"rationale":"`GetOrCreateAsync` is the ASP.NET Core idiom; the entry lambda configures expiry before the value is cached (source: DataCache\\_SCRIPT.docx).","choices":["\\_cache.LoadOrCreate(key, loader)","\\_cache.GetOrAdd(key, loader)","await \\_cache.GetOrCreateAsync(key, async entry =\u003e { entry.AbsoluteExpirationRelativeToNow = ...; return await Load(); })","\\_cache.ReadOrFetch(key, loader)","\\_cache.Miss(key, loader)"]},{"id":"q53","type":"MCQ","topic":"FileBased","marks":1,"question":"Directive referencing another .csproj from a file-based app?","correct":0,"rationale":"`#:project` (source: file-based-apps.pptx). Note: no space after the colon.","choices":["#:project ./lib/MyLib.csproj","#:ref ./lib/MyLib.csproj","#:include ./lib/MyLib.csproj","#:use ./lib/MyLib.csproj",""]},{"id":"q54","type":"MCQ","topic":"FileBased","marks":1,"question":"Directive setting an MSBuild property in a file-based app?","correct":1,"rationale":"`#:property Name=Value` maps one-for-one to MSBuild PropertyGroup entries (source: file-based-apps.pptx).","choices":["#:set LangVersion=preview","#:property LangVersion=preview","#:msbuild LangVersion=preview","preview","#:var LangVersion=preview"]},{"id":"q55","type":"MCQ","topic":"gRPC","marks":1,"question":"Directive to set the generated C# namespace in a .proto file?","correct":2,"rationale":"`option csharp_namespace = \"MyApp\";` (source: gRPC.pptx). `package` also affects namespace but as a fallback; the explicit option wins.","choices":["namespace MyApp;","package MyApp;","option csharp\\_namespace = \"MyApp\";","csharp { namespace = \"MyApp\"; }","#namespace MyApp"]},{"id":"q56","type":"MCQ","topic":"gRPC","marks":1,"question":"In a .proto message, what does the \"= 1\" after a field do?","correct":2,"rationale":"Field numbers identify the field on the wire — re-ordering fields in code is safe as long as numbers stay stable (source: gRPC.pptx). That is the whole point of protobuf schema evolution.","choices":["Default value","Required flag","Unique wire-format field number (stable identifier)","Position in generated C# class","Protobuf version tag"]},{"id":"q57","type":"MCQ","topic":"TDD","marks":1,"question":"xUnit interface for shared state across test methods IN ONE class?","correct":1,"rationale":"`IClassFixture\u003cTFx\u003e` — xUnit instantiates the fixture once per class and injects it via the constructor (source: TDD\\_xunit.pptx). `ICollectionFixture` is for sharing across classes.","choices":["ITestFixture\u003cT\u003e","IClassFixture\u003cT\u003e","ICollectionFixture\u003cT\u003e","ISharedContext\u003cT\u003e","IUseFixture\u003cT\u003e"]},{"id":"q58","type":"MCQ","topic":"Aspire","marks":1,"question":"Line every Aspire-aware service project calls to wire telemetry + discovery defaults?","correct":2,"rationale":"`builder.AddServiceDefaults()` comes from the ServiceDefaults shared project that each service references (source: aspire\\_SCRIPT.docx).","choices":["builder.UseAspire()","builder.AddAspireDefaults()","builder.AddServiceDefaults()","builder.Services.AddAspire()","builder.AddDistributed()"]},{"id":"q59","type":"MCQ","topic":"TagHelpers","marks":1,"question":"Base class + method to override when writing a CUSTOM tag helper?","correct":1,"rationale":"Derive from `TagHelper`; override `Process(context, output)` or its async variant (source: TagHelpers\\_SCRIPT.docx).","choices":["HtmlHelper · Render","TagHelper · Process / ProcessAsync","TagBuilder · Build","IHtmlTag · Emit","Component · OnRender"]},{"id":"q60","type":"MCQ","topic":"ExcelPDF","marks":1,"question":"Which TWO packages together enable PDF generation in the course lab?","correct":2,"rationale":"`itext7` (core) plus `itext.bouncy-castle-adapter` (crypto backend) — BOTH are required (source: Add package for PDF.html).","choices":["iTextSharp + pdfium","QuestPDF + QuestPDF.Fonts","itext7 + itext.bouncy-castle-adapter","PdfSharp + MigraDoc","Spire.PDF + Spire.License"]},{"id":"q61","type":"MCQ","topic":"Match","marks":1,"question":"Match — *Semantic Kernel entry point* →","correct":1,"rationale":"SK starts from the static `Kernel.CreateBuilder()` factory (source: CSharp\\_Meets\\_AI.pptx). `MLContext` is ML.NET; `DistributedApplication.CreateBuilder` is Aspire.","choices":["`MLContext`","`Kernel.CreateBuilder()`","`DistributedApplication.CreateBuilder(args)`","`new Kernel()`","`WebApplication.CreateBuilder(args)`"]},{"id":"q62","type":"MCQ","topic":"Match","marks":1,"question":"Match — *MCP stdio transport* →","correct":2,"rationale":"stdio = the MCP server runs as a co-located child process; host talks to it via stdin/stdout (source: SLM.pptx). SSE is the remote HTTP transport.","choices":["HTTP/2 server","WebSocket connection","Local process pipe (stdin/stdout)","Server-Sent Events over HTTPS","gRPC bidirectional stream"]},{"id":"q63","type":"MCQ","topic":"Match","marks":1,"question":"Match — *ML.NET entry point* →","correct":2,"rationale":"Every ML.NET program starts with `new MLContext(seed: 0)` (source: ML.NET.pptx). The others are downstream products of the pipeline.","choices":["`IDataView`","`Kernel`","`MLContext`","`PredictionEngine`","`ITransformer`"]},{"id":"q64","type":"MCQ","topic":"Match","marks":1,"question":"Match — *IMemoryCache failure mode* →","correct":2,"rationale":"MemoryCache is per-process — behind a load balancer, server A has no idea what server B cached (source: DataCache\\_SCRIPT.docx). Fix: `IDistributedCache` (Redis).","choices":["Runs out of RAM after 1000 entries","Thread-unsafe by default","Each server has its own cache — stale/inconsistent across a web farm","Requires a SQL Server backing store","Deprecated in .NET 8"]},{"id":"q65","type":"MCQ","topic":"Match","marks":1,"question":"Match — *gRPC .proto field identifier* →","correct":3,"rationale":"The wire format uses the number tag; the code order does not matter (source: gRPC.pptx). That is what makes protobuf schema-evolution safe.","choices":["Field name","Field position in the message","Field C# property index","Field number tag (`= 1`)","Field JSON key"]},{"id":"q66","type":"MCQ","topic":"Match","marks":1,"question":"Match — *xUnit parameterized test* →","correct":2,"rationale":"`[Theory]` marks a test as data-driven; `[InlineData]` rows ARE the test cases (source: TDD\\_xunit.pptx). `[TestCase]`/`[DataRow]` are NUnit/MSTest fakes here.","choices":["`[Fact]`","`[TestCase(...)]`","`[Theory] + [InlineData(...)]`","`[DataRow(...)]`","`[Parameterized]`"]},{"id":"q67","type":"MCQ","topic":"Match","marks":1,"question":"Match — *Aspire orchestration* →","correct":1,"rationale":"Aspire AppHost composes resources with `AddProject\u003cT\u003e`, `AddRedis`, etc., and wires dependencies with `.WithReference(...)` (source: aspire\\_SCRIPT.docx).","choices":["`AddMvc() / MapControllers()`","`AddProject\u003cT\u003e() / WithReference()`","`AddSignalR() / MapHub\u003cT\u003e()`","`AddGrpc() / MapGrpcService\u003cT\u003e()`","`UseRouting() / UseEndpoints()`"]},{"id":"q68","type":"MCQ","topic":"Match","marks":1,"question":"Match — *File-based C# package reference* →","correct":2,"rationale":"Directive form is `#:package Name@version` with NO space after the colon (source: file-based-apps.pptx). PackageReference is MSBuild (full project only).","choices":["`// #package X`","`#pragma package X`","`#:package X@version`","`\u003cPackageReference Include=\"X\"/\u003e`","`using package X`"]},{"id":"q69","type":"MCQ","topic":"Match","marks":1,"question":"Match — *Localization culture cookie name* →","correct":2,"rationale":"`CookieRequestCultureProvider.DefaultCookieName` resolves to the literal `.AspNetCore.Culture` (source: razor\\_pages\\_localization\\_SCRIPT.docx).","choices":["`culture=fr`","`.AspNet.Locale`","`.AspNetCore.Culture`","`__culture`","`AspNetCultureCookie`"]},{"id":"q70","type":"MCQ","topic":"Match","marks":1,"question":"Match — *Blazor QuickGrid column with HTML content* →","correct":2,"rationale":"Arbitrary HTML goes in a `TemplateColumn`; because the rendered content is not a bare property, sorting must be supplied explicitly with `SortBy` (source: BlazorServer\\_QuickGrid.docx).","choices":["`PropertyColumn` with `Sortable=\"true\"`","`DataColumn` with `Template`","`TemplateColumn` with `SortBy=\"@gridSort\"`","`GridColumn` with `RenderFragment`","`HtmlColumn` with `Content`"]},{"id":"q71","type":"SHORT","topic":"Coding","marks":10,"question":"Write a gRPC service contract and server implementation for a Calculator service.      Requirements:   1) Create a `.proto` file named `calculator.proto` defining a `Calculator` service with one RPC `Add(AddRequest)` returning `AddResponse`. AddRequest has two int32 fields (`a`, `b`). AddResponse has one int32 field (`sum`).   2) Register the service in `Program.cs`.   3) Implement the service class to return the sum.","correct":"See model solution below.","rationale":"**Marking rubric (10 marks):** proto syntax line + csharp\\_namespace (2) · service + rpc signature (2) · two messages with field tags (2) · AddGrpc + MapGrpcService (2) · correct override signature returning Task\u003cAddResponse\u003e (2)."}]},"lessons":[{"n":1,"id":"4870-lesson-prerequisites-the-asp-net-core-boot-sequence","title":"Prerequisites: the ASP.NET Core boot sequence","hook":"Every W7–13 topic plugs into the same skeleton: builder → services → app → middleware → Run. Learn the skeleton once.","tags":["aspnet-core"],"module":"Foundations","blocks":[{"kind":"p","html":"This lesson defines five terms that the other lessons use without explanation: \u003cstrong\u003eProgram.cs\u003c/strong\u003e, \u003cstrong\u003ebuilder\u003c/strong\u003e, \u003cstrong\u003eDI container\u003c/strong\u003e, \u003cstrong\u003emiddleware\u003c/strong\u003e, and \u003cstrong\u003eRun()\u003c/strong\u003e. Memorize the skeleton — every later lesson (SK, ML.NET, Cache, gRPC, xUnit-in-an-ASP.NET host, Aspire, Localization, Tag Helpers) extends exactly this skeleton.","text":"This lesson defines five terms that the other lessons use without explanation: **Program.cs**, **builder**, **DI container**, **middleware**, and **Run()**. Memorize the skeleton — every later lesson (SK, ML.NET, Cache, gRPC, xUnit-in-an-ASP.NET host, Aspire, Localization, Tag Helpers) extends exactly this skeleton."},{"kind":"callout","variant":"analogy","html":"\u003cp\u003e Program.cs is the front door of your app. The \u003ccode\u003ebuilder\u003c/code\u003e is the contractor who prepares the building (wires up services). \u003ccode\u003eapp.Run()\u003c/code\u003e opens the door to visitors (HTTP requests). Middleware is the line of receptionists each request passes through before reaching a controller/page.\u003c/p\u003e","text":" Program.cs is the front door of your app. The `builder` is the contractor who prepares the building (wires up services). `app.Run()` opens the door to visitors (HTTP requests). Middleware is the line of receptionists each request passes through before reaching a controller/page."},{"kind":"h3","html":"The 5-step skeleton at a glance","text":"The 5-step skeleton at a glance"},{"kind":"mermaid","source":"flowchart LR\n  A[\"1. CreateBuilder\u003cbr/\u003ebuilder = WebApplication\u003cbr/\u003e.CreateBuilder(args)\"] --\u003e B[\"2. AddX\u003cbr/\u003ebuilder.Services.AddX()\u003cbr/\u003e(DI registrations)\"]\n  B --\u003e C[\"3. Build\u003cbr/\u003eapp = builder.Build()\u003cbr/\u003elocks DI container\"]\n  C --\u003e D[\"4. UseX / MapX\u003cbr/\u003emiddleware pipeline\u003cbr/\u003e(order matters)\"]\n  D --\u003e E[\"5. Run\u003cbr/\u003eapp.Run()\u003cbr/\u003eblocks until shutdown\"]\n  classDef step fill:#2a3a4a,stroke:#7aa2f7,color:#e5e5e5\n  classDef lock fill:#3a3528,stroke:#e3af68,color:#e3af68\n  classDef end1 fill:#2d3a2d,stroke:#9ece6a,color:#9ece6a\n  class A,B,D step\n  class C lock\n  class E end1"},{"kind":"p","html":"\u003cstrong\u003eLocked order:\u003c/strong\u003e you can&#39;t \u003ccode\u003eAddX\u003c/code\u003e after \u003ccode\u003eBuild\u003c/code\u003e (container is sealed) and \u003ccode\u003eRun\u003c/code\u003e must be last (it blocks). Every later W7–13 lesson edits step 2 and/or step 4.","text":"**Locked order:** you can't `AddX` after `Build` (container is sealed) and `Run` must be last (it blocks). Every later W7–13 lesson edits step 2 and/or step 4."},{"kind":"h3","html":"The minimal skeleton","text":"The minimal skeleton"},{"kind":"code","lang":"cs","code":"// Program.cs — the single bootstrap file in .NET 6+ (no Startup.cs)\nvar builder = WebApplication.CreateBuilder(args); // 1. contractor shows up\nbuilder.Services.AddControllers();                 // 2. register services into DI container\n// builder.Services.AddMemoryCache();              //    (examples you'll see again: caching)\n// builder.Services.AddGrpc();                     //    (gRPC lesson)\n// builder.Services.AddLocalization(...);          //    (localization lesson)\n\nvar app = builder.Build();                         // 3. produce the WebApplication host\n\napp.UseRouting();                                  // 4. middleware pipeline (order matters)\napp.UseAuthorization();\napp.MapControllers();                              //    map endpoints\n// app.MapGrpcService\u003cGreeterImpl\u003e();             //    endpoints for gRPC / Razor / Blazor / SignalR\n\napp.Run();                                         // 5. open the door — blocks until shutdown"},{"kind":"h3","html":"Five terms the later lessons assume","text":"Five terms the later lessons assume"},{"kind":"p","html":"\u003col\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eProgram.cs\u003c/strong\u003e — single entry-point file introduced by .NET 6 minimal hosting. Replaces the old \u003ccode\u003eStartup.cs\u003c/code\u003e + \u003ccode\u003eProgram.cs\u003c/code\u003e pair. You will see EVERY later lesson edit this file.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003ebuilder\u003c/strong\u003e — object returned by \u003ccode\u003eWebApplication.CreateBuilder(args)\u003c/code\u003e. Exposes \u003ccode\u003ebuilder.Services\u003c/code\u003e (DI registration) and \u003ccode\u003ebuilder.Configuration\u003c/code\u003e (appsettings.json access).\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eDI container\u003c/strong\u003e — \u003ccode\u003eIServiceCollection\u003c/code\u003e accessed via \u003ccode\u003ebuilder.Services\u003c/code\u003e. When you write \u003ccode\u003ebuilder.Services.AddMemoryCache()\u003c/code\u003e, you are saying &quot;anywhere in the app that asks for \u003ccode\u003eIMemoryCache\u003c/code\u003e, hand them this&quot;. The container resolves types automatically via constructor injection.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eMiddleware\u003c/strong\u003e — components chained with \u003ccode\u003eapp.Use...\u003c/code\u003e that each request passes through in order. \u003ccode\u003eUseRouting\u003c/code\u003e before \u003ccode\u003eUseAuthorization\u003c/code\u003e is mandatory because routing decides which endpoint matches BEFORE authorization checks the endpoint&#39;s policy.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eRun()\u003c/strong\u003e — \u003ccode\u003eapp.Run()\u003c/code\u003e starts Kestrel and blocks until the process is stopped. Every later lesson&#39;s code eventually ends here; it is often omitted from snippets because it is identical everywhere.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ol\u003e","text":"1.  **Program.cs** — single entry-point file introduced by .NET 6 minimal hosting. Replaces the old `Startup.cs` + `Program.cs` pair. You will see EVERY later lesson edit this file.\n2.  **builder** — object returned by `WebApplication.CreateBuilder(args)`. Exposes `builder.Services` (DI registration) and `builder.Configuration` (appsettings.json access).\n3.  **DI container** — `IServiceCollection` accessed via `builder.Services`. When you write `builder.Services.AddMemoryCache()`, you are saying \"anywhere in the app that asks for `IMemoryCache`, hand them this\". The container resolves types automatically via constructor injection.\n4.  **Middleware** — components chained with `app.Use...` that each request passes through in order. `UseRouting` before `UseAuthorization` is mandatory because routing decides which endpoint matches BEFORE authorization checks the endpoint's policy.\n5.  **Run()** — `app.Run()` starts Kestrel and blocks until the process is stopped. Every later lesson's code eventually ends here; it is often omitted from snippets because it is identical everywhere."},{"kind":"h3","html":"Why this matters for the W7–13 exam","text":"Why this matters for the W7–13 exam"},{"kind":"p","html":"Every coding-question skeleton (gRPC, ML.NET ASP.NET host, Aspire, Cache, Localization, Tag Helpers) is a variation on this 5-step template. If you remember the skeleton, an exam question that adds \u003cem\u003eone new line\u003c/em\u003e (e.g. \u003ccode\u003ebuilder.Services.AddGrpc()\u003c/code\u003e) is instantly recognizable rather than novel.","text":"Every coding-question skeleton (gRPC, ML.NET ASP.NET host, Aspire, Cache, Localization, Tag Helpers) is a variation on this 5-step template. If you remember the skeleton, an exam question that adds *one new line* (e.g. `builder.Services.AddGrpc()`) is instantly recognizable rather than novel."},{"kind":"checkpoint","q":"**Checkpoint —** Without looking, in what order do these four calls appear in Program.cs? `app.Run()`, `builder.Services.AddX()`, `var builder = WebApplication.CreateBuilder(args)`, `var app = builder.Build()`. Click to reveal.","a":"`CreateBuilder` → `AddX` → `Build` → `Run`. The order is locked: you cannot `AddX` after `Build`, and `Run` must be last because it blocks."},{"kind":"callout","variant":"note","html":"\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eTakeaway —\u003c/strong\u003e CreateBuilder → AddX → Build → UseX/MapX → Run. Five terms, one skeleton. Every W7–13 lesson is &quot;which line do you add in step 2 and step 4?&quot;.\u003c/p\u003e","text":"**Takeaway —** CreateBuilder → AddX → Build → UseX/MapX → Run. Five terms, one skeleton. Every W7–13 lesson is \"which line do you add in step 2 and step 4?\"."}]},{"n":2,"id":"4870-lesson-semantic-kernel-and-chat-completion","title":"Semantic Kernel and chat completion","hook":"SK is Microsoft's AI glue. Build a Kernel, feed it messages, let it call plugins.","tags":["semantic-kernel"],"module":"AI & ML.NET","blocks":[{"kind":"p","html":"\u003cstrong\u003eSemantic Kernel (SK)\u003c/strong\u003e orchestrates LLM calls. You build a \u003ccode\u003eKernel\u003c/code\u003e, it exposes \u003ccode\u003eIChatCompletionService\u003c/code\u003e, you hand it a \u003ccode\u003eChatHistory\u003c/code\u003e with messages, it returns a response.","text":"**Semantic Kernel (SK)** orchestrates LLM calls. You build a `Kernel`, it exposes `IChatCompletionService`, you hand it a `ChatHistory` with messages, it returns a response."},{"kind":"callout","variant":"analogy","html":"\u003cp\u003e Kernel is a kitchen. Plugins are ingredients. ChatHistory is the conversation log. The chef (LLM) cooks responses based on what&#39;s in the log.\u003c/p\u003e","text":" Kernel is a kitchen. Plugins are ingredients. ChatHistory is the conversation log. The chef (LLM) cooks responses based on what's in the log."},{"kind":"code","lang":"cs","code":"// Program.cs — register SK\nvar builder = Kernel.CreateBuilder();\nbuilder.AddOllamaChatCompletion(\"llama3\", new Uri(\"http://localhost:11434\"));\n// OR GitHub Models endpoint: https://models.github.ai/inference\nKernel kernel = builder.Build();\nvar chat = kernel.GetRequiredService\u003cIChatCompletionService\u003e();\nvar history = new ChatHistory(\"You are helpful.\");\nhistory.AddUserMessage(\"Hello\");\nvar reply = await chat.GetChatMessageContentAsync(history, kernel: kernel);"},{"kind":"p","html":"\u003cstrong\u003ePlugins:\u003c/strong\u003e C# classes decorated with \u003ccode\u003e[KernelFunction]\u003c/code\u003e. Register via \u003ccode\u003ekernel.ImportPluginFromType&lt;T&gt;()\u003c/code\u003e or \u003ccode\u003eImportPluginFromPromptDirectory\u003c/code\u003e for skprompt.txt plugins.","text":"**Plugins:** C# classes decorated with `[KernelFunction]`. Register via `kernel.ImportPluginFromType\u003cT\u003e()` or `ImportPluginFromPromptDirectory` for skprompt.txt plugins."},{"kind":"h3","html":"The SK call chain","text":"The SK call chain"},{"kind":"mermaid","source":"flowchart TB\n  B[\"Kernel.CreateBuilder()\"] --\u003e AD[\"AddOllamaChatCompletion / AddOpenAIChatCompletion\"]\n  AD --\u003e K[\"Kernel = Build()\"]\n  K -- \"GetRequiredService\u003cIChatCompletionService\u003e\" --\u003e CS[IChatCompletionService]\n  K -- \"ImportPluginFromType\u003cT\u003e\" --\u003e PL[\"Plugin\u003cbr/\u003e[KernelFunction]\"]\n  H[\"ChatHistory('system')\u003cbr/\u003e.AddUserMessage(...)\"] --\u003e CS\n  CS -- GetChatMessageContentAsync --\u003e OUT[response]"},{"kind":"checkpoint","q":"**Checkpoint —** You have a built `Kernel` and want to send a user question. Which object do you resolve first, what do you construct, and what method returns the model's reply? Name all three.","a":"Resolve `IChatCompletionService` via `kernel.GetRequiredService\u003cIChatCompletionService\u003e()`. Construct a `ChatHistory` (optionally seeded with a system message), then `history.AddUserMessage(\"...\")`. Call `await chat.GetChatMessageContentAsync(history, kernel: kernel)` — its result's `.Content` is the reply string."},{"kind":"callout","variant":"note","html":"\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eTakeaway —\u003c/strong\u003e Kernel + ChatHistory + IChatCompletionService is the trio. Memorize this chain.\u003c/p\u003e","text":"**Takeaway —** Kernel + ChatHistory + IChatCompletionService is the trio. Memorize this chain."}]},{"n":3,"id":"4870-lesson-microsoft-agent-framework-maf-and-mcp","title":"Microsoft Agent Framework (MAF) and MCP","hook":"MAF is SK's bigger sibling — agents with memory, tools, planners. MCP is tool transport.","tags":["maf","mcp"],"module":"AI & ML.NET","blocks":[{"kind":"p","html":"\u003cstrong\u003eMAF\u003c/strong\u003e (Microsoft.Agents.AI) wraps an LLM into an \u003ccode\u003eAIAgent\u003c/code\u003e. It uses \u003ccode\u003eAIFunction\u003c/code\u003e (one tool) built via \u003ccode\u003eAIFunctionFactory.Create(delegate)\u003c/code\u003e.","text":"**MAF** (Microsoft.Agents.AI) wraps an LLM into an `AIAgent`. It uses `AIFunction` (one tool) built via `AIFunctionFactory.Create(delegate)`."},{"kind":"code","lang":"cs","code":"// MAF agent with tools\nvar client = new OpenAIClient(...); // points to GitHub Models or Ollama\nvar agent = client.AsAIAgent(\"gpt-4o-mini\");\nvar tool = AIFunctionFactory.Create(GetWeather, \"get_weather\", \"Get weather\");\nagent.Tools.Add(tool);\nvar session = new AgentSession(agent);\nawait foreach (var update in session.RunStreamingAsync(\"What's the weather?\")) {\n    Console.Write(update);\n}"},{"kind":"callout","variant":"analogy","html":"\u003cp\u003e SK = calling a chef on the phone for each order (you pass the full ChatHistory every call). MAF + AgentSession = a chef who remembers THIS conversation (the session tracks messages across calls within one session — NOT across app restarts). MCP = a universal plug that any kitchen tool honours — the AI host speaks one protocol, any MCP server can respond.\u003c/p\u003e","text":" SK = calling a chef on the phone for each order (you pass the full ChatHistory every call). MAF + AgentSession = a chef who remembers THIS conversation (the session tracks messages across calls within one session — NOT across app restarts). MCP = a universal plug that any kitchen tool honours — the AI host speaks one protocol, any MCP server can respond."},{"kind":"p","html":"\u003cstrong\u003eScope warning (exam trap):\u003c/strong\u003e \u003ccode\u003eAgentSession\u003c/code\u003e holds multi-turn history WITHIN one session object. It does not by itself persist between app runs — if you want persistence you save/restore the history yourself (source: AI-Models_MAF_SCRIPT.docx).","text":"**Scope warning (exam trap):** `AgentSession` holds multi-turn history WITHIN one session object. It does not by itself persist between app runs — if you want persistence you save/restore the history yourself (source: AI-Models\\_MAF\\_SCRIPT.docx)."},{"kind":"p","html":"\u003cstrong\u003eMCP (Model Context Protocol):\u003c/strong\u003e Transport for AI tools. Two transports:","text":"**MCP (Model Context Protocol):** Transport for AI tools. Two transports:"},{"kind":"p","html":"\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003ccode\u003estdio\u003c/code\u003e — local process over stdin/stdout\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003ccode\u003eSSE\u003c/code\u003e — Server-Sent Events over HTTP (cloud)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e","text":"-   `stdio` — local process over stdin/stdout\n-   `SSE` — Server-Sent Events over HTTP (cloud)"},{"kind":"h3","html":"MAF agent stack","text":"MAF agent stack"},{"kind":"mermaid","source":"flowchart TB\n  C[OpenAIClient / GitHub Models] -- \".AsAIAgent('gpt-4o-mini')\" --\u003e A[AIAgent]\n  A -- \"agent.Tools.Add(tool)\" --\u003e F[\"AIFunction\u003cbr/\u003eAIFunctionFactory.Create\"]\n  A --\u003e S[\"AgentSession\u003cbr/\u003eholds multi-turn history\"]\n  S -- \"RunAsync / RunStreamingAsync\" --\u003e R[\"Response\u003cbr/\u003eor token stream\"]"},{"kind":"h3","html":"MCP transports — stdio vs SSE","text":"MCP transports — stdio vs SSE"},{"kind":"mermaid","source":"flowchart LR\n  subgraph STDIO[\"stdio (LOCAL)\"]\n  H1[AI Host] \u003c-. stdin/stdout .-\u003e T1[\"MCP Server\u003cbr/\u003eco-located process\"]\n  end\n  subgraph SSE[\"SSE (REMOTE / CLOUD)\"]\n  H2[AI Host] \u003c-. HTTP SSE .-\u003e T2[\"MCP Server\u003cbr/\u003eAzure Functions HTTPS\"]\n  end"},{"kind":"checkpoint","q":"**Checkpoint —** An MCP server runs as a Python process on the same machine as your .NET host. Which transport do you configure, and what is the concrete mechanism it uses to pass messages?","a":"**stdio**. The host spawns the MCP server as a child process and exchanges JSON-RPC messages over the child's stdin/stdout. No TCP port, no HTTP — just a process pipe. SSE would be wrong because the server is not network-addressable."},{"kind":"callout","variant":"note","html":"\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eTakeaway —\u003c/strong\u003e AsAIAgent() converts a model client into an agent. AIFunctionFactory.Create() wraps a C# method into a tool.\u003c/p\u003e","text":"**Takeaway —** AsAIAgent() converts a model client into an agent. AIFunctionFactory.Create() wraps a C# method into a tool."}]},{"n":4,"id":"4870-lesson-ml-net-seven-steps-to-a-model","title":"ML.NET: seven steps to a model","hook":"ML.NET is always: context → load → split → pipeline → fit → evaluate → save.","tags":["ml-net"],"module":"AI & ML.NET","blocks":[{"kind":"p","html":"Every ML.NET program follows the same seven steps. The code below shows each step in isolation with a \u003cem\u003ewhy\u003c/em\u003e — if you can explain each why on the exam, you can transfer the pattern to a new dataset.","text":"Every ML.NET program follows the same seven steps. The code below shows each step in isolation with a *why* — if you can explain each why on the exam, you can transfer the pattern to a new dataset."},{"kind":"callout","variant":"analogy","html":"\u003cp\u003e MLContext is the lab. IDataView is a raw sample jar. The pipeline is the lab protocol. Fit() runs the experiment. ITransformer is the recipe you save for next time.\u003c/p\u003e","text":" MLContext is the lab. IDataView is a raw sample jar. The pipeline is the lab protocol. Fit() runs the experiment. ITransformer is the recipe you save for next time."},{"kind":"h3","html":"Step 1 — Context","text":"Step 1 — Context"},{"kind":"code","lang":"cs","code":"var mlContext = new MLContext(seed: 0);"},{"kind":"p","html":"\u003cem\u003eWhy:\u003c/em\u003e every ML.NET API hangs off this object — \u003ccode\u003eData\u003c/code\u003e, \u003ccode\u003eTransforms\u003c/code\u003e, \u003ccode\u003eRegression\u003c/code\u003e, \u003ccode\u003eModel\u003c/code\u003e. The \u003ccode\u003eseed: 0\u003c/code\u003e makes training \u003cstrong\u003edeterministic\u003c/strong\u003e: same input + same seed → same model. Without a seed, random initialization gives a slightly different model every run and you cannot reproduce a bug.","text":"*Why:* every ML.NET API hangs off this object — `Data`, `Transforms`, `Regression`, `Model`. The `seed: 0` makes training **deterministic**: same input + same seed → same model. Without a seed, random initialization gives a slightly different model every run and you cannot reproduce a bug."},{"kind":"h3","html":"Step 2 — Load","text":"Step 2 — Load"},{"kind":"code","lang":"cs","code":"IDataView data = mlContext.Data.LoadFromTextFile\u003cTaxiTrip\u003e(\"taxi.csv\", hasHeader: true, separatorChar: ',');"},{"kind":"p","html":"\u003cem\u003eWhy:\u003c/em\u003e \u003ccode\u003eLoadFromTextFile&lt;T&gt;\u003c/code\u003e is lazy — it does not read the whole file into memory. The generic \u003ccode\u003e&lt;TaxiTrip&gt;\u003c/code\u003e tells ML.NET the column layout via \u003ccode\u003e[LoadColumn(n)]\u003c/code\u003e attributes on the class. \u003ccode\u003ehasHeader: true\u003c/code\u003e skips the first row; forgetting this makes the header parse as data and training blows up.","text":"*Why:* `LoadFromTextFile\u003cT\u003e` is lazy — it does not read the whole file into memory. The generic `\u003cTaxiTrip\u003e` tells ML.NET the column layout via `[LoadColumn(n)]` attributes on the class. `hasHeader: true` skips the first row; forgetting this makes the header parse as data and training blows up."},{"kind":"h3","html":"Step 3 — Split","text":"Step 3 — Split"},{"kind":"code","lang":"cs","code":"var split = mlContext.Data.TrainTestSplit(data, testFraction: 0.2);"},{"kind":"p","html":"\u003cem\u003eWhy 0.2:\u003c/em\u003e 80/20 is the default because it keeps enough data to train on while leaving a held-out set large enough to estimate real-world error. Training on 100% of your data gives optimistic metrics — the model has memorized the test set.","text":"*Why 0.2:* 80/20 is the default because it keeps enough data to train on while leaving a held-out set large enough to estimate real-world error. Training on 100% of your data gives optimistic metrics — the model has memorized the test set."},{"kind":"h3","html":"Step 4 — Pipeline","text":"Step 4 — Pipeline"},{"kind":"code","lang":"cs","code":"var pipeline = mlContext.Transforms.CopyColumns(\"Label\", \"FareAmount\")\n    .Append(mlContext.Transforms.Categorical.OneHotEncoding(\"VendorIdEncoded\", \"VendorId\"))\n    .Append(mlContext.Transforms.Concatenate(\"Features\", \"VendorIdEncoded\", \"TripDistance\"))\n    .Append(mlContext.Regression.Trainers.FastTree());"},{"kind":"p","html":"\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eCopyColumns(&quot;Label&quot;, &quot;FareAmount&quot;)\u003c/strong\u003e — trainers expect a column literally named \u003ccode\u003eLabel\u003c/code\u003e. You rename your target so the trainer finds it.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eOneHotEncoding\u003c/strong\u003e — trainers cannot consume strings directly. \u003ccode\u003eVendorId\u003c/code\u003e (e.g. &quot;VTS&quot;) becomes a numeric vector. This is required for every string/categorical input.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eConcatenate(&quot;Features&quot;, ...)\u003c/strong\u003e — trainers expect ONE column literally named \u003ccode\u003eFeatures\u003c/code\u003e. You glue all numeric predictors into that single vector. Skipping this step is the most common beginner bug.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eFastTree()\u003c/strong\u003e — the trainer itself. Swap in \u003ccode\u003eSdca\u003c/code\u003e or \u003ccode\u003eLightGbm\u003c/code\u003e to compare. Note the pipeline is still just a recipe — no training has happened yet.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e","text":"-   **CopyColumns(\"Label\", \"FareAmount\")** — trainers expect a column literally named `Label`. You rename your target so the trainer finds it.\n-   **OneHotEncoding** — trainers cannot consume strings directly. `VendorId` (e.g. \"VTS\") becomes a numeric vector. This is required for every string/categorical input.\n-   **Concatenate(\"Features\", ...)** — trainers expect ONE column literally named `Features`. You glue all numeric predictors into that single vector. Skipping this step is the most common beginner bug.\n-   **FastTree()** — the trainer itself. Swap in `Sdca` or `LightGbm` to compare. Note the pipeline is still just a recipe — no training has happened yet."},{"kind":"h3","html":"Step 5 — Fit","text":"Step 5 — Fit"},{"kind":"code","lang":"cs","code":"ITransformer model = pipeline.Fit(split.TrainSet);"},{"kind":"p","html":"\u003cem\u003eWhy ITransformer, not PredictionEngine:\u003c/em\u003e \u003ccode\u003eFit\u003c/code\u003e returns a stateless, serializable recipe that can re-run on any IDataView. \u003ccode\u003ePredictionEngine\u003c/code\u003e is the \u003cem\u003esingle-record\u003c/em\u003e convenience wrapper you build LATER from this model. Always say &quot;Fit returns ITransformer&quot; — the distractor is &quot;returns predictions&quot;.","text":"*Why ITransformer, not PredictionEngine:* `Fit` returns a stateless, serializable recipe that can re-run on any IDataView. `PredictionEngine` is the *single-record* convenience wrapper you build LATER from this model. Always say \"Fit returns ITransformer\" — the distractor is \"returns predictions\"."},{"kind":"h3","html":"Step 6 — Evaluate","text":"Step 6 — Evaluate"},{"kind":"code","lang":"cs","code":"var predictions = model.Transform(split.TestSet);\nvar metrics = mlContext.Regression.Evaluate(predictions, \"Label\");\nConsole.WriteLine($\"R²: {metrics.RSquared}\");"},{"kind":"p","html":"\u003cem\u003eWhy \u003ccode\u003eTransform\u003c/code\u003e before \u003ccode\u003eEvaluate\u003c/code\u003e:\u003c/em\u003e Evaluate does not train anything — it compares predicted \u003ccode\u003eScore\u003c/code\u003e to actual \u003ccode\u003eLabel\u003c/code\u003e row-by-row. You must run the held-out test set through the trained model first. \u003ccode\u003eRSquared\u003c/code\u003e lives in [0, 1]; closer to 1 means the model explains more of the variance.","text":"*Why `Transform` before `Evaluate`:* Evaluate does not train anything — it compares predicted `Score` to actual `Label` row-by-row. You must run the held-out test set through the trained model first. `RSquared` lives in \\[0, 1\\]; closer to 1 means the model explains more of the variance."},{"kind":"h3","html":"Step 7 — Save","text":"Step 7 — Save"},{"kind":"code","lang":"cs","code":"mlContext.Model.Save(model, data.Schema, \"model.zip\");"},{"kind":"p","html":"\u003cem\u003eWhy the schema is required:\u003c/em\u003e the saved ZIP stores both the trained transformer AND the input column layout. On reload, ML.NET uses the schema to validate that incoming data has the expected column names and types. Saving without schema would produce a model that cannot safely consume new data.","text":"*Why the schema is required:* the saved ZIP stores both the trained transformer AND the input column layout. On reload, ML.NET uses the schema to validate that incoming data has the expected column names and types. Saving without schema would produce a model that cannot safely consume new data."},{"kind":"h3","html":"The 7-step pipeline — memorize the shape","text":"The 7-step pipeline — memorize the shape"},{"kind":"mermaid","source":"flowchart LR\n  M[MLContext] --\u003e L[\"LoadFromTextFile\u003cT\u003e\u003cbr/\u003eIDataView\"]\n  L --\u003e T[TrainTestSplit 0.2]\n  T --\u003e P[\"pipeline:\u003cbr/\u003eConcatenate + Trainer\"]\n  P --\u003e F[\"Fit() → ITransformer\"]\n  F --\u003e E[\"Evaluate()\u003cbr/\u003eRSquared / RMSE\"]\n  E --\u003e V[\"Model.Save('m.zip')\"]"},{"kind":"h3","html":"Trainer namespaces by task","text":"Trainer namespaces by task"},{"kind":"mermaid","source":"flowchart TB\n  ML[mlContext]\n  ML --\u003e REG[\".Regression.Trainers\u003cbr/\u003eFastTree, Sdca\"]\n  ML --\u003e BIN[\".BinaryClassification.Trainers\u003cbr/\u003eLogistic\"]\n  ML --\u003e MC[\".MulticlassClassification.Trainers\u003cbr/\u003eNaiveBayes\"]\n  ML --\u003e CL[\".Clustering.Trainers\u003cbr/\u003eKMeans\"]"},{"kind":"callout","variant":"warning","html":"\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eCommon mistakes (sourced from ML.NET.pptx slide warnings):\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eWrong column name\u003c/strong\u003e — trainers expect \u003ccode\u003eLabel\u003c/code\u003e and \u003ccode\u003eFeatures\u003c/code\u003e EXACTLY. Naming them \u003ccode\u003eTarget\u003c/code\u003e and \u003ccode\u003eInputs\u003c/code\u003e compiles but throws at Fit.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eSkipping Concatenate\u003c/strong\u003e — with 10 feature columns and no \u003ccode\u003eConcatenate(&quot;Features&quot;, ...)\u003c/code\u003e, the trainer cannot locate its input. Symptom: &quot;Features column not found&quot; at Fit.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eLabel vs Score confusion\u003c/strong\u003e — in the TRAIN class the target is the \u003ccode\u003eLabel\u003c/code\u003e column (what you know). In the PREDICT class the output is decorated \u003ccode\u003e[ColumnName(&quot;Score&quot;)]\u003c/code\u003e (what the model produces). They are different columns.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003ePicking accuracy for regression\u003c/strong\u003e — \u003ccode\u003eAccuracy\u003c/code\u003e is a classification metric. For regression use \u003ccode\u003eRSquared\u003c/code\u003e / \u003ccode\u003eRMSE\u003c/code\u003e; for multi-class use \u003ccode\u003eMacroAccuracy\u003c/code\u003e / \u003ccode\u003eLogLoss\u003c/code\u003e.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e","text":"**Common mistakes (sourced from ML.NET.pptx slide warnings):**\n-   **Wrong column name** — trainers expect `Label` and `Features` EXACTLY. Naming them `Target` and `Inputs` compiles but throws at Fit.\n-   **Skipping Concatenate** — with 10 feature columns and no `Concatenate(\"Features\", ...)`, the trainer cannot locate its input. Symptom: \"Features column not found\" at Fit.\n-   **Label vs Score confusion** — in the TRAIN class the target is the `Label` column (what you know). In the PREDICT class the output is decorated `[ColumnName(\"Score\")]` (what the model produces). They are different columns.\n-   **Picking accuracy for regression** — `Accuracy` is a classification metric. For regression use `RSquared` / `RMSE`; for multi-class use `MacroAccuracy` / `LogLoss`."},{"kind":"checkpoint","q":"**Checkpoint —** Without looking: what does `pipeline.Fit(trainSet)` return, and why is that the right return type (not, say, the predictions themselves)?","a":"Returns `ITransformer`. That is correct because the trained pipeline is a reusable, stateless recipe — you can Transform any future IDataView with the same schema, save it to disk, and load it in a separate prediction service. If Fit returned predictions, you would have to retrain to score new data."},{"kind":"callout","variant":"note","html":"\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eTakeaway —\u003c/strong\u003e Fit() returns ITransformer. LoadFromTextFile returns IDataView. RSquared is closer-to-1 = better for regression.\u003c/p\u003e","text":"**Takeaway —** Fit() returns ITransformer. LoadFromTextFile returns IDataView. RSquared is closer-to-1 = better for regression."}]},{"n":5,"id":"4870-lesson-caching-three-strategies-for-one-problem","title":"Caching: three strategies for one problem","hook":"Cache = \"don't recompute what you already know\". Three flavors, one pitfall.","tags":["cache"],"module":"Misc","blocks":[{"kind":"p","html":"ASP.NET Core gives you three caching primitives. You must be able to pick between them on the exam — the choice is never arbitrary.","text":"ASP.NET Core gives you three caching primitives. You must be able to pick between them on the exam — the choice is never arbitrary."},{"kind":"p","html":"\u003col\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eIMemoryCache\u003c/strong\u003e — per-process RAM. \u003cem\u003ePick it when\u003c/em\u003e the app runs on exactly one server (dev, single-VM prod, or a single Docker container). \u003cem\u003eWhy not always:\u003c/em\u003e behind a load balancer, server A has no visibility into server B&#39;s cache. A logged-in user who bounces between servers sees stale or inconsistent data.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eIDistributedCache (Redis)\u003c/strong\u003e — shared storage behind a network call. \u003cem\u003ePick it when\u003c/em\u003e the app runs on 2+ servers (web farm, Kubernetes, App Service with scale-out). \u003cem\u003eCost:\u003c/em\u003e a network round-trip per cache op; values must be serializable (string or byte[]). Solves the consistency problem that kills MemoryCache in farms.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eCache Tag Helper\u003c/strong\u003e — a Razor \u003ccode\u003e&lt;cache&gt;\u003c/code\u003e element that caches rendered HTML fragments. \u003cem\u003ePick it when\u003c/em\u003e the expensive thing is \u003cem\u003erendering\u003c/em\u003e (view model → HTML), not the data itself. \u003cem\u003eUnder the hood:\u003c/em\u003e it writes into IMemoryCache, so the single-server caveat still applies.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ol\u003e","text":"1.  **IMemoryCache** — per-process RAM. *Pick it when* the app runs on exactly one server (dev, single-VM prod, or a single Docker container). *Why not always:* behind a load balancer, server A has no visibility into server B's cache. A logged-in user who bounces between servers sees stale or inconsistent data.\n2.  **IDistributedCache (Redis)** — shared storage behind a network call. *Pick it when* the app runs on 2+ servers (web farm, Kubernetes, App Service with scale-out). *Cost:* a network round-trip per cache op; values must be serializable (string or byte\\[\\]). Solves the consistency problem that kills MemoryCache in farms.\n3.  **Cache Tag Helper** — a Razor `\u003ccache\u003e` element that caches rendered HTML fragments. *Pick it when* the expensive thing is *rendering* (view model → HTML), not the data itself. *Under the hood:* it writes into IMemoryCache, so the single-server caveat still applies."},{"kind":"code","lang":"cs","code":"// In-memory\nbuilder.Services.AddMemoryCache();\nif (!_cache.TryGetValue(\"key\", out Data val)) {\n    val = LoadFromDb();\n    _cache.Set(\"key\", val, new MemoryCacheEntryOptions {\n        AbsoluteExpirationRelativeToNow = TimeSpan.FromMinutes(10),\n        SlidingExpiration = TimeSpan.FromMinutes(2)\n    });\n}\n// Redis\nbuilder.Services.AddStackExchangeRedisCache(o =\u003e o.Configuration = \"localhost:6379\");\nawait _redis.SetStringAsync(\"key\", json);\n// Tag helper\n\u003ccache expires-after=\"@TimeSpan.FromMinutes(10)\" vary-by-user=\"true\"\u003e\u003cpartial name=\"_Expensive\" /\u003e\u003c/cache\u003e"},{"kind":"callout","variant":"analogy","html":"\u003cp\u003e MemoryCache = sticky notes on YOUR desk. Redis = shared whiteboard in hallway. Cache tag helper = laminated HTML fragment.\u003c/p\u003e","text":" MemoryCache = sticky notes on YOUR desk. Redis = shared whiteboard in hallway. Cache tag helper = laminated HTML fragment."},{"kind":"h3","html":"Which cache strategy? Decision tree","text":"Which cache strategy? Decision tree"},{"kind":"mermaid","source":"flowchart TD\n  Q{Caching need?}\n  Q --\u003e|1 server only| IM[\"IMemoryCache\u003cbr/\u003eAddMemoryCache\"]\n  Q --\u003e|web farm / load-balanced| DC[\"IDistributedCache\u003cbr/\u003eAddStackExchangeRedisCache\"]\n  Q --\u003e|Razor HTML fragment| CT[\"\u003ccache vary-by-* expires-after\u003e\u003cbr/\u003etag helper\"]\n  CT -.uses under the hood.-\u003e IM"},{"kind":"callout","variant":"warning","html":"\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eCommon mistakes (sourced from DataCache_SCRIPT.docx slide warnings):\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eConfusing Absolute with Sliding\u003c/strong\u003e — Absolute is a hard deadline; the entry dies at T+10 minutes no matter how often you read it. Sliding resets to &quot;idle-for-2-minutes&quot; on every access. Combine both → whichever fires first wins.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eExpecting MemoryCache to survive app restarts\u003c/strong\u003e — it is in-process RAM. A recycle, redeploy, or crash empties it. Redis persists.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eRegistering \u003ccode\u003eAddMemoryCache()\u003c/code\u003e but injecting \u003ccode\u003eIDistributedCache\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/strong\u003e — these are different registrations. Swapping requires both the service registration and the interface type.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eForgetting to start Redis\u003c/strong\u003e — \u003ccode\u003eAddStackExchangeRedisCache\u003c/code\u003e wires the client; if the Redis container is not running on \u003ccode\u003elocalhost:6379\u003c/code\u003e, every cache call throws at first use, not at startup.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e","text":"**Common mistakes (sourced from DataCache\\_SCRIPT.docx slide warnings):**\n-   **Confusing Absolute with Sliding** — Absolute is a hard deadline; the entry dies at T+10 minutes no matter how often you read it. Sliding resets to \"idle-for-2-minutes\" on every access. Combine both → whichever fires first wins.\n-   **Expecting MemoryCache to survive app restarts** — it is in-process RAM. A recycle, redeploy, or crash empties it. Redis persists.\n-   **Registering `AddMemoryCache()` but injecting `IDistributedCache`** — these are different registrations. Swapping requires both the service registration and the interface type.\n-   **Forgetting to start Redis** — `AddStackExchangeRedisCache` wires the client; if the Redis container is not running on `localhost:6379`, every cache call throws at first use, not at startup."},{"kind":"checkpoint","q":"**Checkpoint —** You deploy your working MemoryCache app to Azure App Service and scale out to 3 instances. Users complain their data \"flickers between old and new\". Which line do you change in Program.cs, and why?","a":"Replace `builder.Services.AddMemoryCache();` with `builder.Services.AddStackExchangeRedisCache(o =\u003e o.Configuration = \"...\");` . Reason: each of the 3 instances had its own MemoryCache; when the load balancer sent a user to a different instance, the cache missed or returned a stale entry from a prior session. Redis is shared — all 3 instances read the same state."},{"kind":"callout","variant":"note","html":"\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eTakeaway —\u003c/strong\u003e Memory cache: one server. Distributed (Redis): many servers. Tag helper: HTML fragments.\u003c/p\u003e","text":"**Takeaway —** Memory cache: one server. Distributed (Redis): many servers. Tag helper: HTML fragments."}]},{"n":6,"id":"4870-lesson-grpc-contract-first-rpc","title":"gRPC: contract-first RPC","hook":"Define the shape in .proto, generate C# both sides. HTTP/2 under the hood.","tags":["grpc"],"module":"gRPC","blocks":[{"kind":"p","html":"\u003cstrong\u003egRPC\u003c/strong\u003e = Google Remote Procedure Call. Contract lives in a \u003ccode\u003e.proto\u003c/code\u003e file. Protoc generates C# classes for server AND client.","text":"**gRPC** = Google Remote Procedure Call. Contract lives in a `.proto` file. Protoc generates C# classes for server AND client."},{"kind":"code","lang":"proto","code":"// greet.proto\nsyntax = \"proto3\";\noption csharp_namespace = \"MyApp\";\nservice Greeter {\n  rpc SayHello (HelloRequest) returns (HelloReply);\n}\nmessage HelloRequest { string name = 1; }\nmessage HelloReply   { string message = 1; }"},{"kind":"p","html":"\u003cstrong\u003e.csproj:\u003c/strong\u003e \u003ccode\u003e&lt;Protobuf Include=&quot;Protos/greet.proto&quot; GrpcServices=&quot;Server&quot;/&gt;\u003c/code\u003e + \u003ccode\u003eGrpc.Tools\u003c/code\u003e package.","text":"**.csproj:** `\u003cProtobuf Include=\"Protos/greet.proto\" GrpcServices=\"Server\"/\u003e` + `Grpc.Tools` package."},{"kind":"code","lang":"cs","code":"// Server Program.cs\nbuilder.Services.AddGrpc();\napp.MapGrpcService\u003cGreeterImpl\u003e();\n// Server impl\npublic override Task\u003cHelloReply\u003e SayHello(HelloRequest r, ServerCallContext c)\n  =\u003e Task.FromResult(new HelloReply { Message = \"Hi \" + r.Name });\n// Client\nvar channel = GrpcChannel.ForAddress(\"https://localhost:5001\");\nvar client = new Greeter.GreeterClient(channel);\nvar reply = await client.SayHelloAsync(new HelloRequest { Name = \"Bob\" });"},{"kind":"callout","variant":"analogy","html":"\u003cp\u003e REST = text message (&quot;please send user #5&quot;). gRPC = binary function call (\u003ccode\u003eGetUser(5)\u003c/code\u003e) with HTTP/2 streaming.\u003c/p\u003e","text":" REST = text message (\"please send user #5\"). gRPC = binary function call (`GetUser(5)`) with HTTP/2 streaming."},{"kind":"h3","html":"Why field numbers matter (exam trap)","text":"Why field numbers matter (exam trap)"},{"kind":"p","html":"In \u003ccode\u003emessage HelloRequest { string name = 1; }\u003c/code\u003e, the \u003ccode\u003e= 1\u003c/code\u003e is a \u003cstrong\u003ewire-format field number\u003c/strong\u003e, not a default value and not a position. On the wire, protobuf emits \u003ccode\u003e[field_number][wire_type][value]\u003c/code\u003e. That is why:","text":"In `message HelloRequest { string name = 1; }`, the `= 1` is a **wire-format field number**, not a default value and not a position. On the wire, protobuf emits `[field_number][wire_type][value]`. That is why:"},{"kind":"p","html":"\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eOrder in code does not matter.\u003c/strong\u003e Moving \u003ccode\u003ename = 1\u003c/code\u003e below \u003ccode\u003eage = 2\u003c/code\u003e still serializes correctly because the number — not the position — identifies the field.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eRenaming a field is safe; changing its number is not.\u003c/strong\u003e An old client emitting field 1 and a new server expecting field 7 silently drop data.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eTags 1–15 cost one byte\u003c/strong\u003e on the wire, tags 16+ cost two. Reserve 1–15 for the fields you send most often.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e","text":"-   **Order in code does not matter.** Moving `name = 1` below `age = 2` still serializes correctly because the number — not the position — identifies the field.\n-   **Renaming a field is safe; changing its number is not.** An old client emitting field 1 and a new server expecting field 7 silently drop data.\n-   **Tags 1–15 cost one byte** on the wire, tags 16+ cost two. Reserve 1–15 for the fields you send most often."},{"kind":"p","html":"\u003cstrong\u003eFour call types:\u003c/strong\u003e unary, server streaming, client streaming, bidirectional.","text":"**Four call types:** unary, server streaming, client streaming, bidirectional."},{"kind":"h3","html":"4 call types — unary vs streaming","text":"4 call types — unary vs streaming"},{"kind":"mermaid","source":"flowchart LR\n  subgraph Unary[\"1. Unary\"]\n  C1[Client] -- \"1 req\" --\u003e S1[Server]\n  S1 -- \"1 rep\" --\u003e C1\n  end\n  subgraph SStream[\"2. Server streaming\"]\n  C2[Client] -- \"1 req\" --\u003e S2[Server]\n  S2 -- \"stream of replies\" --\u003e C2\n  end\n  subgraph CStream[\"3. Client streaming\"]\n  C3[Client] -- \"stream of reqs\" --\u003e S3[Server]\n  S3 -- \"1 rep\" --\u003e C3\n  end\n  subgraph BiDi[\"4. Bidirectional\"]\n  C4[Client] \u003c--\u003e S4[Server]\n  end"},{"kind":"checkpoint","q":"**Checkpoint —** Your old `.proto` had `message User { string name = 1; int32 age = 2; }`. A teammate reorders the fields in a new commit to `int32 age = 2; string name = 1;`. Is this a breaking change for existing clients? Why?","a":"No — not a breaking change. Protobuf identifies fields by their number, not their declaration order. Old clients emitting field 1 still reach the server as `name`. The breaking change would be swapping the NUMBERS (e.g. making `name = 2`), because then old clients' field-1 bytes would collide with the new `age`."},{"kind":"callout","variant":"note","html":"\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eTakeaway —\u003c/strong\u003e .proto defines the contract. Field numbers (not order) identify fields. TLS is default. Needs HTTP/2.\u003c/p\u003e","text":"**Takeaway —** .proto defines the contract. Field numbers (not order) identify fields. TLS is default. Needs HTTP/2."}]},{"n":7,"id":"4870-lesson-tdd-xunit-red-green-refactor","title":"TDD / xUnit: red, green, refactor","hook":"Write the test first. Watch it fail. Make it pass. Clean it up.","tags":["tdd"],"module":"Testing","blocks":[{"kind":"p","html":"\u003cstrong\u003eTDD\u003c/strong\u003e = Test-Driven Development. Robert Martin&#39;s three laws: (1) no code without a failing test, (2) no more test than what fails, (3) no more code than what makes it pass.","text":"**TDD** = Test-Driven Development. Robert Martin's three laws: (1) no code without a failing test, (2) no more test than what fails, (3) no more code than what makes it pass."},{"kind":"code","lang":"cs","code":"using Xunit;\npublic class CalculatorTests\n{\n    [Fact]\n    public void Add_TwoPositives_ReturnsSum()\n    {\n        // Arrange\n        var calc = new Calculator();\n        // Act\n        var result = calc.Add(2, 3);\n        // Assert\n        Assert.Equal(5, result); // expected, actual — ORDER MATTERS\n    }\n\n    [Theory]\n    [InlineData(1, 2, 3)]\n    [InlineData(0, 0, 0)]\n    [InlineData(-1, 1, 0)]\n    public void Add_Various(int a, int b, int expected)\n    {\n        var calc = new Calculator();\n        Assert.Equal(expected, calc.Add(a, b));\n    }\n}"},{"kind":"callout","variant":"analogy","html":"\u003cp\u003e [Fact] = one photograph. [Theory] + [InlineData] = same photo shoot, different subjects. The [InlineData] rows ARE the test cases.\u003c/p\u003e","text":" \\[Fact\\] = one photograph. \\[Theory\\] + \\[InlineData\\] = same photo shoot, different subjects. The \\[InlineData\\] rows ARE the test cases."},{"kind":"p","html":"\u003cstrong\u003eSetup:\u003c/strong\u003e Use the test class&#39;s constructor. \u003cstrong\u003eTeardown:\u003c/strong\u003e Implement \u003ccode\u003eIDisposable\u003c/code\u003e. \u003cstrong\u003eShared state:\u003c/strong\u003e \u003ccode\u003eIClassFixture&lt;T&gt;\u003c/code\u003e.","text":"**Setup:** Use the test class's constructor. **Teardown:** Implement `IDisposable`. **Shared state:** `IClassFixture\u003cT\u003e`."},{"kind":"p","html":"\u003cstrong\u003eAssert methods:\u003c/strong\u003e Equal, True, False, Null, NotNull, Throws\u003cT\u003e, ThrowsAsync\u003cT\u003e, Contains, Empty, InRange, IsType\u003cT\u003e.","text":"**Assert methods:** Equal, True, False, Null, NotNull, Throws\u003cT\u003e, ThrowsAsync\u003cT\u003e, Contains, Empty, InRange, IsType\u003cT\u003e."},{"kind":"h3","html":"The TDD cycle","text":"The TDD cycle"},{"kind":"mermaid","source":"flowchart LR\n  R[\"RED\u003cbr/\u003ewrite failing test\"] --\u003e G[\"GREEN\u003cbr/\u003emake it pass\u003cbr/\u003esmallest change\"]\n  G --\u003e F[\"REFACTOR\u003cbr/\u003eclean up, stay green\"]\n  F --\u003e R"},{"kind":"callout","variant":"warning","html":"\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eCommon mistakes (sourced from TDD_xunit.pptx slide warnings):\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eSwapping the Assert.Equal arguments\u003c/strong\u003e — \u003ccode\u003eAssert.Equal(actual, expected)\u003c/code\u003e compiles and passes, but on failure the message says &quot;Expected: \u003cyour actual\u003e, Actual: \u003cyour expected\u003e&quot; which sends you debugging in the wrong direction.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eUsing [Fact] with parameters\u003c/strong\u003e — xUnit will refuse to run it. Parametrized tests need \u003ccode\u003e[Theory]\u003c/code\u003e paired with at least one \u003ccode\u003e[InlineData(...)]\u003c/code\u003e, \u003ccode\u003e[MemberData(...)]\u003c/code\u003e, or \u003ccode\u003e[ClassData(typeof(X))]\u003c/code\u003e.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eExpecting [SetUp] / [TestInitialize]\u003c/strong\u003e — xUnit has neither. Setup goes in the class constructor; teardown goes in \u003ccode\u003eDispose()\u003c/code\u003e (implement \u003ccode\u003eIDisposable\u003c/code\u003e).\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eTesting async with \u003ccode\u003eAssert.Throws\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/strong\u003e — for async code use \u003ccode\u003eawait Assert.ThrowsAsync&lt;T&gt;(...)\u003c/code\u003e. The sync variant returns before the awaited exception surfaces and silently passes.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e","text":"**Common mistakes (sourced from TDD\\_xunit.pptx slide warnings):**\n-   **Swapping the Assert.Equal arguments** — `Assert.Equal(actual, expected)` compiles and passes, but on failure the message says \"Expected: \u003cyour actual\u003e, Actual: \u003cyour expected\u003e\" which sends you debugging in the wrong direction.\n-   **Using \\[Fact\\] with parameters** — xUnit will refuse to run it. Parametrized tests need `[Theory]` paired with at least one `[InlineData(...)]`, `[MemberData(...)]`, or `[ClassData(typeof(X))]`.\n-   **Expecting \\[SetUp\\] / \\[TestInitialize\\]** — xUnit has neither. Setup goes in the class constructor; teardown goes in `Dispose()` (implement `IDisposable`).\n-   **Testing async with `Assert.Throws`** — for async code use `await Assert.ThrowsAsync\u003cT\u003e(...)`. The sync variant returns before the awaited exception surfaces and silently passes."},{"kind":"checkpoint","q":"**Checkpoint —** You have three test methods that need the same in-memory DbContext. Should each method `new` its own, use a constructor, or use `IClassFixture\u003cT\u003e`? Explain.","a":"Use `IClassFixture\u003cDbFixture\u003e` when the setup is *expensive* and the tests do not write to it. xUnit creates the fixture once per class and injects it via the constructor, so all 3 methods share one instance. Use a plain constructor when setup is *cheap* or tests mutate state — constructor runs fresh per method, which keeps tests isolated."},{"kind":"callout","variant":"note","html":"\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eTakeaway —\u003c/strong\u003e [Fact]=no args, [Theory]=with data. Assert.Equal(expected, actual). Constructor setup, IDisposable teardown.\u003c/p\u003e","text":"**Takeaway —** \\[Fact\\]=no args, \\[Theory\\]=with data. Assert.Equal(expected, actual). Constructor setup, IDisposable teardown."}]},{"n":8,"id":"4870-lesson-file-based-c-apps-and-asp-net-aspire","title":"File-based C# apps and ASP.NET Aspire","hook":"File-based apps: `.cs` without `.csproj`. Aspire: orchestrate many projects.","tags":["file-based","aspire"],"module":"Hosting","blocks":[{"kind":"p","html":"\u003cstrong\u003eFile-based apps\u003c/strong\u003e (.NET 10): write plain \u003ccode\u003ehello.cs\u003c/code\u003e, run with \u003ccode\u003edotnet run hello.cs\u003c/code\u003e. Use \u003ccode\u003e#:\u003c/code\u003e directives for packages, SDKs, MSBuild properties.","text":"**File-based apps** (.NET 10): write plain `hello.cs`, run with `dotnet run hello.cs`. Use `#:` directives for packages, SDKs, MSBuild properties."},{"kind":"code","lang":"cs","code":"// hello.cs\n#:package Spectre.Console@0.48.0\n#:sdk Microsoft.NET.Sdk.Web\n#:property LangVersion=preview\n\nusing Spectre.Console;\nAnsiConsole.MarkupLine(\"[green]Hello[/]\");"},{"kind":"callout","variant":"analogy","html":"\u003cp\u003e File-based C# = Python script. \u003ccode\u003edotnet project convert file.cs\u003c/code\u003e promotes it to a real project when you outgrow one file.\u003c/p\u003e","text":" File-based C# = Python script. `dotnet project convert file.cs` promotes it to a real project when you outgrow one file."},{"kind":"p","html":"\u003cstrong\u003eCRITICAL:\u003c/strong\u003e NO space after the colon. \u003ccode\u003e#: package\u003c/code\u003e ❌. \u003ccode\u003e#:package\u003c/code\u003e ✓.","text":"**CRITICAL:** NO space after the colon. `#: package` ❌. `#:package` ✓."},{"kind":"p","html":"\u003cstrong\u003eAspire\u003c/strong\u003e orchestrates multi-project solutions (web + api + db + cache) via an \u003cstrong\u003eAppHost\u003c/strong\u003e project.","text":"**Aspire** orchestrates multi-project solutions (web + api + db + cache) via an **AppHost** project."},{"kind":"code","lang":"cs","code":"// AppHost/Program.cs\nvar builder = DistributedApplication.CreateBuilder(args);\nvar cache = builder.AddRedis(\"cache\");\nvar db    = builder.AddSqlServer(\"sql\").AddDatabase(\"app\");\nvar api   = builder.AddProject\u003cProjects.Api\u003e(\"api\").WithReference(cache).WithReference(db);\nbuilder.AddProject\u003cProjects.Web\u003e(\"web\").WithReference(api);\nbuilder.Build().Run();"},{"kind":"p","html":"\u003cstrong\u003eServiceDefaults\u003c/strong\u003e: shared telemetry + service discovery package. Each project calls \u003ccode\u003ebuilder.AddServiceDefaults()\u003c/code\u003e.","text":"**ServiceDefaults**: shared telemetry + service discovery package. Each project calls `builder.AddServiceDefaults()`."},{"kind":"h3","html":"Aspire AppHost orchestration — resource graph","text":"Aspire AppHost orchestration — resource graph"},{"kind":"mermaid","source":"flowchart TB\n  AH[\"AppHost\u003cbr/\u003eDistributedApplication.CreateBuilder\"]\n  CA[\"AddRedis('cache')\"]\n  DB[\"AddSqlServer → AddDatabase('app')\"]\n  API[\"AddProject\u003cProjects.Api\u003e('api')\"]\n  WEB[\"AddProject\u003cProjects.Web\u003e('web')\"]\n  AH --\u003e CA\n  AH --\u003e DB\n  AH --\u003e API\n  AH --\u003e WEB\n  API -. WithReference .-\u003e CA\n  API -. WithReference .-\u003e DB\n  WEB -. WithReference + WaitFor .-\u003e API"},{"kind":"checkpoint","q":"**Checkpoint —** You have a file-based `dashboard.cs` that needs Spectre.Console AND the ASP.NET Core web SDK (because you added a minimal API). Write the two top-of-file directives in the correct syntax.","a":"``` #:sdk Microsoft.NET.Sdk.Web #:package Spectre.Console@0.48.0 ``` Key details: no space after the colon (`#:sdk` not `#: sdk`), package version uses `@` not `=`, SDK directive uses the full MSBuild identifier `Microsoft.NET.Sdk.Web`."},{"kind":"callout","variant":"note","html":"\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eTakeaway —\u003c/strong\u003e File-based: \u003ccode\u003e#:package\u003c/code\u003e, \u003ccode\u003e#:sdk\u003c/code\u003e, \u003ccode\u003e#:property\u003c/code\u003e. Aspire: AppHost + AddProject + WithReference.\u003c/p\u003e","text":"**Takeaway —** File-based: `#:package`, `#:sdk`, `#:property`. Aspire: AppHost + AddProject + WithReference."}]},{"n":9,"id":"4870-lesson-localization-making-an-app-speak-french","title":"Localization: making an app speak French","hook":"Translation is data, not code. You register the service, ship .resx resource files, and ASP.NET does the rest.","tags":["localization"],"module":"Localization","blocks":[{"kind":"p","html":"Localization (4 marks) splits into two concerns that students routinely conflate: \u003cstrong\u003epicking a culture\u003c/strong\u003e (which language does THIS request want?) and \u003cstrong\u003eloading the right strings\u003c/strong\u003e (give me the French version of &quot;Hello&quot;).","text":"Localization (4 marks) splits into two concerns that students routinely conflate: **picking a culture** (which language does THIS request want?) and **loading the right strings** (give me the French version of \"Hello\")."},{"kind":"callout","variant":"analogy","html":"\u003cp\u003e Think of a restaurant. \u003cem\u003ePicking a culture\u003c/em\u003e is the host deciding which menu to hand the diner (English? French?). \u003cem\u003eLoading strings\u003c/em\u003e is the kitchen reading the recipes off the chosen menu. ASP.NET plays both roles automatically once you register the service and drop the right \u003ccode\u003e.resx\u003c/code\u003e files in place.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003ch4\u003eProgram.cs wiring\u003c/h4\u003e\n\u003cpre\u003e\u003ccode class=\"language-cs\"\u003ebuilder.Services.AddLocalization(o =&gt; o.ResourcesPath = &quot;Resources&quot;);\nbuilder.Services.Configure&lt;RequestLocalizationOptions&gt;(o =&gt; {\n    var cultures = new[] { new CultureInfo(&quot;en&quot;), new CultureInfo(&quot;fr&quot;) };\n    o.DefaultRequestCulture = new RequestCulture(&quot;en&quot;);\n    o.SupportedCultures    = cultures;\n    o.SupportedUICultures  = cultures;\n});\napp.UseRequestLocalization();  // middleware — PLACE BEFORE UseRouting\n// In a Razor view:\n// @inject IViewLocalizer Localizer\n// &lt;h1&gt;@Localizer[&quot;Hello&quot;]&lt;/h1&gt;\n\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cem\u003eWhy two culture lists:\u003c/em\u003e \u003cstrong\u003eCurrentCulture\u003c/strong\u003e controls number/date/currency \u003cem\u003eformatting\u003c/em\u003e (0.5 vs 0,5). \u003cstrong\u003eCurrentUICulture\u003c/strong\u003e controls \u003cem\u003ewhich .resx\u003c/em\u003e the translator loads. In practice they match, but they are independent knobs.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003ch4\u003eResource file convention\u003c/h4\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe resource file name encodes target language with a culture code: \u003ccode\u003ePages.Index.fr.resx\u003c/code\u003e for the French translations of \u003ccode\u003ePages/Index.cshtml\u003c/code\u003e. ASP.NET finds the file by matching the page/model name + the \u003cem\u003eCurrentUICulture\u003c/em\u003e. No match → falls back to the neutral \u003ccode\u003ePages.Index.resx\u003c/code\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003ch4\u003eCulture provider chain — how the culture is decided\u003c/h4\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eflowchart LR\n  REQ[Incoming request]\n  REQ --&gt; QS[&quot;1. QueryString\n?culture=fr&quot;]\n  QS --&gt; CK[&quot;2. Cookie\n.AspNetCore.Culture&quot;]\n  CK --&gt; AL[&quot;3. Accept-Language\nbrowser default&quot;]\n  AL --&gt; FB[DefaultRequestCulture]\n  FB --&gt; APP[CurrentUICulture set]\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe three built-in providers run in priority order. First match wins — so \u003ccode\u003e?culture=fr\u003c/code\u003e overrides the cookie, which overrides the browser&#39;s Accept-Language, which falls back to the default you registered.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cblockquote\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eQ:\u003c/strong\u003e \u003cstrong\u003eCheckpoint —\u003c/strong\u003e A user has \u003ccode\u003e.AspNetCore.Culture\u003c/code\u003e cookie set to \u003ccode\u003een\u003c/code\u003e and their browser sends \u003ccode\u003eAccept-Language: fr\u003c/code\u003e. They load \u003ccode\u003e/home?culture=de\u003c/code\u003e. What culture is active, and why?\n\u003cstrong\u003eA:\u003c/strong\u003e \u003ccode\u003ede\u003c/code\u003e. QueryString is first in the provider chain, so \u003ccode\u003e?culture=de\u003c/code\u003e wins even though the cookie and header disagree. (If the app only registered en/fr as SupportedCultures, the fallback would apply — but the ordering rule itself is what the exam tests.)\n\u003cstrong\u003eNote\u003c/strong\u003e\n\u003cstrong\u003eTakeaway —\u003c/strong\u003e AddLocalization + UseRequestLocalization + .resx naming (Name.fr.resx). Provider chain: query → cookie → Accept-Language → default. CurrentCulture formats, CurrentUICulture translates. (Source: asp_core_localization.pptx, razor_pages_localization_SCRIPT.docx)\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/blockquote\u003e","text":" Think of a restaurant. *Picking a culture* is the host deciding which menu to hand the diner (English? French?). *Loading strings* is the kitchen reading the recipes off the chosen menu. ASP.NET plays both roles automatically once you register the service and drop the right `.resx` files in place.\n#### Program.cs wiring\n```cs\nbuilder.Services.AddLocalization(o =\u003e o.ResourcesPath = \"Resources\");\nbuilder.Services.Configure\u003cRequestLocalizationOptions\u003e(o =\u003e {\n    var cultures = new[] { new CultureInfo(\"en\"), new CultureInfo(\"fr\") };\n    o.DefaultRequestCulture = new RequestCulture(\"en\");\n    o.SupportedCultures    = cultures;\n    o.SupportedUICultures  = cultures;\n});\napp.UseRequestLocalization();  // middleware — PLACE BEFORE UseRouting\n// In a Razor view:\n// @inject IViewLocalizer Localizer\n// \u003ch1\u003e@Localizer[\"Hello\"]\u003c/h1\u003e\n```\n*Why two culture lists:* **CurrentCulture** controls number/date/currency *formatting* (0.5 vs 0,5). **CurrentUICulture** controls *which .resx* the translator loads. In practice they match, but they are independent knobs.\n#### Resource file convention\nThe resource file name encodes target language with a culture code: `Pages.Index.fr.resx` for the French translations of `Pages/Index.cshtml`. ASP.NET finds the file by matching the page/model name + the *CurrentUICulture*. No match → falls back to the neutral `Pages.Index.resx`.\n#### Culture provider chain — how the culture is decided\nflowchart LR\n  REQ\\[Incoming request\\]\n  REQ --\u003e QS\\[\"1. QueryString\n?culture=fr\"\\]\n  QS --\u003e CK\\[\"2. Cookie\n.AspNetCore.Culture\"\\]\n  CK --\u003e AL\\[\"3. Accept-Language\nbrowser default\"\\]\n  AL --\u003e FB\\[DefaultRequestCulture\\]\n  FB --\u003e APP\\[CurrentUICulture set\\]\n      \nThe three built-in providers run in priority order. First match wins — so `?culture=fr` overrides the cookie, which overrides the browser's Accept-Language, which falls back to the default you registered.\n\u003e **Q:** **Checkpoint —** A user has `.AspNetCore.Culture` cookie set to `en` and their browser sends `Accept-Language: fr`. They load `/home?culture=de`. What culture is active, and why?\n\u003e **A:** `de`. QueryString is first in the provider chain, so `?culture=de` wins even though the cookie and header disagree. (If the app only registered en/fr as SupportedCultures, the fallback would apply — but the ordering rule itself is what the exam tests.)\n\u003e **Note**\n\u003e **Takeaway —** AddLocalization + UseRequestLocalization + .resx naming (Name.fr.resx). Provider chain: query → cookie → Accept-Language → default. CurrentCulture formats, CurrentUICulture translates. (Source: asp\\_core\\_localization.pptx, razor\\_pages\\_localization\\_SCRIPT.docx)"}]},{"n":10,"id":"4870-lesson-tag-helpers-razor-attributes-that-run-c","title":"Tag Helpers: Razor attributes that run C#","hook":"Tag Helpers look like HTML attributes but are C# classes. Built-ins cover 90%; custom ones are a 10-line class.","tags":["tag-helpers"],"module":"Tag Helpers","blocks":[{"kind":"p","html":"Tag Helpers (3 marks) are server-side Razor components that see an element at render time and can modify its markup. When you write \u003ccode\u003e&lt;a asp-controller=&quot;Home&quot; asp-action=&quot;Index&quot;&gt;\u003c/code\u003e, the \u003ccode\u003eAnchorTagHelper\u003c/code\u003e runs, reads those attributes, and emits \u003ccode\u003e&lt;a href=&quot;/Home/Index&quot;&gt;\u003c/code\u003e. The raw Razor never reaches the browser.","text":"Tag Helpers (3 marks) are server-side Razor components that see an element at render time and can modify its markup. When you write `\u003ca asp-controller=\"Home\" asp-action=\"Index\"\u003e`, the `AnchorTagHelper` runs, reads those attributes, and emits `\u003ca href=\"/Home/Index\"\u003e`. The raw Razor never reaches the browser."},{"kind":"callout","variant":"analogy","html":"\u003cp\u003e A tag helper is a kitchen inspector who intercepts your HTML on its way to the browser, adjusts the plate (adds \u003ccode\u003ehref\u003c/code\u003e, appends a cache-bust version), and sends it out. The diner never sees the inspector.\u003c/p\u003e","text":" A tag helper is a kitchen inspector who intercepts your HTML on its way to the browser, adjusts the plate (adds `href`, appends a cache-bust version), and sends it out. The diner never sees the inspector."},{"kind":"h3","html":"Registering + using built-ins","text":"Registering + using built-ins"},{"kind":"code","lang":"cs","code":"// _ViewImports.cshtml — one line per folder root\n@addTagHelper *, Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.TagHelpers\n\n@* In any .cshtml: *@\n\u003cform asp-controller=\"Home\" asp-action=\"Save\"\u003e\n  \u003cinput asp-for=\"Email\" /\u003e\n  \u003cspan asp-validation-for=\"Email\"\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\n  \u003ca asp-controller=\"Home\" asp-action=\"Index\" asp-route-id=\"42\"\u003eCancel\u003c/a\u003e\n  \u003cscript src=\"/js/site.js\" asp-append-version=\"true\"\u003e\u003c/script\u003e\n\u003c/form\u003e"},{"kind":"p","html":"\u003cem\u003eWhy \u003ccode\u003easp-append-version\u003c/code\u003e:\u003c/em\u003e it hashes the file and appends \u003ccode\u003e?v=HASH\u003c/code\u003e — so when you redeploy a fixed \u003ccode\u003esite.js\u003c/code\u003e, the URL changes and every browser&#39;s cache is bypassed exactly once.","text":"*Why `asp-append-version`:* it hashes the file and appends `?v=HASH` — so when you redeploy a fixed `site.js`, the URL changes and every browser's cache is bypassed exactly once."},{"kind":"h3","html":"How a tag helper intercepts the render","text":"How a tag helper intercepts the render"},{"kind":"mermaid","source":"flowchart LR\n  A[\"Razor source\u003cbr/\u003e&lt;email-link address='x'\u003cbr/\u003edisplay-text='Mail'/&gt;\"] --\u003e B[\"Razor parser\u003cbr/\u003erecognises the tag\u003cbr/\u003e(matches HtmlTargetElement)\"]\n  B --\u003e C[\"EmailLinkTagHelper\u003cbr/\u003e.Process(ctx, output)\"]\n  C --\u003e D[\"output.TagName='a'\u003cbr/\u003e+ href, content\"]\n  D --\u003e E[\"Final HTML\u003cbr/\u003e&lt;a href='mailto:x'&gt;Mail&lt;/a&gt;\"]\n  E --\u003e F[\"Browser\u003cbr/\u003esees only HTML\"]\n  classDef in fill:#2a3a4a,stroke:#7aa2f7,color:#e5e5e5\n  classDef helper fill:#3a3528,stroke:#e3af68,color:#e3af68\n  classDef out fill:#2d3a2d,stroke:#9ece6a,color:#9ece6a\n  class A,B in\n  class C,D helper\n  class E,F out"},{"kind":"p","html":"The browser never sees \u003ccode\u003e&lt;email-link&gt;\u003c/code\u003e — the inspector rewrote the plate before service.","text":"The browser never sees `\u003cemail-link\u003e` — the inspector rewrote the plate before service."},{"kind":"h3","html":"Custom tag helper — minimum skeleton","text":"Custom tag helper — minimum skeleton"},{"kind":"code","lang":"cs","code":"[HtmlTargetElement(\"email-link\")]                    // matches \u003cemail-link\u003e\npublic class EmailLinkTagHelper : TagHelper\n{\n    public string Address { get; set; } = \"\";        // attribute address=\"...\"\n    public string DisplayText { get; set; } = \"\";    // attribute display-text=\"...\" (kebab!)\n\n    public override void Process(TagHelperContext ctx, TagHelperOutput output)\n    {\n        output.TagName = \"a\";                        // rewrite to \u003ca\u003e\n        output.Attributes.SetAttribute(\"href\", $\"mailto:{Address}\");\n        output.Content.SetContent(DisplayText);\n    }\n}"},{"kind":"p","html":"\u003cem\u003eThe kebab-case rule:\u003c/em\u003e a C# property \u003ccode\u003eFontFamily\u003c/code\u003e binds to the HTML attribute \u003ccode\u003efont-family\u003c/code\u003e. ASP.NET converts PascalCase to lowercase-hyphenated automatically. This is an exam classic — distractors offer \u003ccode\u003efontFamily\u003c/code\u003e, \u003ccode\u003eFont-Family\u003c/code\u003e, \u003ccode\u003eFONT_FAMILY\u003c/code\u003e.","text":"*The kebab-case rule:* a C# property `FontFamily` binds to the HTML attribute `font-family`. ASP.NET converts PascalCase to lowercase-hyphenated automatically. This is an exam classic — distractors offer `fontFamily`, `Font-Family`, `FONT_FAMILY`."},{"kind":"checkpoint","q":"**Checkpoint —** You add `public int MaxLength { get; set; }` to a custom tag helper targeting `\u003cphone\u003e`. What HTML attribute name does a view author write to set that property?","a":"`max-length` — the PascalCase → kebab-case conversion is automatic. `\u003cphone max-length=\"10\"\u003e` binds to the property."},{"kind":"callout","variant":"note","html":"\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eTakeaway —\u003c/strong\u003e Register in _ViewImports. Built-ins: asp-for / asp-controller / asp-action / asp-validation-for / asp-append-version. Custom: derive \u003ccode\u003eTagHelper\u003c/code\u003e, override \u003ccode\u003eProcess\u003c/code\u003e, decorate \u003ccode\u003e[HtmlTargetElement(...)]\u003c/code\u003e. PascalCase → kebab-case. (Source: TagHelpers_SCRIPT.docx)\u003c/p\u003e","text":"**Takeaway —** Register in \\_ViewImports. Built-ins: asp-for / asp-controller / asp-action / asp-validation-for / asp-append-version. Custom: derive `TagHelper`, override `Process`, decorate `[HtmlTargetElement(...)]`. PascalCase → kebab-case. (Source: TagHelpers\\_SCRIPT.docx)"}]},{"n":11,"id":"4870-lesson-blazor-quickgrid-tabular-data-in-three-components","title":"Blazor QuickGrid: tabular data in three components","hook":"Drop a \u003cQuickGrid Items=\"\"/\u003e, add PropertyColumn per field, wire a Paginator. Done.","tags":["blazor"],"module":"Blazor","blocks":[{"kind":"p","html":"QuickGrid (2 marks) is the Blazor table component shipped with ASP.NET Core. The whole API fits on a sticky note: one grid, two column types, one paginator.","text":"QuickGrid (2 marks) is the Blazor table component shipped with ASP.NET Core. The whole API fits on a sticky note: one grid, two column types, one paginator."},{"kind":"h3","html":"Component tree at a glance","text":"Component tree at a glance"},{"kind":"mermaid","source":"flowchart TD\n  G[\"&lt;QuickGrid Items=people\u003cbr/\u003ePagination=pagination&gt;\"]\n  P1[\"&lt;PropertyColumn\u003cbr/\u003eProperty=p =&gt; p.Name\u003cbr/\u003eSortable=true /&gt;\"]\n  P2[\"&lt;PropertyColumn\u003cbr/\u003eProperty=p =&gt; p.Age\u003cbr/\u003eSortable=true /&gt;\"]\n  T[\"&lt;TemplateColumn Title='Actions'\u003cbr/\u003eSortBy=nameSort&gt;\u003cbr/\u003earbitrary HTML / @context\"]\n  PG[\"&lt;Paginator State=pagination /&gt;\u003cbr/\u003eshares same PaginationState\"]\n  G --\u003e P1\n  G --\u003e P2\n  G --\u003e T\n  G -.-|same state| PG\n  classDef grid fill:#2a3a4a,stroke:#7aa2f7,color:#e5e5e5\n  classDef prop fill:#2d3a2d,stroke:#9ece6a,color:#9ece6a\n  classDef tmpl fill:#3a3528,stroke:#e3af68,color:#e3af68\n  class G grid\n  class P1,P2 prop\n  class T tmpl\n  class PG grid"},{"kind":"p","html":"PropertyColumn auto-sorts (it has a lambda → expression). TemplateColumn ships custom HTML, so framework can&#39;t infer the sort key — you hand it one via \u003ccode\u003eSortBy\u003c/code\u003e.","text":"PropertyColumn auto-sorts (it has a lambda → expression). TemplateColumn ships custom HTML, so framework can't infer the sort key — you hand it one via `SortBy`."},{"kind":"h3","html":"Minimum working grid","text":"Minimum working grid"},{"kind":"code","lang":"cs","code":"@@page \"/people\"\n@@using Microsoft.AspNetCore.Components.QuickGrid\n\n\u003cQuickGrid Items=\"@people\" Pagination=\"@pagination\"\u003e\n    \u003cPropertyColumn Property=\"@(p =\u003e p.Name)\"   Sortable=\"true\" /\u003e\n    \u003cPropertyColumn Property=\"@(p =\u003e p.Age)\"    Sortable=\"true\" /\u003e\n    \u003cTemplateColumn Title=\"Actions\" SortBy=\"@nameSort\"\u003e\n        \u003ca href=\"/edit/@context.Id\"\u003eEdit\u003c/a\u003e\n    \u003c/TemplateColumn\u003e\n\u003c/QuickGrid\u003e\n\u003cPaginator State=\"@pagination\" /\u003e\n\n@@code {\n    private IQueryable\u003cPerson\u003e people = ...;\n    private PaginationState pagination = new() { ItemsPerPage = 10 };\n    private GridSort\u003cPerson\u003e nameSort = GridSort\u003cPerson\u003e.ByAscending(p =\u003e p.Name);\n}"},{"kind":"p","html":"\u003cem\u003eWhy PropertyColumn auto-sorts but TemplateColumn does not:\u003c/em\u003e PropertyColumn receives a lambda pointing to a single property — QuickGrid can build a sort expression from it. TemplateColumn receives arbitrary child HTML — the framework has no idea what data the template is showing, so you must hand it an explicit \u003ccode\u003eGridSort&lt;T&gt;\u003c/code\u003e via \u003ccode\u003eSortBy\u003c/code\u003e.","text":"*Why PropertyColumn auto-sorts but TemplateColumn does not:* PropertyColumn receives a lambda pointing to a single property — QuickGrid can build a sort expression from it. TemplateColumn receives arbitrary child HTML — the framework has no idea what data the template is showing, so you must hand it an explicit `GridSort\u003cT\u003e` via `SortBy`."},{"kind":"checkpoint","q":"**Checkpoint —** You render a TemplateColumn that shows `@context.FirstName + \" \" + @context.LastName` and you want it sortable by LastName. What do you add?","a":"`SortBy=\"@lastSort\"` plus a backing field `GridSort\u003cPerson\u003e lastSort = GridSort\u003cPerson\u003e.ByAscending(p =\u003e p.LastName);`. Setting `Sortable=\"true\"` alone is ignored on TemplateColumn."},{"kind":"callout","variant":"note","html":"\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eTakeaway —\u003c/strong\u003e Package \u003ccode\u003eMicrosoft.AspNetCore.Components.QuickGrid\u003c/code\u003e. PropertyColumn for direct properties, TemplateColumn + SortBy for custom HTML. \u003ccode\u003ePaginationState { ItemsPerPage = N }\u003c/code\u003e + \u003ccode\u003e&lt;Paginator State=&quot;@x&quot;/&gt;\u003c/code\u003e. (Source: BlazorServer_QuickGrid.docx, BlazorWasm_QuickGrid.docx)\u003c/p\u003e","text":"**Takeaway —** Package `Microsoft.AspNetCore.Components.QuickGrid`. PropertyColumn for direct properties, TemplateColumn + SortBy for custom HTML. `PaginationState { ItemsPerPage = N }` + `\u003cPaginator State=\"@x\"/\u003e`. (Source: BlazorServer\\_QuickGrid.docx, BlazorWasm\\_QuickGrid.docx)"}]},{"n":12,"id":"4870-lesson-excel-pdf-and-charts-from-a-controller","title":"Excel, PDF, and charts from a controller","hook":"Generate a byte array, wrap in File(...), return. The MIME type is the only thing you have to remember.","tags":["excel","pdf","chart"],"module":"Export","blocks":[{"kind":"p","html":"Excel/PDF/Chart (2 marks) is almost entirely package-name and MIME-type recall. The pattern is identical across all three formats: build the bytes, return \u003ccode\u003eFile(bytes, mimeType, fileName)\u003c/code\u003e.","text":"Excel/PDF/Chart (2 marks) is almost entirely package-name and MIME-type recall. The pattern is identical across all three formats: build the bytes, return `File(bytes, mimeType, fileName)`."},{"kind":"diagram","title":null,"svg":"\u003csvg viewBox=\"0 0 760 360\" preserveAspectRatio=\"xMidYMid meet\"\u003e\u003cdefs\u003e\u003cmarker id=\"arrEX\" viewBox=\"0 0 10 10\" refX=\"9\" refY=\"5\" markerWidth=\"6\" markerHeight=\"6\" orient=\"auto\"\u003e\u003cpath d=\"M0 0 L10 5 L0 10 Z\" fill=\"#a3a3a3\"\u003e\u003c/path\u003e\u003c/marker\u003e\u003c/defs\u003e\u003ctext x=\"20\" y=\"22\" class=\"label-accent\"\u003eThree export pipelines — same File() shape, different builders\u003c/text\u003e\u003crect x=\"20\" y=\"40\" width=\"500\" height=\"20\" class=\"box-warn\" rx=\"3\"\u003e\u003c/rect\u003e\u003ctext x=\"270\" y=\"55\" text-anchor=\"middle\" class=\"sub\"\u003eSERVER-SIDE — controller builds bytes, returns File()\u003c/text\u003e\u003crect x=\"540\" y=\"40\" width=\"200\" height=\"20\" class=\"box-ok\" rx=\"3\"\u003e\u003c/rect\u003e\u003ctext x=\"640\" y=\"55\" text-anchor=\"middle\" class=\"sub\"\u003eCLIENT-SIDE\u003c/text\u003e\u003ctext x=\"40\" y=\"90\" class=\"label\"\u003eExcel\u003c/text\u003e\u003crect x=\"40\" y=\"100\" width=\"140\" height=\"36\" class=\"box\" rx=\"3\"\u003e\u003c/rect\u003e\u003ctext x=\"110\" y=\"120\" text-anchor=\"middle\" class=\"sub\"\u003enew XLWorkbook\u003c/text\u003e\u003ctext x=\"110\" y=\"132\" text-anchor=\"middle\" class=\"sub\"\u003ews.Cell(r,c).Value\u003c/text\u003e\u003cpath d=\"M180 118 L210 118\" class=\"arrow-line\" marker-end=\"url(#arrEX)\"\u003e\u003c/path\u003e\u003crect x=\"210\" y=\"100\" width=\"120\" height=\"36\" class=\"box-accent\" rx=\"3\"\u003e\u003c/rect\u003e\u003ctext x=\"270\" y=\"120\" text-anchor=\"middle\" class=\"sub\"\u003ewb.SaveAs(ms)\u003c/text\u003e\u003ctext x=\"270\" y=\"132\" text-anchor=\"middle\" class=\"sub\"\u003e→ MemoryStream\u003c/text\u003e\u003cpath d=\"M330 118 L360 118\" class=\"arrow-line\" marker-end=\"url(#arrEX)\"\u003e\u003c/path\u003e\u003crect x=\"360\" y=\"100\" width=\"160\" height=\"36\" class=\"box-ok\" rx=\"3\"\u003e\u003c/rect\u003e\u003ctext x=\"440\" y=\"116\" text-anchor=\"middle\" class=\"sub\"\u003ereturn File(bytes,\u003c/text\u003e\u003ctext x=\"440\" y=\"130\" text-anchor=\"middle\" class=\"sub\"\u003eopenxml.spreadsheet, .xlsx)\u003c/text\u003e\u003ctext x=\"40\" y=\"180\" class=\"label\"\u003ePDF\u003c/text\u003e\u003crect x=\"40\" y=\"190\" width=\"140\" height=\"36\" class=\"box\" rx=\"3\"\u003e\u003c/rect\u003e\u003ctext x=\"110\" y=\"210\" text-anchor=\"middle\" class=\"sub\"\u003ePdfWriter(ms)\u003c/text\u003e\u003ctext x=\"110\" y=\"222\" text-anchor=\"middle\" class=\"sub\"\u003ePdfDocument · doc.Add\u003c/text\u003e\u003cpath d=\"M180 208 L210 208\" class=\"arrow-line\" marker-end=\"url(#arrEX)\"\u003e\u003c/path\u003e\u003crect x=\"210\" y=\"190\" width=\"120\" height=\"36\" class=\"box-accent\" rx=\"3\"\u003e\u003c/rect\u003e\u003ctext x=\"270\" y=\"210\" text-anchor=\"middle\" class=\"sub\"\u003edoc.Close()\u003c/text\u003e\u003ctext x=\"270\" y=\"222\" text-anchor=\"middle\" class=\"sub\"\u003e→ MemoryStream\u003c/text\u003e\u003cpath d=\"M330 208 L360 208\" class=\"arrow-line\" marker-end=\"url(#arrEX)\"\u003e\u003c/path\u003e\u003crect x=\"360\" y=\"190\" width=\"160\" height=\"36\" class=\"box-ok\" rx=\"3\"\u003e\u003c/rect\u003e\u003ctext x=\"440\" y=\"206\" text-anchor=\"middle\" class=\"sub\"\u003ereturn File(bytes,\u003c/text\u003e\u003ctext x=\"440\" y=\"220\" text-anchor=\"middle\" class=\"sub\"\u003eapplication/pdf, .pdf)\u003c/text\u003e\u003ctext x=\"40\" y=\"270\" class=\"label\"\u003eCharts\u003c/text\u003e\u003crect x=\"540\" y=\"100\" width=\"180\" height=\"60\" class=\"box\" rx=\"3\"\u003e\u003c/rect\u003e\u003ctext x=\"630\" y=\"124\" text-anchor=\"middle\" class=\"sub\"\u003econtroller returns JSON\u003c/text\u003e\u003ctext x=\"630\" y=\"140\" text-anchor=\"middle\" class=\"sub\"\u003edata only\u003c/text\u003e\u003cpath d=\"M540 130 L520 130\" class=\"arrow-line\" marker-end=\"url(#arrEX)\"\u003e\u003c/path\u003e\u003crect x=\"540\" y=\"180\" width=\"180\" height=\"80\" class=\"box-warn\" rx=\"3\"\u003e\u003c/rect\u003e\u003ctext x=\"630\" y=\"204\" text-anchor=\"middle\" class=\"label\"\u003eBrowser\u003c/text\u003e\u003ctext x=\"630\" y=\"222\" text-anchor=\"middle\" class=\"sub\"\u003eChart.js (CDN script)\u003c/text\u003e\u003ctext x=\"630\" y=\"238\" text-anchor=\"middle\" class=\"sub\"\u003erenders &lt;canvas&gt;\u003c/text\u003e\u003ctext x=\"630\" y=\"254\" text-anchor=\"middle\" class=\"sub\"\u003eon the client\u003c/text\u003e\u003cpath d=\"M630 160 L630 180\" class=\"arrow-line\" marker-end=\"url(#arrEX)\"\u003e\u003c/path\u003e\u003crect x=\"40\" y=\"285\" width=\"680\" height=\"55\" class=\"box\" rx=\"4\"\u003e\u003c/rect\u003e\u003ctext x=\"380\" y=\"306\" text-anchor=\"middle\" class=\"label-accent\"\u003eTake-home\u003c/text\u003e\u003ctext x=\"380\" y=\"324\" text-anchor=\"middle\" class=\"sub\"\u003eExcel + PDF: server builds bytes, return File(bytes, MIME, name). Charts: server sends JSON, client renders.\u003c/text\u003e\u003c/svg\u003e","legend":null},{"kind":"h3","html":"Excel — ClosedXML","text":"Excel — ClosedXML"},{"kind":"code","lang":"cs","code":"using ClosedXML.Excel;\n\nusing var wb = new XLWorkbook();\nvar ws = wb.Worksheets.Add(\"Sales\");\nws.Cell(1, 1).Value = \"Product\";\nws.Cell(1, 2).Value = \"Units\";\n// ...fill rows...\n\nusing var ms = new MemoryStream();\nwb.SaveAs(ms);\nreturn File(ms.ToArray(),\n    \"application/vnd.openxmlformats-officedocument.spreadsheetml.sheet\",\n    \"sales.xlsx\");"},{"kind":"h3","html":"PDF — itext7","text":"PDF — itext7"},{"kind":"code","lang":"cs","code":"using iText.Kernel.Pdf;\nusing iText.Layout;\nusing iText.Layout.Element;\n\nusing var ms = new MemoryStream();\nvar writer = new PdfWriter(ms);\nvar pdf    = new PdfDocument(writer);\nvar doc    = new Document(pdf);\ndoc.Add(new Paragraph(\"Hello PDF\"));\ndoc.Close();\nreturn File(ms.ToArray(), \"application/pdf\", \"report.pdf\");"},{"kind":"p","html":"\u003cem\u003eWhy TWO packages for PDF:\u003c/em\u003e \u003ccode\u003eitext7\u003c/code\u003e ships the rendering engine; \u003ccode\u003eitext.bouncy-castle-adapter\u003c/code\u003e provides the cryptographic backend itext relies on for PDF encryption/signing. Installing only \u003ccode\u003eitext7\u003c/code\u003e throws at runtime when iText tries to resolve its crypto provider. Always install BOTH together.","text":"*Why TWO packages for PDF:* `itext7` ships the rendering engine; `itext.bouncy-castle-adapter` provides the cryptographic backend itext relies on for PDF encryption/signing. Installing only `itext7` throws at runtime when iText tries to resolve its crypto provider. Always install BOTH together."},{"kind":"h3","html":"Charts — Chart.js via CDN","text":"Charts — Chart.js via CDN"},{"kind":"p","html":"Charts are client-side: include Chart.js from a CDN in a Razor view, supply a \u003ccode\u003e&lt;canvas&gt;\u003c/code\u003e + JS config. The server never renders the chart — it just sends the data as JSON.","text":"Charts are client-side: include Chart.js from a CDN in a Razor view, supply a `\u003ccanvas\u003e` + JS config. The server never renders the chart — it just sends the data as JSON."},{"kind":"checkpoint","q":"**Checkpoint —** Your controller returns `File(bytes, \"application/vnd.ms-excel\", \"report.xlsx\")`. Users complain Excel warns the file is corrupt. What's wrong and what's the fix?","a":"`application/vnd.ms-excel` is the LEGACY .xls MIME. Modern .xlsx (Open XML format) needs `application/vnd.openxmlformats-officedocument.spreadsheetml.sheet`. Swap the MIME string and the warning disappears."},{"kind":"callout","variant":"note","html":"\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eTakeaway —\u003c/strong\u003e Excel = ClosedXML (XLWorkbook). PDF = itext7 + bouncy-castle-adapter. Charts = Chart.js CDN. Always \u003ccode\u003eFile(bytes, mime, name)\u003c/code\u003e. (Source: Add package for PDF.html, W13 lab)\u003c/p\u003e","text":"**Takeaway —** Excel = ClosedXML (XLWorkbook). PDF = itext7 + bouncy-castle-adapter. Charts = Chart.js CDN. Always `File(bytes, mime, name)`. (Source: Add package for PDF.html, W13 lab)"}]},{"n":13,"id":"4870-lesson-reading-the-mcq-trap-spotting","title":"Reading the MCQ: trap-spotting","hook":"Elmasry's MCQ style: 5 options, fake method names, subtle flag swaps. Here's how to filter.","tags":["exam-prep"],"module":"Exam prep","blocks":[{"kind":"p","html":"From the midterm, the distractor patterns are consistent:","text":"From the midterm, the distractor patterns are consistent:"},{"kind":"p","html":"\u003col\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eFake method names\u003c/strong\u003e — e.g. \u003ccode\u003e_context.Migrate()\u003c/code\u003e vs \u003ccode\u003e_context.Database.Migrate()\u003c/code\u003e. Always pick the one with the real namespace chain.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eWrong bracket style\u003c/strong\u003e — e.g. \u003ccode\u003e[Route(&quot;api/[controller]&quot;)]\u003c/code\u003e vs \u003ccode\u003eRoute(&quot;[api]/[controller]&quot;)\u003c/code\u003e. Remember: annotation = square brackets around, placeholder = square brackets inside.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eCommand order swap\u003c/strong\u003e — e.g. \u003ccode\u003edotnet ef update database\u003c/code\u003e vs \u003ccode\u003edotnet ef database update\u003c/code\u003e. The subject comes before the verb.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eSingular vs plural\u003c/strong\u003e — \u003ccode\u003edotnet ef add migration\u003c/code\u003e vs \u003ccode\u003edotnet ef migrations add\u003c/code\u003e. Collection commands use the plural.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eFake interface variants\u003c/strong\u003e — \u003ccode\u003eSignInManager\u003c/code\u003e vs \u003ccode\u003eRoleManager\u003c/code\u003e vs \u003ccode\u003eAuthManager\u003c/code\u003e (fake) vs \u003ccode\u003eIdentityManager\u003c/code\u003e (fake).\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ol\u003e","text":"1.  **Fake method names** — e.g. `_context.Migrate()` vs `_context.Database.Migrate()`. Always pick the one with the real namespace chain.\n2.  **Wrong bracket style** — e.g. `[Route(\"api/[controller]\")]` vs `Route(\"[api]/[controller]\")`. Remember: annotation = square brackets around, placeholder = square brackets inside.\n3.  **Command order swap** — e.g. `dotnet ef update database` vs `dotnet ef database update`. The subject comes before the verb.\n4.  **Singular vs plural** — `dotnet ef add migration` vs `dotnet ef migrations add`. Collection commands use the plural.\n5.  **Fake interface variants** — `SignInManager` vs `RoleManager` vs `AuthManager` (fake) vs `IdentityManager` (fake)."},{"kind":"callout","variant":"analogy","html":"\u003cp\u003e Treat wrong options like a phishing email. One giveaway (fake namespace, wrong capitalization, missing keyword) is enough to eliminate.\u003c/p\u003e","text":" Treat wrong options like a phishing email. One giveaway (fake namespace, wrong capitalization, missing keyword) is enough to eliminate."},{"kind":"p","html":"\u003cstrong\u003eMatch-column strategy (from midterm):\u003c/strong\u003e The pattern is \u003cem\u003ething → its canonical tool or command\u003c/em\u003e. Examples seen: React → Vite, TypeScript → tsc, Swagger → WebAPI docs, SignalR → Hub, Multi-docker → docker-compose.yml, Single docker → Dockerfile. Expect same pattern on final.","text":"**Match-column strategy (from midterm):** The pattern is *thing → its canonical tool or command*. Examples seen: React → Vite, TypeScript → tsc, Swagger → WebAPI docs, SignalR → Hub, Multi-docker → docker-compose.yml, Single docker → Dockerfile. Expect same pattern on final."},{"kind":"h3","html":"MCQ elimination flow — 30 seconds per question","text":"MCQ elimination flow — 30 seconds per question"},{"kind":"mermaid","source":"flowchart TD\n  Q[Read question] --\u003e F{Spot a fake\nmethod name?}\n  F --\u003e|yes| X1[Eliminate]\n  F --\u003e|no| B{Word order or\nsingular/plural trap?}\n  B --\u003e|yes| X2[Eliminate]\n  B --\u003e|no| C{2+ options left?}\n  X1 --\u003e C\n  X2 --\u003e C\n  C --\u003e|yes| GUESS[Best guess\nMOVE ON]\n  C --\u003e|1 left| PICK[Pick it]"},{"kind":"callout","variant":"note","html":"\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eTakeaway —\u003c/strong\u003e Eliminate first, guess last. Two clear eliminations on an MCQ = 50% → skipping should be rare.\u003c/p\u003e","text":"**Takeaway —** Eliminate first, guess last. Two clear eliminations on an MCQ = 50% → skipping should be rare."}]},{"n":14,"id":"4870-lesson-hand-written-cheat-sheet-pack-strategy","title":"Hand-written cheat sheet: pack strategy","hook":"ONE 8.5×11, both sides. Hand-written. What goes on it decides 10-15 marks.","tags":["cheat-sheet"],"module":"Exam prep","blocks":[{"kind":"p","html":"Your cheat sheet is the force multiplier. Pack it right and it answers 15+ MCQ directly.","text":"Your cheat sheet is the force multiplier. Pack it right and it answers 15+ MCQ directly."},{"kind":"p","html":"\u003cstrong\u003eFront side layout (suggested):\u003c/strong\u003e","text":"**Front side layout (suggested):**"},{"kind":"p","html":"\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eUpper-left:\u003c/strong\u003e AI/SK/MAF/MCP method cheat block — \u003ccode\u003eKernel.CreateBuilder\u003c/code\u003e, \u003ccode\u003eAddOllamaChatCompletion\u003c/code\u003e, \u003ccode\u003eChatHistory\u003c/code\u003e, \u003ccode\u003eIChatCompletionService\u003c/code\u003e, \u003ccode\u003eAsAIAgent\u003c/code\u003e, \u003ccode\u003eAIFunctionFactory.Create\u003c/code\u003e.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eUpper-right:\u003c/strong\u003e ML.NET 7-step template — \u003ccode\u003eMLContext\u003c/code\u003e → \u003ccode\u003eLoadFromTextFile&lt;T&gt;\u003c/code\u003e → \u003ccode\u003eTrainTestSplit\u003c/code\u003e → pipeline → \u003ccode\u003eFit\u003c/code\u003e → \u003ccode\u003eEvaluate\u003c/code\u003e → \u003ccode\u003eSave\u003c/code\u003e.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eMiddle:\u003c/strong\u003e Cache patterns — MemoryCache, Redis, \u003ccode\u003e&lt;cache&gt;\u003c/code\u003e tag helper with all vary-by-* options.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eLower:\u003c/strong\u003e gRPC .proto skeleton + server/client Program.cs + csproj \u003ccode\u003e&lt;Protobuf&gt;\u003c/code\u003e line.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e","text":"-   **Upper-left:** AI/SK/MAF/MCP method cheat block — `Kernel.CreateBuilder`, `AddOllamaChatCompletion`, `ChatHistory`, `IChatCompletionService`, `AsAIAgent`, `AIFunctionFactory.Create`.\n-   **Upper-right:** ML.NET 7-step template — `MLContext` → `LoadFromTextFile\u003cT\u003e` → `TrainTestSplit` → pipeline → `Fit` → `Evaluate` → `Save`.\n-   **Middle:** Cache patterns — MemoryCache, Redis, `\u003ccache\u003e` tag helper with all vary-by-\\* options.\n-   **Lower:** gRPC .proto skeleton + server/client Program.cs + csproj `\u003cProtobuf\u003e` line."},{"kind":"p","html":"\u003cstrong\u003eBack side layout (suggested):\u003c/strong\u003e","text":"**Back side layout (suggested):**"},{"kind":"p","html":"\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003exUnit: \u003ccode\u003e[Fact]\u003c/code\u003e, \u003ccode\u003e[Theory]\u003c/code\u003e, \u003ccode\u003e[InlineData]\u003c/code\u003e, \u003ccode\u003eAssert.Equal(expected,actual)\u003c/code\u003e, \u003ccode\u003eAssert.Throws&lt;T&gt;\u003c/code\u003e.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eFile-based: all four \u003ccode\u003e#:\u003c/code\u003e directives with EXAMPLE syntax.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eAspire: AppHost Program.cs with \u003ccode\u003eAddProject\u003c/code\u003e, \u003ccode\u003eWithReference\u003c/code\u003e, \u003ccode\u003eAddRedis\u003c/code\u003e, \u003ccode\u003eAddSqlServer\u003c/code\u003e.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eLocalization: \u003ccode\u003eAddLocalization\u003c/code\u003e, resource file naming, CurrentCulture vs CurrentUICulture.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eTag Helpers: built-in list + custom class skeleton.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eQuickGrid: PropertyColumn + PaginationState + filter @bind pattern.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eExcel/PDF: package names + MIME strings.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e","text":"-   xUnit: `[Fact]`, `[Theory]`, `[InlineData]`, `Assert.Equal(expected,actual)`, `Assert.Throws\u003cT\u003e`.\n-   File-based: all four `#:` directives with EXAMPLE syntax.\n-   Aspire: AppHost Program.cs with `AddProject`, `WithReference`, `AddRedis`, `AddSqlServer`.\n-   Localization: `AddLocalization`, resource file naming, CurrentCulture vs CurrentUICulture.\n-   Tag Helpers: built-in list + custom class skeleton.\n-   QuickGrid: PropertyColumn + PaginationState + filter @bind pattern.\n-   Excel/PDF: package names + MIME strings."},{"kind":"callout","variant":"analogy","html":"\u003cp\u003e The cheat sheet is like your free souvenir from the topic. Bring back concrete method chains and exact syntax — not prose.\u003c/p\u003e","text":" The cheat sheet is like your free souvenir from the topic. Bring back concrete method chains and exact syntax — not prose."},{"kind":"h3","html":"Suggested cheat-sheet layout","text":"Suggested cheat-sheet layout"},{"kind":"mermaid","source":"flowchart TB\n  subgraph FRONT[\"FRONT SIDE\"]\n  F1[\"AI/SK/MAF/MCP\u003cbr/\u003emethod names\"]\n  F2[\"ML.NET 7-step\u003cbr/\u003epipeline template\"]\n  F3[\"Cache patterns\u003cbr/\u003evary-by-* list\"]\n  F4[\"gRPC proto + server\u003cbr/\u003e+ client skeleton\"]\n  end\n  subgraph BACK[\"BACK SIDE\"]\n  B1[\"xUnit [Fact] [Theory]\u003cbr/\u003eAssert methods\"]\n  B2[\"#:package #:sdk\u003cbr/\u003e#:property\"]\n  B3[\"Aspire AddProject\u003cbr/\u003eWithReference\"]\n  B4[\"Localization setup\u003cbr/\u003eTagHelpers + QuickGrid\u003cbr/\u003eExcel/PDF MIME\"]\n  end"},{"kind":"callout","variant":"note","html":"\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eTakeaway —\u003c/strong\u003e Cheat sheet = method names + exact syntax + package names. Not definitions. Not prose.\u003c/p\u003e","text":"**Takeaway —** Cheat sheet = method names + exact syntax + package names. Not definitions. Not prose."}]}],"codePractice":[{"n":1,"id":"4870-code-grpc-calculator-coding-candidate-1","title":"gRPC Calculator (coding candidate #1)","lang":"cs","tags":["grpc"],"variant":"starter-solution","prompt_html":"\u003cp\u003eWrite a gRPC service for a Calculator. Define Add(a,b) returning sum. Include: (1) calculator.proto with proto3 syntax, csharp_namespace, service + rpc, AddRequest/AddResponse messages with field tags; (2) .csproj Protobuf item; (3) Program.cs AddGrpc + MapGrpcService; (4) CalculatorImpl class overriding Add.\u003c/p\u003e","starter":"// calculator.proto\nsyntax = \"proto3\";\noption csharp_namespace = \"CalcGrpc\";\n\nservice Calculator {\n  // TODO\n}\n\nmessage AddRequest {\n  // TODO\n}\n\nmessage AddResponse {\n  // TODO\n}\n\n// Program.cs\nvar builder = WebApplication.CreateBuilder(args);\n// TODO: register gRPC\n\nvar app = builder.Build();\n// TODO: map service\napp.Run();\n\n// CalculatorImpl.cs\npublic class CalculatorImpl : /* TODO: base class */ {\n    // TODO: override Add\n}","solution":"// calculator.proto\nsyntax = \"proto3\";\noption csharp_namespace = \"CalcGrpc\";\n\nservice Calculator {\n  rpc Add (AddRequest) returns (AddResponse);\n}\n\nmessage AddRequest {\n  int32 a = 1;\n  int32 b = 2;\n}\n\nmessage AddResponse {\n  int32 sum = 1;\n}\n\n// .csproj\n// \u003cItemGroup\u003e\n//   \u003cProtobuf Include=\"Protos/calculator.proto\" GrpcServices=\"Server\" /\u003e\n// \u003c/ItemGroup\u003e\n\n// Program.cs\nvar builder = WebApplication.CreateBuilder(args);\nbuilder.Services.AddGrpc();\n\nvar app = builder.Build();\napp.MapGrpcService\u003cCalculatorImpl\u003e();\napp.Run();\n\n// CalculatorImpl.cs\nusing Grpc.Core;\nusing CalcGrpc;\n\npublic class CalculatorImpl : Calculator.CalculatorBase {\n    public override Task\u003cAddResponse\u003e Add(AddRequest r, ServerCallContext ctx) {\n        return Task.FromResult(new AddResponse { Sum = r.A + r.B });\n    }\n}","why_html":"\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eMarking checklist (10 marks):\u003c/strong\u003e\u003cul\u003e\u003cli\u003esyntax = &quot;proto3&quot; + csharp_namespace (2)\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003eservice Calculator + rpc Add signature (2)\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003eAddRequest / AddResponse with int32 fields + field numbers (2)\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003eAddGrpc + MapGrpcService\u003cT\u003e (2)\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003eOverride signature Task\u003cAddResponse\u003e Add(AddRequest, ServerCallContext) (2)\u003c/li\u003e\u003c/ul\u003e\u003c/p\u003e"},{"n":2,"id":"4870-code-xunit-test-class-coding-candidate-2","title":"xUnit test class (coding candidate #2)","lang":"cs","tags":["tdd"],"variant":"starter-solution","prompt_html":"\u003cp\u003eWrite an xUnit test class for a \u003ccode\u003eStringValidator\u003c/code\u003e class with a method \u003ccode\u003eIsValidEmail(string)\u003c/code\u003e. Include: (1) one [Fact] for happy path; (2) one [Theory] with 3 [InlineData] rows of invalid emails; (3) one test asserting a \u003ccode\u003enull\u003c/code\u003e input throws \u003ccode\u003eArgumentNullException\u003c/code\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e","starter":"using Xunit;\n\npublic class StringValidatorTests {\n    // TODO: happy path [Fact]\n\n    // TODO: [Theory] with invalid emails\n\n    // TODO: [Fact] that null throws\n}","solution":"using Xunit;\nusing System;\n\npublic class StringValidatorTests {\n    private readonly StringValidator _v = new StringValidator();\n\n    [Fact]\n    public void IsValidEmail_WellFormed_ReturnsTrue() {\n        var result = _v.IsValidEmail(\"user@bcit.ca\");\n        Assert.True(result);\n    }\n\n    [Theory]\n    [InlineData(\"\")]\n    [InlineData(\"no-at-sign\")]\n    [InlineData(\"@nouser\")]\n    public void IsValidEmail_Invalid_ReturnsFalse(string input) {\n        Assert.False(_v.IsValidEmail(input));\n    }\n\n    [Fact]\n    public void IsValidEmail_Null_ThrowsArgumentNull() {\n        Assert.Throws\u003cArgumentNullException\u003e(() =\u003e _v.IsValidEmail(null));\n    }\n}","why_html":"\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eMarking checklist (10 marks):\u003c/strong\u003e\u003cul\u003e\u003cli\u003eTest class public, no attributes on class (1)\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003e[Fact] method name describing scenario (1)\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003eAAA pattern visible (1)\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003e[Theory] + 3 [InlineData] (3)\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003eparameter signature matches InlineData args (1)\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003eAssert.Throws&lt;ArgumentNullException&gt;(Action) (2)\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003eUsing statement for Xunit (1)\u003c/li\u003e\u003c/ul\u003e\u003c/p\u003e"},{"n":3,"id":"4870-code-ml-net-regression-pipeline-coding-candidate-3","title":"ML.NET regression pipeline (coding candidate #3)","lang":"cs","tags":["ml-net"],"variant":"starter-solution","prompt_html":"\u003cp\u003eWrite the ML.NET code to train and evaluate a regression model predicting HousePrice from Area and Bedrooms. Include: MLContext creation, data model class with [LoadColumn], LoadFromTextFile, TrainTestSplit, pipeline with Concatenate + Regression.Trainers.FastTree, Fit, Evaluate reporting RSquared, and model save.\u003c/p\u003e","starter":"// Data model\npublic class House {\n    // TODO: LoadColumn attributes\n}\n\n// Program.cs\nvar ml = new MLContext(seed: 0);\n// TODO: load CSV\n// TODO: split\n// TODO: pipeline\n// TODO: fit\n// TODO: evaluate + Console.WriteLine R²\n// TODO: save model","solution":"using Microsoft.ML;\nusing Microsoft.ML.Data;\n\npublic class House {\n    [LoadColumn(0)] public float Area;\n    [LoadColumn(1)] public float Bedrooms;\n    [LoadColumn(2), ColumnName(\"Label\")] public float HousePrice;\n}\n\npublic class HousePrediction {\n    [ColumnName(\"Score\")] public float HousePrice;\n}\n\n// Program.cs\nvar ml = new MLContext(seed: 0);\n\nIDataView data = ml.Data.LoadFromTextFile\u003cHouse\u003e(\n    \"houses.csv\", hasHeader: true, separatorChar: ',');\n\nvar split = ml.Data.TrainTestSplit(data, testFraction: 0.2);\n\nvar pipeline = ml.Transforms.Concatenate(\"Features\", \"Area\", \"Bedrooms\")\n    .Append(ml.Regression.Trainers.FastTree());\n\nITransformer model = pipeline.Fit(split.TrainSet);\n\nIDataView preds = model.Transform(split.TestSet);\nvar metrics = ml.Regression.Evaluate(preds, labelColumnName: \"Label\");\nConsole.WriteLine($\"R²: {metrics.RSquared:F3}\");\nConsole.WriteLine($\"RMSE: {metrics.RootMeanSquaredError:F2}\");\n\nml.Model.Save(model, data.Schema, \"house.zip\");","why_html":"\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eMarking checklist (10 marks):\u003c/strong\u003e\u003cul\u003e\u003cli\u003eMLContext instantiated with seed (1)\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003e[LoadColumn] on data model properties (2)\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003eLabel column marked via ColumnName(&quot;Label&quot;) (1)\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003eLoadFromTextFile&lt;T&gt; with hasHeader + separator (2)\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003eTrainTestSplit with testFraction (1)\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003epipeline with Concatenate(&quot;Features&quot;, ...).Append(FastTree()) (2)\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003eFit returns ITransformer, Evaluate reports RSquared (1)\u003c/li\u003e\u003c/ul\u003e\u003c/p\u003e"},{"n":4,"id":"4870-code-semantic-kernel-chat-plugin","title":"Semantic Kernel chat + plugin","lang":"cs","tags":["semantic-kernel"],"variant":"starter-solution","prompt_html":"\u003cp\u003eRegister Semantic Kernel with Ollama llama3 endpoint. Create a plugin with a [KernelFunction] method \u003ccode\u003eGetWeather(string city)\u003c/code\u003e. Run a chat with a user prompt &quot;What is the weather in Vancouver?&quot; and print the response.\u003c/p\u003e","starter":"using Microsoft.SemanticKernel;\n\npublic class WeatherPlugin {\n    // TODO: [KernelFunction] GetWeather\n}\n\n// Program.cs\n// TODO: build kernel with Ollama\n// TODO: import plugin\n// TODO: chat history with user prompt\n// TODO: get response","solution":"using Microsoft.SemanticKernel;\nusing Microsoft.SemanticKernel.ChatCompletion;\nusing System.ComponentModel;\n\npublic class WeatherPlugin {\n    [KernelFunction, Description(\"Get weather for a city\")]\n    public string GetWeather(string city) =\u003e $\"Sunny in {city}.\";\n}\n\n// Program.cs\nvar builder = Kernel.CreateBuilder();\nbuilder.AddOllamaChatCompletion(\"llama3\", new Uri(\"http://localhost:11434\"));\nKernel kernel = builder.Build();\n\nkernel.ImportPluginFromType\u003cWeatherPlugin\u003e();\n\nvar chat = kernel.GetRequiredService\u003cIChatCompletionService\u003e();\nvar history = new ChatHistory(\"You are helpful.\");\nhistory.AddUserMessage(\"What is the weather in Vancouver?\");\n\nvar response = await chat.GetChatMessageContentAsync(history, kernel: kernel);\nConsole.WriteLine(response.Content);","why_html":"\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eMarking checklist (10 marks):\u003c/strong\u003e\u003cul\u003e\u003cli\u003eKernel.CreateBuilder() (1)\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003eAddOllamaChatCompletion with correct endpoint (2)\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003eImportPluginFromType&lt;T&gt; (1)\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003e[KernelFunction] attribute (2)\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003eIChatCompletionService via GetRequiredService (1)\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003eChatHistory with system prompt (1)\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003eAddUserMessage + GetChatMessageContentAsync (2)\u003c/li\u003e\u003c/ul\u003e\u003c/p\u003e"},{"n":5,"id":"4870-code-aspire-apphost-stack","title":"Aspire AppHost stack","lang":"cs","tags":["aspire"],"variant":"starter-solution","prompt_html":"\u003cp\u003eWrite AppHost Program.cs that orchestrates: a Redis cache, a SQL Server with a database named \u003ccode\u003eapp\u003c/code\u003e, an API project that references both, and a Web project that references the API and waits for it.\u003c/p\u003e","starter":"var builder = DistributedApplication.CreateBuilder(args);\n\n// TODO: Redis\n// TODO: SQL + database\n// TODO: API project referencing cache + db\n// TODO: Web referencing API + waits\n\nbuilder.Build().Run();","solution":"var builder = DistributedApplication.CreateBuilder(args);\n\nvar cache = builder.AddRedis(\"cache\");\nvar sql   = builder.AddSqlServer(\"sql\");\nvar db    = sql.AddDatabase(\"app\");\n\nvar api = builder.AddProject\u003cProjects.Api\u003e(\"api\")\n    .WithReference(cache)\n    .WithReference(db);\n\nbuilder.AddProject\u003cProjects.Web\u003e(\"web\")\n    .WithReference(api)\n    .WaitFor(api);\n\nbuilder.Build().Run();","why_html":"\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eMarking checklist (10 marks):\u003c/strong\u003e\u003cul\u003e\u003cli\u003eDistributedApplication.CreateBuilder(args) (1)\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003eAddRedis(&quot;cache&quot;) (1)\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003eAddSqlServer + AddDatabase (2)\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003eAddProject&lt;Projects.Api&gt; (1)\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003eWithReference(cache) + WithReference(db) on api (2)\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003eWeb WithReference(api) (1)\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003eWaitFor(api) (1)\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003ebuilder.Build().Run() (1)\u003c/li\u003e\u003c/ul\u003e\u003c/p\u003e"}],"topicDives":[{"id":"4870-topic-aspire-orchestrating-a-stack","title":"Aspire — orchestrating a stack","pillar":"tech","priority":"medium","chapter":"W09","tags":["aspire"],"blocks":[{"kind":"h3","html":"AppHost Program.cs","text":"AppHost Program.cs"},{"kind":"code","lang":"cs","code":"var builder = DistributedApplication.CreateBuilder(args);\n\n// Resources\nvar cache = builder.AddRedis(\"cache\");\nvar sql   = builder.AddSqlServer(\"sql\");\nvar db    = sql.AddDatabase(\"appdb\");\n\n// Projects\nvar api = builder.AddProject\u003cProjects.Api\u003e(\"api\")\n    .WithReference(cache)\n    .WithReference(db);\n\nbuilder.AddProject\u003cProjects.Web\u003e(\"web\")\n    .WithReference(api)\n    .WaitFor(api);\n\nbuilder.Build().Run();"},{"kind":"h3","html":"Each service calls:","text":"Each service calls:"},{"kind":"code","lang":"cs","code":"// In every downstream project's Program.cs\nbuilder.AddServiceDefaults();          // telemetry, health, discovery\nbuilder.AddRedisClient(\"cache\");        // named resource\nbuilder.AddSqlServerDbContext\u003cAppDb\u003e(\"appdb\");"},{"kind":"h3","html":"Service discovery URL","text":"Service discovery URL"},{"kind":"code","lang":"cs","code":"// HttpClient registration — logical name, not URL\nbuilder.Services.AddHttpClient\u003cApiClient\u003e(c =\u003e c.BaseAddress = new Uri(\"https+http://api\"));"},{"kind":"h3","html":"Aspire Dashboard","text":"Aspire Dashboard"},{"kind":"p","html":"Automatic telemetry UI launched on AppHost run. Shows logs, traces, metrics per resource.","text":"Automatic telemetry UI launched on AppHost run. Shows logs, traces, metrics per resource."},{"kind":"h3","html":"Exam traps","text":"Exam traps"},{"kind":"p","html":"\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eAppHost ≠ ServiceDefaults. AppHost orchestrates. ServiceDefaults is a library each service imports.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003ccode\u003eAddProject&lt;Projects.Foo&gt;\u003c/code\u003e — \u003ccode\u003eProjects.Foo\u003c/code\u003e is a generated type from the project reference\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003ccode\u003ehttps+http://api\u003c/code\u003e → the scheme tells the resolver to try HTTPS first, fall back to HTTP\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e","text":"-   AppHost ≠ ServiceDefaults. AppHost orchestrates. ServiceDefaults is a library each service imports.\n-   `AddProject\u003cProjects.Foo\u003e` — `Projects.Foo` is a generated type from the project reference\n-   `https+http://api` → the scheme tells the resolver to try HTTPS first, fall back to HTTP\n"}]},{"id":"4870-topic-file-based-c-every-directive","title":"File-based C# — every directive","pillar":"tech","priority":"high","chapter":"W11","tags":["filebased","file-based"],"blocks":[{"kind":"h3","html":"All four directives","text":"All four directives"},{"kind":"code","lang":"cs","code":"// ==== app.cs ====\n#:package Spectre.Console@0.48.0       // NuGet package\n#:package Newtonsoft.Json@13.0.3\n#:sdk Microsoft.NET.Sdk.Web            // use ASP.NET SDK\n#:property LangVersion=preview         // MSBuild property\n#:property TargetFramework=net10.0\n#:project ./lib/MyHelpers.csproj       // reference another project\n\nusing Spectre.Console;\n\nAnsiConsole.MarkupLine(\"[green]Hello[/]\");\n\nforeach (var arg in args) Console.WriteLine(arg);"},{"kind":"p","html":"\u003cstrong\u003eRun:\u003c/strong\u003e \u003ccode\u003edotnet run app.cs -- extra args\u003c/code\u003e (anything after \u003ccode\u003e--\u003c/code\u003e goes to \u003ccode\u003eargs\u003c/code\u003e)","text":"**Run:** `dotnet run app.cs -- extra args` (anything after `--` goes to `args`)"},{"kind":"h3","html":"CRITICAL syntax rules","text":"CRITICAL syntax rules"},{"kind":"p","html":"\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003ccode\u003e#:package\u003c/code\u003e — NO space after colon (\u003ccode\u003e#: package\u003c/code\u003e ❌)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eDirectives must be at TOP of file before any code\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e@version optional → uses latest if omitted\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eSDK names are Microsoft-standard: \u003ccode\u003eMicrosoft.NET.Sdk\u003c/code\u003e (default), \u003ccode\u003eMicrosoft.NET.Sdk.Web\u003c/code\u003e, \u003ccode\u003eMicrosoft.NET.Sdk.Worker\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e","text":"-   `#:package` — NO space after colon (`#: package` ❌)\n-   Directives must be at TOP of file before any code\n-   @version optional → uses latest if omitted\n-   SDK names are Microsoft-standard: `Microsoft.NET.Sdk` (default), `Microsoft.NET.Sdk.Web`, `Microsoft.NET.Sdk.Worker`"},{"kind":"h3","html":"Minimal Web API — single file","text":"Minimal Web API — single file"},{"kind":"code","lang":"cs","code":"#:sdk Microsoft.NET.Sdk.Web\n\nvar builder = WebApplication.CreateBuilder(args);\nvar app = builder.Build();\napp.MapGet(\"/\", () =\u003e \"Hello\");\napp.Run();"},{"kind":"h3","html":"Convert to a real project","text":"Convert to a real project"},{"kind":"code","lang":"cs","code":"dotnet project convert app.cs -o NewFolder"},{"kind":"h3","html":"Shebang (mac/linux)","text":"Shebang (mac/linux)"},{"kind":"code","lang":"cs","code":"#!/usr/bin/env dotnet\n#:package Spectre.Console@0.48.0\n..."},{"kind":"p","html":"Then \u003ccode\u003echmod +x app.cs\u003c/code\u003e and run as \u003ccode\u003e./app.cs\u003c/code\u003e.","text":"Then `chmod +x app.cs` and run as `./app.cs`."}]},{"id":"4870-topic-grpc-proto-server-client","title":"gRPC — proto + server + client","pillar":"tech","priority":"high","chapter":"W09","tags":["grpc"],"blocks":[{"kind":"h3","html":"greet.proto","text":"greet.proto"},{"kind":"code","lang":"proto","code":"syntax = \"proto3\";\noption csharp_namespace = \"GrpcGreeter\";\npackage greet;\n\nservice Greeter {\n  rpc SayHello (HelloRequest) returns (HelloReply);\n  rpc StreamNames (HelloRequest) returns (stream HelloReply);       // server stream\n  rpc CollectNames (stream HelloRequest) returns (HelloReply);      // client stream\n  rpc Chat (stream HelloRequest) returns (stream HelloReply);       // bidi\n}\n\nmessage HelloRequest {\n  string name = 1;\n  int32  age  = 2;\n}\n\nmessage HelloReply {\n  string message = 1;\n}"},{"kind":"h3","html":"Server .csproj","text":"Server .csproj"},{"kind":"code","lang":"xml","code":"\u003cItemGroup\u003e\n  \u003cProtobuf Include=\"Protos/greet.proto\" GrpcServices=\"Server\" /\u003e\n  \u003cPackageReference Include=\"Grpc.AspNetCore\" /\u003e\n\u003c/ItemGroup\u003e"},{"kind":"h3","html":"Server impl","text":"Server impl"},{"kind":"code","lang":"cs","code":"public class GreeterImpl : Greeter.GreeterBase {\n    public override Task\u003cHelloReply\u003e SayHello(HelloRequest req, ServerCallContext ctx) {\n        return Task.FromResult(new HelloReply { Message = $\"Hello {req.Name}\" });\n    }\n}\n// Program.cs\nbuilder.Services.AddGrpc();\napp.MapGrpcService\u003cGreeterImpl\u003e();"},{"kind":"h3","html":"Client","text":"Client"},{"kind":"code","lang":"cs","code":"using var channel = GrpcChannel.ForAddress(\"https://localhost:5001\");\nvar client = new Greeter.GreeterClient(channel);\nvar reply = await client.SayHelloAsync(new HelloRequest { Name = \"Bob\", Age = 30 });\nConsole.WriteLine(reply.Message);"},{"kind":"h3","html":"DI client","text":"DI client"},{"kind":"code","lang":"cs","code":"builder.Services.AddGrpcClient\u003cGreeter.GreeterClient\u003e(o =\u003e {\n    o.Address = new Uri(\"https://localhost:5001\");\n});"},{"kind":"h3","html":"Exam traps","text":"Exam traps"},{"kind":"p","html":"\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eField numbers (\u003ccode\u003e= 1, = 2\u003c/code\u003e) are ID tags, NOT ordinals; reordering in code is fine\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eTags 1-15 encode in 1 byte → reserve them for frequent fields\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eServer-streaming uses \u003ccode\u003eIServerStreamWriter&lt;T&gt;\u003c/code\u003e and returns \u003ccode\u003eTask\u003c/code\u003e, writes with \u003ccode\u003eawait responseStream.WriteAsync(...)\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eDefault port in ASP.NET gRPC template: HTTPS 5001, HTTP 5000. gRPC REQUIRES HTTP/2, which requires TLS in browsers\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e","text":"-   Field numbers (`= 1, = 2`) are ID tags, NOT ordinals; reordering in code is fine\n-   Tags 1-15 encode in 1 byte → reserve them for frequent fields\n-   Server-streaming uses `IServerStreamWriter\u003cT\u003e` and returns `Task`, writes with `await responseStream.WriteAsync(...)`\n-   Default port in ASP.NET gRPC template: HTTPS 5001, HTTP 5000. gRPC REQUIRES HTTP/2, which requires TLS in browsers\n"}]},{"id":"4870-topic-imemorycache-single-server-cache","title":"IMemoryCache — single-server cache","pillar":"tech","priority":"high","chapter":"W10","tags":["cache"],"blocks":[{"kind":"h3","html":"Register","text":"Register"},{"kind":"code","lang":"cs","code":"builder.Services.AddMemoryCache();"},{"kind":"h3","html":"Consume","text":"Consume"},{"kind":"code","lang":"cs","code":"public class WeatherService {\n    private readonly IMemoryCache _cache;\n    public WeatherService(IMemoryCache cache) { _cache = cache; }\n\n    public Forecast Get() {\n        if (!_cache.TryGetValue(\"fc\", out Forecast fc)) {\n            fc = Load();  // expensive\n            var opts = new MemoryCacheEntryOptions {\n                AbsoluteExpirationRelativeToNow = TimeSpan.FromMinutes(10),\n                SlidingExpiration = TimeSpan.FromMinutes(2),\n                Priority = CacheItemPriority.Normal\n            };\n            _cache.Set(\"fc\", fc, opts);\n        }\n        return fc;\n    }\n}"},{"kind":"h3","html":"GetOrCreateAsync","text":"GetOrCreateAsync"},{"kind":"code","lang":"cs","code":"var fc = await _cache.GetOrCreateAsync(\"fc\", async entry =\u003e {\n    entry.AbsoluteExpirationRelativeToNow = TimeSpan.FromMinutes(10);\n    return await LoadAsync();\n});"},{"kind":"h3","html":"Why this fails in production","text":"Why this fails in production"},{"kind":"p","html":"Each web server has its own \u003ccode\u003eIMemoryCache\u003c/code\u003e. In a load balancer with 3 servers, the same user hitting server A vs B sees different cached data. Solution: use \u003ccode\u003eIDistributedCache\u003c/code\u003e (Redis).","text":"Each web server has its own `IMemoryCache`. In a load balancer with 3 servers, the same user hitting server A vs B sees different cached data. Solution: use `IDistributedCache` (Redis)."}]},{"id":"4870-topic-localization-culture-resources","title":"Localization — culture + resources","pillar":"tech","priority":"medium","chapter":"W10","tags":["localization"],"blocks":[{"kind":"h3","html":"Program.cs setup","text":"Program.cs setup"},{"kind":"code","lang":"cs","code":"builder.Services.AddLocalization(o =\u003e o.ResourcesPath = \"Resources\");\nbuilder.Services.AddRazorPages()\n    .AddViewLocalization()\n    .AddDataAnnotationsLocalization();\n\nbuilder.Services.Configure\u003cRequestLocalizationOptions\u003e(o =\u003e {\n    var cultures = new[] { new CultureInfo(\"en\"), new CultureInfo(\"fr\"), new CultureInfo(\"es\") };\n    o.DefaultRequestCulture = new RequestCulture(\"en\");\n    o.SupportedCultures = cultures;\n    o.SupportedUICultures = cultures;\n});\n\nvar app = builder.Build();\napp.UseRequestLocalization();"},{"kind":"h3","html":"Resource files","text":"Resource files"},{"kind":"p","html":"Default culture: \u003ccode\u003eResources/Pages.Index.resx\u003c/code\u003e (or no .resx — strings used as fallbacks). Localized: \u003ccode\u003eResources/Pages.Index.fr.resx\u003c/code\u003e, \u003ccode\u003eResources/Pages.Index.es.resx\u003c/code\u003e.","text":"Default culture: `Resources/Pages.Index.resx` (or no .resx — strings used as fallbacks). Localized: `Resources/Pages.Index.fr.resx`, `Resources/Pages.Index.es.resx`."},{"kind":"h3","html":"In PageModel","text":"In PageModel"},{"kind":"code","lang":"cs","code":"public class IndexModel : PageModel {\n    private readonly IStringLocalizer\u003cIndexModel\u003e _loc;\n    public IndexModel(IStringLocalizer\u003cIndexModel\u003e loc) { _loc = loc; }\n    public string Greet() =\u003e _loc[\"Hello\"];\n}"},{"kind":"h3","html":"In Razor view","text":"In Razor view"},{"kind":"code","lang":"cs","code":"@inject IViewLocalizer Localizer\n\u003ch1\u003e@Localizer[\"Welcome\"]\u003c/h1\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e@Html.Raw(Localizer[\"GreetWithName\", User.Identity.Name])\u003c/p\u003e"},{"kind":"h3","html":"Change culture via cookie","text":"Change culture via cookie"},{"kind":"code","lang":"cs","code":"Response.Cookies.Append(\n    CookieRequestCultureProvider.DefaultCookieName,\n    CookieRequestCultureProvider.MakeCookieValue(new RequestCulture(\"fr\")),\n    new CookieOptions { Expires = DateTimeOffset.UtcNow.AddYears(1) });"},{"kind":"h3","html":"CurrentCulture vs CurrentUICulture","text":"CurrentCulture vs CurrentUICulture"},{"kind":"p","html":"\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eCurrentCulture\u003c/strong\u003e — number/date formatting (e.g., \u003ccode\u003e1,234.56\u003c/code\u003e US vs \u003ccode\u003e1 234,56\u003c/code\u003e FR)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eCurrentUICulture\u003c/strong\u003e — which .resx to load\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e","text":"-   **CurrentCulture** — number/date formatting (e.g., `1,234.56` US vs `1 234,56` FR)\n-   **CurrentUICulture** — which .resx to load\n"}]},{"id":"4870-topic-mcp-model-context-protocol","title":"MCP — Model Context Protocol","pillar":"tech","priority":"high","chapter":"W05-06","tags":["ai","mcp"],"blocks":[{"kind":"h3","html":"What MCP is","text":"What MCP is"},{"kind":"p","html":"Open protocol for wiring AI models to external tools, resources, and prompts. Two transports:","text":"Open protocol for wiring AI models to external tools, resources, and prompts. Two transports:"},{"kind":"p","html":"\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003estdio\u003c/strong\u003e — process pipe (local, co-located tools)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eSSE\u003c/strong\u003e — Server-Sent Events over HTTP (cloud / remote)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e","text":"-   **stdio** — process pipe (local, co-located tools)\n-   **SSE** — Server-Sent Events over HTTP (cloud / remote)"},{"kind":"h3","html":"Three primitives a server exposes","text":"Three primitives a server exposes"},{"kind":"table","html":"\u003ctable\u003e\n\u003cthead\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003cth\u003ePrimitive\u003c/th\u003e\n\u003cth\u003ePurpose\u003c/th\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003c/thead\u003e\n\u003ctbody\u003e\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eTools\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eExecutable functions the model can call\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eResources\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eRead-only data (files, DB rows, wiki pages)\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003e\u003cstrong\u003ePrompts\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eReusable templated prompts\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003c/tbody\u003e\u003c/table\u003e"},{"kind":"h3","html":"Minimal server (Labs W05/W06)","text":"Minimal server (Labs W05/W06)"},{"kind":"code","lang":"cs","code":"// W05: stdio MCP server (console app, runs under Claude/other host)\nvar builder = Host.CreateApplicationBuilder(args);\nbuilder.Services\n  .AddMcpServer()\n  .WithStdioServerTransport()\n  .WithToolsFromAssembly();\nawait builder.Build().RunAsync();\n\n// Tool class\n[McpServerToolType]\npublic static class Tools {\n  [McpServerTool, Description(\"Multiply two numbers\")]\n  public static int Multiply(int a, int b) =\u003e a * b;\n}"},{"kind":"h3","html":"W06 — Azure Functions MCP server uses SSE transport","text":"W06 — Azure Functions MCP server uses SSE transport"},{"kind":"p","html":"Azure Function app with MCP trigger → reachable over HTTPS → works with any MCP client.","text":"Azure Function app with MCP trigger → reachable over HTTPS → works with any MCP client."},{"kind":"h3","html":"Exam traps","text":"Exam traps"},{"kind":"p","html":"\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eMCP is NOT a Microsoft-only protocol — it&#39;s open, maintained by Anthropic + broader community\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003estdio transport = LOCAL only (not network-addressable)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eSSE = one-way stream from server to client (classic Server-Sent Events)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003ccode\u003e[McpServerTool]\u003c/code\u003e attribute on the method; \u003ccode\u003e[McpServerToolType]\u003c/code\u003e on the class\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e","text":"-   MCP is NOT a Microsoft-only protocol — it's open, maintained by Anthropic + broader community\n-   stdio transport = LOCAL only (not network-addressable)\n-   SSE = one-way stream from server to client (classic Server-Sent Events)\n-   `[McpServerTool]` attribute on the method; `[McpServerToolType]` on the class\n"}]},{"id":"4870-topic-microsoft-agent-framework-maf","title":"Microsoft Agent Framework (MAF)","pillar":"tech","priority":"high","chapter":"W12-13","tags":["ai","maf"],"blocks":[{"kind":"h3","html":"Create an agent","text":"Create an agent"},{"kind":"code","lang":"cs","code":"// NuGet: Microsoft.Agents.AI, Microsoft.Agents.AI.OpenAI\nusing Microsoft.Agents.AI;\nusing OpenAI;\n\nvar client = new OpenAIClient(new ApiKeyCredential(token),\n    new OpenAIClientOptions { Endpoint = new Uri(\"https://models.github.ai/inference\") });\nAIAgent agent = client.AsAIAgent(\"gpt-4o-mini\");\nagent.Instructions = \"You are a helpful weather assistant.\";"},{"kind":"h3","html":"Register an AI tool (function)","text":"Register an AI tool (function)"},{"kind":"code","lang":"cs","code":"string GetWeather(string city) =\u003e $\"It is sunny in {city}.\";\n\nAIFunction weatherTool = AIFunctionFactory.Create(\n    GetWeather,\n    name: \"get_weather\",\n    description: \"Get current weather for a city.\");\n\nagent.Tools.Add(weatherTool);"},{"kind":"h3","html":"Sessions &amp; streaming","text":"Sessions & streaming"},{"kind":"code","lang":"cs","code":"var session = new AgentSession(agent);\n// Single turn\nvar response = await session.RunAsync(\"Weather in Vancouver?\");\nConsole.WriteLine(response);\n\n// Stream tokens\nawait foreach (var update in session.RunStreamingAsync(\"And Toronto?\")) {\n    Console.Write(update.Content);\n}"},{"kind":"h3","html":"Exam traps","text":"Exam traps"},{"kind":"p","html":"\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003ccode\u003eAsAIAgent\u003c/code\u003e is an extension on an OpenAI client — not \u003ccode\u003e.ToAIAgent\u003c/code\u003e or \u003ccode\u003e.CreateAgent\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003ccode\u003eAIFunctionFactory.Create(delegate, name, description)\u003c/code\u003e — delegate comes first\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eTools are added to \u003ccode\u003eagent.Tools\u003c/code\u003e (collection), not via a method\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003ccode\u003eAgentSession\u003c/code\u003e carries multi-turn history — creating a new session each call = no memory\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e","text":"-   `AsAIAgent` is an extension on an OpenAI client — not `.ToAIAgent` or `.CreateAgent`\n-   `AIFunctionFactory.Create(delegate, name, description)` — delegate comes first\n-   Tools are added to `agent.Tools` (collection), not via a method\n-   `AgentSession` carries multi-turn history — creating a new session each call = no memory\n"}]},{"id":"4870-topic-ml-net-full-pipeline-and-metrics","title":"ML.NET — Full pipeline and metrics","pillar":"tech","priority":"high","chapter":"W08-09","tags":["ml-net"],"blocks":[{"kind":"h3","html":"Data model","text":"Data model"},{"kind":"code","lang":"cs","code":"public class TaxiTrip {\n    [LoadColumn(0)] public string VendorId;\n    [LoadColumn(1)] public string RateCode;\n    [LoadColumn(2)] public float PassengerCount;\n    [LoadColumn(3)] public float TripDistance;\n    [LoadColumn(4)] public float FareAmount;  // target\n}\n\npublic class TaxiFarePrediction {\n    [ColumnName(\"Score\")] public float FareAmount;\n}"},{"kind":"h3","html":"Pipeline","text":"Pipeline"},{"kind":"code","lang":"cs","code":"var ml = new MLContext(seed: 0);\nIDataView data = ml.Data.LoadFromTextFile\u003cTaxiTrip\u003e(\"taxi.csv\", hasHeader: true, separatorChar: ',');\nvar split = ml.Data.TrainTestSplit(data, testFraction: 0.2);\n\nvar pipeline = ml.Transforms.CopyColumns(\"Label\", \"FareAmount\")\n    .Append(ml.Transforms.Categorical.OneHotEncoding(\"VendorIdEncoded\", \"VendorId\"))\n    .Append(ml.Transforms.Concatenate(\"Features\", \"VendorIdEncoded\", \"TripDistance\"))\n    .Append(ml.Regression.Trainers.FastTree());\n\nITransformer model = pipeline.Fit(split.TrainSet);\nIDataView preds = model.Transform(split.TestSet);\nvar m = ml.Regression.Evaluate(preds, labelColumnName: \"Label\");\nConsole.WriteLine($\"R²={m.RSquared:F3}, RMSE={m.RootMeanSquaredError:F3}\");\n\nml.Model.Save(model, data.Schema, \"taxi.zip\");"},{"kind":"h3","html":"Trainer namespaces","text":"Trainer namespaces"},{"kind":"table","html":"\u003ctable\u003e\n\u003cthead\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003cth\u003eTask\u003c/th\u003e\n\u003cth\u003eNamespace\u003c/th\u003e\n\u003cth\u003eTrainer examples\u003c/th\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003c/thead\u003e\n\u003ctbody\u003e\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eRegression\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003emlContext.Regression.Trainers\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eFastTree, FastForest, Sdca, LightGbm\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eBinary classification\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eBinaryClassification.Trainers\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eLogisticRegression, AveragedPerceptron\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eMulticlass\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eMulticlassClassification.Trainers\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eNaiveBayes, SdcaMaximumEntropy\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eClustering\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eClustering.Trainers\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eKMeans\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003c/tbody\u003e\u003c/table\u003e"},{"kind":"h3","html":"Metrics","text":"Metrics"},{"kind":"table","html":"\u003ctable\u003e\n\u003cthead\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003cth\u003eTask\u003c/th\u003e\n\u003cth\u003eMetric\u003c/th\u003e\n\u003cth\u003eBetter direction\u003c/th\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003c/thead\u003e\n\u003ctbody\u003e\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eRegression\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eRSquared\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003e0→1, higher = better\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eRegression\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eRootMeanSquaredError (RMSE)\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003elower = better\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eBinary\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eAccuracy, F1Score, AreaUnderRocCurve\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003ehigher = better\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eMulticlass\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eMacroAccuracy, LogLoss\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eacc higher, logloss lower\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003c/tbody\u003e\u003c/table\u003e"}]},{"id":"4870-topic-ollama-running-a-local-slm","title":"Ollama — running a local SLM","pillar":"tech","priority":"high","chapter":"W12-13","tags":["ai","dotnet"],"blocks":[{"kind":"h3","html":"Install + download model","text":"Install + download model"},{"kind":"code","lang":"cs","code":"ollama pull llama3        # download\nollama run llama3         # interactive REPL\nollama list               # list downloaded models"},{"kind":"h3","html":"C# client via OllamaSharp","text":"C# client via OllamaSharp"},{"kind":"code","lang":"cs","code":"// NuGet: OllamaSharp\nvar ollama = new OllamaApiClient(\"http://localhost:11434\");\nollama.SelectedModel = \"llama3\";\nawait foreach (var chunk in ollama.GenerateAsync(\"Tell me a joke\")) {\n    Console.Write(chunk.Response);\n}"},{"kind":"h3","html":"With Semantic Kernel","text":"With Semantic Kernel"},{"kind":"code","lang":"cs","code":"var b = Kernel.CreateBuilder();\nb.AddOllamaChatCompletion(\"llama3\", new Uri(\"http://localhost:11434\"));\nvar kernel = b.Build();"},{"kind":"h3","html":"Why Ollama","text":"Why Ollama"},{"kind":"p","html":"\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eRuns locally — NO API key, NO cloud bill, offline-capable\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eGood for privacy-sensitive or learning contexts\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eTradeoff: slower, smaller models (7B-13B typical vs 1T+ cloud)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e","text":"-   Runs locally — NO API key, NO cloud bill, offline-capable\n-   Good for privacy-sensitive or learning contexts\n-   Tradeoff: slower, smaller models (7B-13B typical vs 1T+ cloud)"},{"kind":"h3","html":"Exam traps","text":"Exam traps"},{"kind":"p","html":"\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eEndpoint is \u003ccode\u003ehttp://\u003c/code\u003e (not https) on localhost\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eDefault port 11434\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eOpenAI SDK is NOT the Ollama SDK — use \u003ccode\u003eOllamaSharp\u003c/code\u003e for direct calls OR SK&#39;s \u003ccode\u003eAddOllamaChatCompletion\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e","text":"-   Endpoint is `http://` (not https) on localhost\n-   Default port 11434\n-   OpenAI SDK is NOT the Ollama SDK — use `OllamaSharp` for direct calls OR SK's `AddOllamaChatCompletion`\n"}]},{"id":"4870-topic-redis-idistributedcache-cache-tag-helper","title":"Redis (IDistributedCache) + Cache Tag Helper","pillar":"tech","priority":"high","chapter":"W10","tags":["cache","tag-helpers"],"blocks":[{"kind":"h3","html":"Start Redis","text":"Start Redis"},{"kind":"code","lang":"cs","code":"docker run -d --name redis -p 6379:6379 redis"},{"kind":"h3","html":"Register","text":"Register"},{"kind":"code","lang":"cs","code":"builder.Services.AddStackExchangeRedisCache(o =\u003e {\n    o.Configuration = \"localhost:6379\";\n    o.InstanceName = \"myapp_\";\n});"},{"kind":"h3","html":"Consume","text":"Consume"},{"kind":"code","lang":"cs","code":"public class Svc {\n    private readonly IDistributedCache _cache;\n    public Svc(IDistributedCache c) { _cache = c; }\n    public async Task SetAsync(string key, string value) {\n        var opts = new DistributedCacheEntryOptions {\n            AbsoluteExpirationRelativeToNow = TimeSpan.FromMinutes(10)\n        };\n        await _cache.SetStringAsync(key, value, opts);\n    }\n    public Task\u003cstring\u003e GetAsync(string key) =\u003e _cache.GetStringAsync(key);\n}"},{"kind":"h3","html":"Cache Tag Helper","text":"Cache Tag Helper"},{"kind":"code","lang":"cs","code":"\u003ccache expires-after=\"@TimeSpan.FromMinutes(10)\"\n       vary-by-user=\"true\"\n       vary-by-route=\"category\"\n       vary-by-query=\"page;sort\"\n       priority=\"High\"\u003e\n    \u003cpartial name=\"_ExpensiveFragment\" /\u003e\n\u003c/cache\u003e"},{"kind":"p","html":"\u003cstrong\u003evary-by-*\u003c/strong\u003e attributes: \u003ccode\u003evary-by-user\u003c/code\u003e, \u003ccode\u003evary-by-route\u003c/code\u003e, \u003ccode\u003evary-by-query\u003c/code\u003e, \u003ccode\u003evary-by-cookie\u003c/code\u003e, \u003ccode\u003evary-by-header\u003c/code\u003e, custom \u003ccode\u003evary-by=&quot;@Model.Id&quot;\u003c/code\u003e.","text":"**vary-by-\\*** attributes: `vary-by-user`, `vary-by-route`, `vary-by-query`, `vary-by-cookie`, `vary-by-header`, custom `vary-by=\"@Model.Id\"`."},{"kind":"p","html":"Uses \u003ccode\u003eIMemoryCache\u003c/code\u003e under the hood → same load-balancer caveat applies.","text":"Uses `IMemoryCache` under the hood → same load-balancer caveat applies."}]},{"id":"4870-topic-semantic-kernel-kernel-chathistory-plugins","title":"Semantic Kernel — Kernel, ChatHistory, Plugins","pillar":"tech","priority":"high","chapter":"W12-13","tags":["ai","semantic-kernel"],"blocks":[{"kind":"h3","html":"Exact registration pattern","text":"Exact registration pattern"},{"kind":"code","lang":"cs","code":"// Program.cs\nvar builder = Kernel.CreateBuilder();\n// Ollama (local)\nbuilder.AddOllamaChatCompletion(\"llama3\", new Uri(\"http://localhost:11434\"));\n// OR OpenAI-compatible (e.g., GitHub Models)\nbuilder.AddOpenAIChatCompletion(\n    modelId: \"gpt-4o-mini\",\n    apiKey: token,\n    endpoint: new Uri(\"https://models.github.ai/inference\"));\nKernel kernel = builder.Build();"},{"kind":"h3","html":"Running a prompt","text":"Running a prompt"},{"kind":"code","lang":"cs","code":"var chat = kernel.GetRequiredService\u003cIChatCompletionService\u003e();\nvar history = new ChatHistory(\"You are a helpful assistant.\");\nhistory.AddUserMessage(\"Hello!\");\nvar response = await chat.GetChatMessageContentAsync(history, kernel: kernel);\nConsole.WriteLine(response.Content);"},{"kind":"h3","html":"Plugins (C# native)","text":"Plugins (C# native)"},{"kind":"code","lang":"cs","code":"public class MathPlugin {\n    [KernelFunction, Description(\"Add two numbers\")]\n    public int Add(int a, int b) =\u003e a + b;\n}\n// Register\nkernel.ImportPluginFromType\u003cMathPlugin\u003e();"},{"kind":"h3","html":"Plugins (prompt-based / skprompt.txt)","text":"Plugins (prompt-based / skprompt.txt)"},{"kind":"code","lang":"cs","code":"// Folder structure:\n// Plugins/\n//   Writer/\n//     Summarize/\n//       skprompt.txt       \u003c- contains prompt with {{$input}}\n//       config.json        \u003c- execution settings\n\nkernel.ImportPluginFromPromptDirectory(\"Plugins/Writer\");"},{"kind":"h3","html":"Exam traps","text":"Exam traps"},{"kind":"p","html":"\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003ccode\u003eKernel.CreateBuilder()\u003c/code\u003e NOT \u003ccode\u003enew Kernel()\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eOllama default port 11434 (not 11343, not 11434 over HTTPS)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003ePlugin annotation is \u003ccode\u003e[KernelFunction]\u003c/code\u003e not \u003ccode\u003e[SKFunction]\u003c/code\u003e (renamed)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eSystem prompt goes into \u003ccode\u003eChatHistory\u003c/code\u003e ctor OR \u003ccode\u003eAddSystemMessage\u003c/code\u003e — it does NOT go to the user message\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e","text":"-   `Kernel.CreateBuilder()` NOT `new Kernel()`\n-   Ollama default port 11434 (not 11343, not 11434 over HTTPS)\n-   Plugin annotation is `[KernelFunction]` not `[SKFunction]` (renamed)\n-   System prompt goes into `ChatHistory` ctor OR `AddSystemMessage` — it does NOT go to the user message\n"}]},{"id":"4870-topic-tag-helpers-built-in-and-custom","title":"Tag Helpers — built-in and custom","pillar":"tech","priority":"medium","chapter":"W07","tags":["taghelpers","tag-helpers"],"blocks":[{"kind":"h3","html":"Register in _ViewImports.cshtml","text":"Register in \\_ViewImports.cshtml"},{"kind":"code","lang":"cs","code":"@addTagHelper *, Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.TagHelpers\n@addTagHelper \"*, MyApp\"  // your custom tag helpers"},{"kind":"h3","html":"Built-in reference","text":"Built-in reference"},{"kind":"table","html":"\u003ctable\u003e\n\u003cthead\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003cth\u003eElement\u003c/th\u003e\n\u003cth\u003eKey attrs\u003c/th\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003c/thead\u003e\n\u003ctbody\u003e\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eform\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003easp-controller, asp-action, asp-route-*\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003einput/label/select/textarea\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003easp-for, asp-items\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003espan/div\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003easp-validation-for\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003ediv (summary)\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003easp-validation-summary\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003ea\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003easp-controller, asp-action, asp-route-*\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003escript / link\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003easp-append-version, asp-fallback-src\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eenvironment\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003enames (Development, Production)\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003ctr\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003ecache\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003ctd\u003eexpires-after, vary-by-*\u003c/td\u003e\n\u003c/tr\u003e\n\u003c/tbody\u003e\u003c/table\u003e"},{"kind":"h3","html":"Custom tag helper skeleton","text":"Custom tag helper skeleton"},{"kind":"code","lang":"cs","code":"using Microsoft.AspNetCore.Razor.TagHelpers;\n\n[HtmlTargetElement(\"quote\")]  // \u003cquote text=\"...\"\u003e\u003c/quote\u003e\npublic class QuoteTag : TagHelper {\n    public string Text { get; set; }\n    public string Author { get; set; }  // attribute: author\n\n    public override void Process(TagHelperContext ctx, TagHelperOutput out) {\n        out.TagName = \"blockquote\";\n        out.Attributes.SetAttribute(\"class\", \"quote\");\n        out.Content.SetHtmlContent($\"\"{Text}\" — {Author}\");\n    }\n}"},{"kind":"h3","html":"Kebab-case rule","text":"Kebab-case rule"},{"kind":"p","html":"Property \u003ccode\u003eFontFamily\u003c/code\u003e → HTML attribute \u003ccode\u003efont-family\u003c/code\u003e. Property \u003ccode\u003eText\u003c/code\u003e → \u003ccode\u003etext\u003c/code\u003e.","text":"Property `FontFamily` → HTML attribute `font-family`. Property `Text` → `text`."}]},{"id":"4870-topic-xunit-the-full-assert-surface","title":"xUnit — the full Assert surface","pillar":"tech","priority":"high","chapter":"W08","tags":["tdd"],"blocks":[{"kind":"h3","html":"Full example — AAA + Theory + exception + async","text":"Full example — AAA + Theory + exception + async"},{"kind":"code","lang":"cs","code":"public class CalculatorTests : IDisposable {\n    private readonly Calculator _calc;\n\n    public CalculatorTests() {   // setup\n        _calc = new Calculator();\n    }\n\n    public void Dispose() { }    // teardown\n\n    [Fact]\n    public void Add_TwoPositives_ReturnsSum() {\n        var r = _calc.Add(2, 3);\n        Assert.Equal(5, r);\n    }\n\n    [Theory]\n    [InlineData(1, 2, 3)]\n    [InlineData(0, 0, 0)]\n    [InlineData(-1, 1, 0)]\n    public void Add_Various(int a, int b, int expected) {\n        Assert.Equal(expected, _calc.Add(a, b));\n    }\n\n    [Fact]\n    public void Divide_ByZero_Throws() {\n        var ex = Assert.Throws\u003cDivideByZeroException\u003e(() =\u003e _calc.Divide(5, 0));\n        Assert.Contains(\"zero\", ex.Message);\n    }\n\n    [Fact]\n    public async Task LongTask_Completes() {\n        await Assert.ThrowsAsync\u003cTimeoutException\u003e(async () =\u003e await _calc.SlowAsync());\n    }\n}"},{"kind":"h3","html":"Asserts in the course","text":"Asserts in the course"},{"kind":"p","html":"\u003ccode\u003eEqual, NotEqual, True, False, Null, NotNull, Same, NotSame, Throws&lt;T&gt;, ThrowsAsync&lt;T&gt;, Contains, DoesNotContain, Empty, NotEmpty, InRange, IsType&lt;T&gt;, IsAssignableFrom&lt;T&gt;, Collection\u003c/code\u003e","text":"`Equal, NotEqual, True, False, Null, NotNull, Same, NotSame, Throws\u003cT\u003e, ThrowsAsync\u003cT\u003e, Contains, DoesNotContain, Empty, NotEmpty, InRange, IsType\u003cT\u003e, IsAssignableFrom\u003cT\u003e, Collection`"},{"kind":"h3","html":"Test data sources","text":"Test data sources"},{"kind":"p","html":"\u003ccode\u003e[InlineData(...)]\u003c/code\u003e — literal args. \u003ccode\u003e[MemberData(nameof(Data))]\u003c/code\u003e — reference a static \u003ccode\u003eIEnumerable&lt;object[]&gt;\u003c/code\u003e property. \u003ccode\u003e[ClassData(typeof(X))]\u003c/code\u003e — class implementing \u003ccode\u003eIEnumerable&lt;object[]&gt;\u003c/code\u003e.","text":"`[InlineData(...)]` — literal args. `[MemberData(nameof(Data))]` — reference a static `IEnumerable\u003cobject[]\u003e` property. `[ClassData(typeof(X))]` — class implementing `IEnumerable\u003cobject[]\u003e`."},{"kind":"h3","html":"Shared fixtures","text":"Shared fixtures"},{"kind":"p","html":"\u003ccode\u003eIClassFixture&lt;TFx&gt;\u003c/code\u003e — one fixture per test class. \u003ccode\u003eICollectionFixture&lt;TFx&gt;\u003c/code\u003e + \u003ccode\u003e[Collection(&quot;Name&quot;)]\u003c/code\u003e — shared across classes.","text":"`IClassFixture\u003cTFx\u003e` — one fixture per test class. `ICollectionFixture\u003cTFx\u003e` + `[Collection(\"Name\")]` — shared across classes."}]},{"id":"4870-topic-blazor-quickgrid","title":"Blazor QuickGrid","pillar":"tech","priority":"low","chapter":"W07","tags":["blazor"],"blocks":[{"kind":"h3","html":"Setup","text":"Setup"},{"kind":"code","lang":"cs","code":"// _Imports.razor\n@using Microsoft.AspNetCore.Components.QuickGrid"},{"kind":"h3","html":"Full grid with sort + pagination + filter","text":"Full grid with sort + pagination + filter"},{"kind":"code","lang":"cs","code":"@page \"/students\"\n\n\u003cinput @bind=\"filter\" @bind:event=\"oninput\" placeholder=\"Search...\" /\u003e\n\n\u003cQuickGrid Items=\"@filtered\" Pagination=\"@pagination\"\u003e\n    \u003cPropertyColumn Property=\"@(_ =\u003e _.Id)\" Sortable=\"true\" /\u003e\n    \u003cTemplateColumn Title=\"Name\" SortBy=\"@sortByName\"\u003e\n        \u003cstrong\u003e@context.FirstName @context.LastName\u003c/strong\u003e\n    \u003c/TemplateColumn\u003e\n    \u003cPropertyColumn Property=\"@(_ =\u003e _.School)\" Sortable=\"true\" /\u003e\n\u003c/QuickGrid\u003e\n\n\u003cPaginator State=\"@pagination\" /\u003e\n\n@code {\n    string filter = \"\";\n    PaginationState pagination = new() { ItemsPerPage = 10 };\n    GridSort\u003cStudent\u003e sortByName = GridSort\u003cStudent\u003e\n        .ByAscending(s =\u003e s.FirstName).ThenAscending(s =\u003e s.LastName);\n\n    IQueryable\u003cStudent\u003e allStudents = Student.GetStudents();\n    IQueryable\u003cStudent\u003e filtered =\u003e string.IsNullOrEmpty(filter)\n        ? allStudents\n        : allStudents.Where(s =\u003e s.FirstName.Contains(filter, StringComparison.OrdinalIgnoreCase));\n}"},{"kind":"h3","html":"Server vs WASM","text":"Server vs WASM"},{"kind":"p","html":"\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eServer\u003c/strong\u003e: use \u003ccode\u003eItemsProvider\u003c/code\u003e callback for server-paged data\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eWASM\u003c/strong\u003e: \u003ccode\u003eIQueryable&lt;T&gt;\u003c/code\u003e is in-memory only (no LINQ-to-SQL on client)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e","text":"-   **Server**: use `ItemsProvider` callback for server-paged data\n-   **WASM**: `IQueryable\u003cT\u003e` is in-memory only (no LINQ-to-SQL on client)"},{"kind":"h3","html":"Exam traps","text":"Exam traps"},{"kind":"p","html":"\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003ccode\u003ePropertyColumn\u003c/code\u003e sortable with \u003ccode\u003eSortable=&quot;true&quot;\u003c/code\u003e. \u003ccode\u003eTemplateColumn\u003c/code\u003e needs \u003ccode\u003eSortBy\u003c/code\u003e, not Sortable.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eMust declare \u003ccode\u003ePaginationState\u003c/code\u003e explicitly — not auto-created\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003ePackage: \u003ccode\u003eMicrosoft.AspNetCore.Components.QuickGrid\u003c/code\u003e — .NET 8+\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e","text":"-   `PropertyColumn` sortable with `Sortable=\"true\"`. `TemplateColumn` needs `SortBy`, not Sortable.\n-   Must declare `PaginationState` explicitly — not auto-created\n-   Package: `Microsoft.AspNetCore.Components.QuickGrid` — .NET 8+\n"}]},{"id":"4870-topic-excel-pdf-chart-export","title":"Excel / PDF / Chart export","pillar":"tech","priority":"low","chapter":"W13","tags":["excelpdf","excel","pdf","chart"],"blocks":[{"kind":"h3","html":"Excel with ClosedXML","text":"Excel with ClosedXML"},{"kind":"code","lang":"cs","code":"using ClosedXML.Excel;\nusing var wb = new XLWorkbook();\nvar ws = wb.Worksheets.Add(\"Sheet1\");\nws.Cell(1, 1).Value = \"Name\";\nws.Cell(1, 2).Value = \"Score\";\nws.Cell(2, 1).Value = \"Alice\";\nws.Cell(2, 2).Value = 92;\n\nusing var ms = new MemoryStream();\nwb.SaveAs(ms);\nreturn File(ms.ToArray(),\n    \"application/vnd.openxmlformats-officedocument.spreadsheetml.sheet\",\n    \"report.xlsx\");"},{"kind":"h3","html":"PDF with iText7","text":"PDF with iText7"},{"kind":"code","lang":"cs","code":"using iText.Kernel.Pdf;\nusing iText.Layout;\nusing iText.Layout.Element;\n\nusing var ms = new MemoryStream();\nvar writer = new PdfWriter(ms);\nvar pdf = new PdfDocument(writer);\nvar doc = new Document(pdf);\ndoc.Add(new Paragraph(\"Hello PDF\"));\nvar table = new Table(2);\ntable.AddCell(\"Name\"); table.AddCell(\"Score\");\ntable.AddCell(\"Alice\"); table.AddCell(\"92\");\ndoc.Add(table);\ndoc.Close();\nreturn File(ms.ToArray(), \"application/pdf\", \"report.pdf\");"},{"kind":"p","html":"\u003cstrong\u003eRequired packages:\u003c/strong\u003e \u003ccode\u003eitext7\u003c/code\u003e + \u003ccode\u003eitext.bouncy-castle-adapter\u003c/code\u003e","text":"**Required packages:** `itext7` + `itext.bouncy-castle-adapter`"},{"kind":"h3","html":"Chart.js (client-side in Razor)","text":"Chart.js (client-side in Razor)"},{"kind":"code","lang":"cs","code":"\u003ccanvas id=\"myChart\"\u003e\u003c/canvas\u003e\n\u003cscript src=\"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/chart.js\"\u003e\u003c/script\u003e\n\u003cscript\u003e\n  new Chart(document.getElementById('myChart'), {\n    type: 'pie',\n    data: {\n      labels: [@:Html.Raw(string.Join(',', labels.Select(l =\u003e $\"'{l}'\")))],\n      datasets: [{ data: [@:Html.Raw(string.Join(',', values))] }]\n    }\n  });\n\u003c/script\u003e"},{"kind":"h3","html":"MIME types","text":"MIME types"},{"kind":"p","html":"\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eExcel \u003ccode\u003e.xlsx\u003c/code\u003e → \u003ccode\u003eapplication/vnd.openxmlformats-officedocument.spreadsheetml.sheet\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003ePDF → \u003ccode\u003eapplication/pdf\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003ePNG image → \u003ccode\u003eimage/png\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e","text":"-   Excel `.xlsx` → `application/vnd.openxmlformats-officedocument.spreadsheetml.sheet`\n-   PDF → `application/pdf`\n-   PNG image → `image/png`\n"}]}],"cheatSheet":{"title":"COMP 4870 — exam-eve cheat sheet","blocks":[{"heading":"AI — Semantic Kernel skeleton","body_md":"```cs\nvar b = Kernel.CreateBuilder();\nb.AddOllamaChatCompletion(\"llama3\",\n  new Uri(\"http://localhost:11434\"));\nKernel kernel = b.Build();\n\nvar chat = kernel.GetRequiredService\n  \u003cIChatCompletionService\u003e();\nvar h = new ChatHistory(\"system\");\nh.AddUserMessage(\"...\");\nvar r = await chat.GetChatMessageContentAsync(h, kernel: kernel);\n\nkernel.ImportPluginFromType\u003cMyPlugin\u003e();\n// [KernelFunction, Description(\"...\")]\n```","body_html":"\u003cpre\u003e\u003ccode class=\"language-cs\"\u003evar b = Kernel.CreateBuilder();\nb.AddOllamaChatCompletion(&quot;llama3&quot;,\n  new Uri(&quot;http://localhost:11434&quot;));\nKernel kernel = b.Build();\n\nvar chat = kernel.GetRequiredService\n  &lt;IChatCompletionService&gt;();\nvar h = new ChatHistory(&quot;system&quot;);\nh.AddUserMessage(&quot;...&quot;);\nvar r = await chat.GetChatMessageContentAsync(h, kernel: kernel);\n\nkernel.ImportPluginFromType&lt;MyPlugin&gt;();\n// [KernelFunction, Description(&quot;...&quot;)]\n\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e"},{"heading":"AI — MAF agent skeleton","body_md":"```cs\nusing Microsoft.Agents.AI;\nvar client = new OpenAIClient(cred,\n  new OpenAIClientOptions { Endpoint =\n    new Uri(\"https://models.github.ai/inference\")});\nvar agent = client.AsAIAgent(\"gpt-4o-mini\");\nvar tool = AIFunctionFactory.Create(\n  MyFn, \"name\", \"desc\");\nagent.Tools.Add(tool);\nvar s = new AgentSession(agent);\nawait foreach (var u in s.RunStreamingAsync(\"q\"))\n  Console.Write(u);\n```","body_html":"\u003cpre\u003e\u003ccode class=\"language-cs\"\u003eusing Microsoft.Agents.AI;\nvar client = new OpenAIClient(cred,\n  new OpenAIClientOptions { Endpoint =\n    new Uri(&quot;https://models.github.ai/inference&quot;)});\nvar agent = client.AsAIAgent(&quot;gpt-4o-mini&quot;);\nvar tool = AIFunctionFactory.Create(\n  MyFn, &quot;name&quot;, &quot;desc&quot;);\nagent.Tools.Add(tool);\nvar s = new AgentSession(agent);\nawait foreach (var u in s.RunStreamingAsync(&quot;q&quot;))\n  Console.Write(u);\n\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e"},{"heading":"AI — MCP transports + primitives","body_md":"-   **stdio** — local process pipe\n-   **SSE** — HTTP Server-Sent Events\n\n3 primitives: **Tools** (exec) · **Resources** (data) · **Prompts** (templates)\n\nServer tool: `[McpServerTool]` on method, `[McpServerToolType]` on class. `.WithStdioServerTransport().WithToolsFromAssembly()`","body_html":"\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003estdio\u003c/strong\u003e — local process pipe\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eSSE\u003c/strong\u003e — HTTP Server-Sent Events\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e3 primitives: \u003cstrong\u003eTools\u003c/strong\u003e (exec) · \u003cstrong\u003eResources\u003c/strong\u003e (data) · \u003cstrong\u003ePrompts\u003c/strong\u003e (templates)\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eServer tool: \u003ccode\u003e[McpServerTool]\u003c/code\u003e on method, \u003ccode\u003e[McpServerToolType]\u003c/code\u003e on class. \u003ccode\u003e.WithStdioServerTransport().WithToolsFromAssembly()\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/p\u003e"},{"heading":"ML.NET — 7-step pipeline","body_md":"```cs\nvar ml = new MLContext(seed:0);\nIDataView d = ml.Data.LoadFromTextFile\u003cT\u003e(\n  \"x.csv\", hasHeader:true, separatorChar:',');\nvar sp = ml.Data.TrainTestSplit(d, 0.2);\n\nvar p = ml.Transforms.Concatenate(\"Features\",...)\n  .Append(ml.Regression.Trainers.FastTree());\n\nITransformer m = p.Fit(sp.TrainSet);\nvar pr = m.Transform(sp.TestSet);\nvar mx = ml.Regression.Evaluate(pr, \"Label\");\nml.Model.Save(m, d.Schema, \"m.zip\");\n```\n\nAttrs: `[LoadColumn(0)]`, `[ColumnName(\"Label\")]`, `[ColumnName(\"Score\")]` (output)","body_html":"\u003cpre\u003e\u003ccode class=\"language-cs\"\u003evar ml = new MLContext(seed:0);\nIDataView d = ml.Data.LoadFromTextFile&lt;T&gt;(\n  &quot;x.csv&quot;, hasHeader:true, separatorChar:&#39;,&#39;);\nvar sp = ml.Data.TrainTestSplit(d, 0.2);\n\nvar p = ml.Transforms.Concatenate(&quot;Features&quot;,...)\n  .Append(ml.Regression.Trainers.FastTree());\n\nITransformer m = p.Fit(sp.TrainSet);\nvar pr = m.Transform(sp.TestSet);\nvar mx = ml.Regression.Evaluate(pr, &quot;Label&quot;);\nml.Model.Save(m, d.Schema, &quot;m.zip&quot;);\n\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eAttrs: \u003ccode\u003e[LoadColumn(0)]\u003c/code\u003e, \u003ccode\u003e[ColumnName(&quot;Label&quot;)]\u003c/code\u003e, \u003ccode\u003e[ColumnName(&quot;Score&quot;)]\u003c/code\u003e (output)\u003c/p\u003e"},{"heading":"ML.NET — trainer namespaces","body_md":"-   `mlContext.Regression.Trainers` — FastTree, FastForest, Sdca\n-   `BinaryClassification.Trainers` — Logistic, AveragedPerceptron\n-   `MulticlassClassification.Trainers` — NaiveBayes, SdcaMax\n-   `Clustering.Trainers` — KMeans\n\nMetrics: Regression → RSquared, RMSE. Binary → Accuracy, AUC, F1. Multi → MacroAccuracy, LogLoss.","body_html":"\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003ccode\u003emlContext.Regression.Trainers\u003c/code\u003e — FastTree, FastForest, Sdca\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003ccode\u003eBinaryClassification.Trainers\u003c/code\u003e — Logistic, AveragedPerceptron\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003ccode\u003eMulticlassClassification.Trainers\u003c/code\u003e — NaiveBayes, SdcaMax\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003ccode\u003eClustering.Trainers\u003c/code\u003e — KMeans\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eMetrics: Regression → RSquared, RMSE. Binary → Accuracy, AUC, F1. Multi → MacroAccuracy, LogLoss.\u003c/p\u003e"},{"heading":"Cache — 3 strategies","body_md":"```cs\n// In-memory\nbuilder.Services.AddMemoryCache();\n_cache.TryGetValue\u003cT\u003e(\"k\", out var v);\n_cache.Set(\"k\", v, new MemoryCacheEntryOptions {\n  AbsoluteExpirationRelativeToNow = TimeSpan.FromMinutes(10),\n  SlidingExpiration = TimeSpan.FromMinutes(2)});\n\n// Redis\nbuilder.Services.AddStackExchangeRedisCache(\n  o =\u003e o.Configuration = \"localhost:6379\");\n// inject IDistributedCache\n\n// Tag helper\n\u003ccache expires-after=\"@TimeSpan.FromMinutes(10)\"\n  vary-by-user=\"true\" vary-by-route=\"id\"\u003e\n  \u003cpartial name=\"_X\"/\u003e\u003c/cache\u003e\n```","body_html":"\u003cpre\u003e\u003ccode class=\"language-cs\"\u003e// In-memory\nbuilder.Services.AddMemoryCache();\n_cache.TryGetValue&lt;T&gt;(&quot;k&quot;, out var v);\n_cache.Set(&quot;k&quot;, v, new MemoryCacheEntryOptions {\n  AbsoluteExpirationRelativeToNow = TimeSpan.FromMinutes(10),\n  SlidingExpiration = TimeSpan.FromMinutes(2)});\n\n// Redis\nbuilder.Services.AddStackExchangeRedisCache(\n  o =&gt; o.Configuration = &quot;localhost:6379&quot;);\n// inject IDistributedCache\n\n// Tag helper\n&lt;cache expires-after=&quot;@TimeSpan.FromMinutes(10)&quot;\n  vary-by-user=&quot;true&quot; vary-by-route=&quot;id&quot;&gt;\n  &lt;partial name=&quot;_X&quot;/&gt;&lt;/cache&gt;\n\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e"},{"heading":"gRPC — proto + server + client","body_md":"```cs\n// .proto\nsyntax = \"proto3\";\noption csharp_namespace = \"X\";\nservice S { rpc M (Req) returns (Rep); }\nmessage Req { int32 a = 1; }\nmessage Rep { string r = 1; }\n\n// csproj\n\u003cProtobuf Include=\"Protos/s.proto\"\n  GrpcServices=\"Server\"/\u003e\n\n// server\nbuilder.Services.AddGrpc();\napp.MapGrpcService\u003cImpl\u003e();\npublic class Impl : S.SBase {\n  public override Task\u003cRep\u003e M(Req r, ServerCallContext c)\n    =\u003e Task.FromResult(new Rep{R=\"hi\"});\n}\n\n// client\nvar ch = GrpcChannel.ForAddress(\"https://...\");\nvar c = new S.SClient(ch);\nawait c.MAsync(new Req{A=1});\n```","body_html":"\u003cpre\u003e\u003ccode class=\"language-cs\"\u003e// .proto\nsyntax = &quot;proto3&quot;;\noption csharp_namespace = &quot;X&quot;;\nservice S { rpc M (Req) returns (Rep); }\nmessage Req { int32 a = 1; }\nmessage Rep { string r = 1; }\n\n// csproj\n&lt;Protobuf Include=&quot;Protos/s.proto&quot;\n  GrpcServices=&quot;Server&quot;/&gt;\n\n// server\nbuilder.Services.AddGrpc();\napp.MapGrpcService&lt;Impl&gt;();\npublic class Impl : S.SBase {\n  public override Task&lt;Rep&gt; M(Req r, ServerCallContext c)\n    =&gt; Task.FromResult(new Rep{R=&quot;hi&quot;});\n}\n\n// client\nvar ch = GrpcChannel.ForAddress(&quot;https://...&quot;);\nvar c = new S.SClient(ch);\nawait c.MAsync(new Req{A=1});\n\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e"},{"heading":"xUnit — cheat block","body_md":"```cs\n[Fact]\npublic void X_When_Y() {\n  // Arrange\n  var s = new Svc();\n  // Act\n  var r = s.Do();\n  // Assert  EXPECTED, ACTUAL\n  Assert.Equal(5, r);\n}\n\n[Theory]\n[InlineData(1,2,3)]\n[InlineData(0,0,0)]\npublic void Add(int a,int b,int e) =\u003e\n  Assert.Equal(e, new Calc().Add(a,b));\n\nAssert.Throws\u003cEx\u003e(()=\u003ebad());\nawait Assert.ThrowsAsync\u003cEx\u003e(async ()=\u003eawait bad());\n// teardown → IDisposable\n// shared → IClassFixture\u003cF\u003e\n```","body_html":"\u003cpre\u003e\u003ccode class=\"language-cs\"\u003e[Fact]\npublic void X_When_Y() {\n  // Arrange\n  var s = new Svc();\n  // Act\n  var r = s.Do();\n  // Assert  EXPECTED, ACTUAL\n  Assert.Equal(5, r);\n}\n\n[Theory]\n[InlineData(1,2,3)]\n[InlineData(0,0,0)]\npublic void Add(int a,int b,int e) =&gt;\n  Assert.Equal(e, new Calc().Add(a,b));\n\nAssert.Throws&lt;Ex&gt;(()=&gt;bad());\nawait Assert.ThrowsAsync&lt;Ex&gt;(async ()=&gt;await bad());\n// teardown → IDisposable\n// shared → IClassFixture&lt;F&gt;\n\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e"},{"heading":"File-based C# — all directives","body_md":"```cs\n#:package Spectre.Console@0.48.0\n#:package Newtonsoft.Json@13.0.3\n#:sdk Microsoft.NET.Sdk.Web\n#:property LangVersion=preview\n#:project ./lib/X.csproj\n\nConsole.WriteLine(\"Hello\");\n```\n\n-   Run: `dotnet run app.cs`\n-   Convert: `dotnet project convert app.cs`\n-   NO space after colon\n-   .NET 10 required","body_html":"\u003cpre\u003e\u003ccode class=\"language-cs\"\u003e#:package Spectre.Console@0.48.0\n#:package Newtonsoft.Json@13.0.3\n#:sdk Microsoft.NET.Sdk.Web\n#:property LangVersion=preview\n#:project ./lib/X.csproj\n\nConsole.WriteLine(&quot;Hello&quot;);\n\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eRun: \u003ccode\u003edotnet run app.cs\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eConvert: \u003ccode\u003edotnet project convert app.cs\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eNO space after colon\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e.NET 10 required\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e"},{"heading":"Aspire — AppHost template","body_md":"```cs\nvar b = DistributedApplication\n  .CreateBuilder(args);\n\nvar cache = b.AddRedis(\"cache\");\nvar sql   = b.AddSqlServer(\"sql\");\nvar db    = sql.AddDatabase(\"app\");\n\nvar api = b.AddProject\u003cProjects.Api\u003e(\"api\")\n  .WithReference(cache)\n  .WithReference(db);\n\nb.AddProject\u003cProjects.Web\u003e(\"web\")\n  .WithReference(api).WaitFor(api);\n\nb.Build().Run();\n```\n\nEach service: `builder.AddServiceDefaults();`","body_html":"\u003cpre\u003e\u003ccode class=\"language-cs\"\u003evar b = DistributedApplication\n  .CreateBuilder(args);\n\nvar cache = b.AddRedis(&quot;cache&quot;);\nvar sql   = b.AddSqlServer(&quot;sql&quot;);\nvar db    = sql.AddDatabase(&quot;app&quot;);\n\nvar api = b.AddProject&lt;Projects.Api&gt;(&quot;api&quot;)\n  .WithReference(cache)\n  .WithReference(db);\n\nb.AddProject&lt;Projects.Web&gt;(&quot;web&quot;)\n  .WithReference(api).WaitFor(api);\n\nb.Build().Run();\n\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eEach service: \u003ccode\u003ebuilder.AddServiceDefaults();\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/p\u003e"},{"heading":"Localization setup","body_md":"```cs\nbuilder.Services.AddLocalization(\n  o =\u003e o.ResourcesPath = \"Resources\");\nbuilder.Services.AddRazorPages()\n  .AddViewLocalization();\n\nbuilder.Services.Configure\n  \u003cRequestLocalizationOptions\u003e(o =\u003e {\n  var c = new[]{new CultureInfo(\"en\"),\n                new CultureInfo(\"fr\")};\n  o.DefaultRequestCulture = new RequestCulture(\"en\");\n  o.SupportedCultures = c;\n  o.SupportedUICultures = c;\n});\napp.UseRequestLocalization();\n\n// Razor: @inject IViewLocalizer L\n// @L[\"Hello\"]\n// File: Pages.Index.fr.resx\n```\n\n**CurrentCulture**\\=formatting · **CurrentUICulture**\\=resx lookup","body_html":"\u003cpre\u003e\u003ccode class=\"language-cs\"\u003ebuilder.Services.AddLocalization(\n  o =&gt; o.ResourcesPath = &quot;Resources&quot;);\nbuilder.Services.AddRazorPages()\n  .AddViewLocalization();\n\nbuilder.Services.Configure\n  &lt;RequestLocalizationOptions&gt;(o =&gt; {\n  var c = new[]{new CultureInfo(&quot;en&quot;),\n                new CultureInfo(&quot;fr&quot;)};\n  o.DefaultRequestCulture = new RequestCulture(&quot;en&quot;);\n  o.SupportedCultures = c;\n  o.SupportedUICultures = c;\n});\napp.UseRequestLocalization();\n\n// Razor: @inject IViewLocalizer L\n// @L[&quot;Hello&quot;]\n// File: Pages.Index.fr.resx\n\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eCurrentCulture\u003c/strong\u003e=formatting · \u003cstrong\u003eCurrentUICulture\u003c/strong\u003e=resx lookup\u003c/p\u003e"},{"heading":"Tag Helpers — built-in + custom","body_md":"```cs\n// _ViewImports.cshtml\n@addTagHelper *,\n  Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.TagHelpers\n\n// Built-in\n\u003cform asp-controller=\"Home\" asp-action=\"X\"/\u003e\n\u003cinput asp-for=\"Name\"/\u003e\n\u003cspan asp-validation-for=\"Name\"/\u003e\n\u003ca asp-controller=\"Home\" asp-action=\"Index\"\n  asp-route-id=\"5\"\u003eGo\u003c/a\u003e\n\u003cscript src=\"s.js\" asp-append-version=\"true\"/\u003e\n\n// Custom\n[HtmlTargetElement(\"quote\")]\npublic class QuoteTag : TagHelper {\n  public string Text { get; set; }\n  public override void Process(TagHelperContext c,\n    TagHelperOutput o) {\n    o.TagName = \"blockquote\";\n    o.Content.SetHtmlContent(Text);\n  }\n}\n```\n\nProperty PascalCase → attribute kebab-case","body_html":"\u003cpre\u003e\u003ccode class=\"language-cs\"\u003e// _ViewImports.cshtml\n@addTagHelper *,\n  Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.TagHelpers\n\n// Built-in\n&lt;form asp-controller=&quot;Home&quot; asp-action=&quot;X&quot;/&gt;\n&lt;input asp-for=&quot;Name&quot;/&gt;\n&lt;span asp-validation-for=&quot;Name&quot;/&gt;\n&lt;a asp-controller=&quot;Home&quot; asp-action=&quot;Index&quot;\n  asp-route-id=&quot;5&quot;&gt;Go&lt;/a&gt;\n&lt;script src=&quot;s.js&quot; asp-append-version=&quot;true&quot;/&gt;\n\n// Custom\n[HtmlTargetElement(&quot;quote&quot;)]\npublic class QuoteTag : TagHelper {\n  public string Text { get; set; }\n  public override void Process(TagHelperContext c,\n    TagHelperOutput o) {\n    o.TagName = &quot;blockquote&quot;;\n    o.Content.SetHtmlContent(Text);\n  }\n}\n\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eProperty PascalCase → attribute kebab-case\u003c/p\u003e"},{"heading":"Blazor QuickGrid","body_md":"```cs\n@using Microsoft.AspNetCore\n  .Components.QuickGrid\n\n\u003cQuickGrid Items=\"@q\" Pagination=\"@p\"\u003e\n  \u003cPropertyColumn\n    Property=\"@(_=\u003e_.Name)\" Sortable=\"true\"/\u003e\n  \u003cTemplateColumn Title=\"X\" SortBy=\"@sort\"\u003e\n    \u003cstrong\u003e@context.Y\u003c/strong\u003e\n  \u003c/TemplateColumn\u003e\n\u003c/QuickGrid\u003e\n\u003cPaginator State=\"@p\"/\u003e\n\n@code {\n  PaginationState p =\n    new() { ItemsPerPage = 10 };\n  GridSort\u003cT\u003e sort = GridSort\u003cT\u003e\n    .ByAscending(x=\u003ex.Y);\n}\n```\n\nFilter: `\u003cinput @bind=\"f\" @bind:event=\"oninput\"/\u003e`","body_html":"\u003cpre\u003e\u003ccode class=\"language-cs\"\u003e@using Microsoft.AspNetCore\n  .Components.QuickGrid\n\n&lt;QuickGrid Items=&quot;@q&quot; Pagination=&quot;@p&quot;&gt;\n  &lt;PropertyColumn\n    Property=&quot;@(_=&gt;_.Name)&quot; Sortable=&quot;true&quot;/&gt;\n  &lt;TemplateColumn Title=&quot;X&quot; SortBy=&quot;@sort&quot;&gt;\n    &lt;strong&gt;@context.Y&lt;/strong&gt;\n  &lt;/TemplateColumn&gt;\n&lt;/QuickGrid&gt;\n&lt;Paginator State=&quot;@p&quot;/&gt;\n\n@code {\n  PaginationState p =\n    new() { ItemsPerPage = 10 };\n  GridSort&lt;T&gt; sort = GridSort&lt;T&gt;\n    .ByAscending(x=&gt;x.Y);\n}\n\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eFilter: \u003ccode\u003e&lt;input @bind=&quot;f&quot; @bind:event=&quot;oninput&quot;/&gt;\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/p\u003e"},{"heading":"Excel / PDF / Chart","body_md":"**Excel (ClosedXML)**\n\n```cs\nusing var w = new XLWorkbook();\nvar s = w.Worksheets.Add(\"x\");\ns.Cell(1,1).Value = \"hi\";\nusing var ms = new MemoryStream();\nw.SaveAs(ms);\nreturn File(ms.ToArray(),\n \"application/vnd.openxmlformats-officedocument.spreadsheetml.sheet\",\n \"x.xlsx\");\n```\n\n**PDF (iText7 + bouncy-castle-adapter)**\n\n```cs\nvar w = new PdfWriter(ms);\nvar pdf = new PdfDocument(w);\nvar d = new Document(pdf);\nd.Add(new Paragraph(\"hi\"));\nd.Close();\nreturn File(ms.ToArray(),\"application/pdf\",\"x.pdf\");\n```\n\nChart.js via CDN, client-side","body_html":"\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eExcel (ClosedXML)\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cpre\u003e\u003ccode class=\"language-cs\"\u003eusing var w = new XLWorkbook();\nvar s = w.Worksheets.Add(&quot;x&quot;);\ns.Cell(1,1).Value = &quot;hi&quot;;\nusing var ms = new MemoryStream();\nw.SaveAs(ms);\nreturn File(ms.ToArray(),\n &quot;application/vnd.openxmlformats-officedocument.spreadsheetml.sheet&quot;,\n &quot;x.xlsx&quot;);\n\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003ePDF (iText7 + bouncy-castle-adapter)\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cpre\u003e\u003ccode class=\"language-cs\"\u003evar w = new PdfWriter(ms);\nvar pdf = new PdfDocument(w);\nvar d = new Document(pdf);\nd.Add(new Paragraph(&quot;hi&quot;));\nd.Close();\nreturn File(ms.ToArray(),&quot;application/pdf&quot;,&quot;x.pdf&quot;);\n\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eChart.js via CDN, client-side\u003c/p\u003e"},{"heading":"MCQ trap patterns (from midterm)","body_md":"1.  Fake method names — eliminate if namespace chain looks wrong\n2.  Bracket style swaps: `[Route(\"api/[c]\")]` vs `Route(\"[api]/[c]\")`\n3.  Word order swap: `dotnet ef update database` vs `dotnet ef database update`\n4.  Singular/plural: `migrations add` not `migration add`\n5.  Fake interfaces: `AuthManager`, `IdentityManager` — not real\n6.  Protocol: gRPC = HTTP/2 (not 1.1); Ollama = http (not https)","body_html":"\u003col\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eFake method names — eliminate if namespace chain looks wrong\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eBracket style swaps: \u003ccode\u003e[Route(&quot;api/[c]&quot;)]\u003c/code\u003e vs \u003ccode\u003eRoute(&quot;[api]/[c]&quot;)\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eWord order swap: \u003ccode\u003edotnet ef update database\u003c/code\u003e vs \u003ccode\u003edotnet ef database update\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eSingular/plural: \u003ccode\u003emigrations add\u003c/code\u003e not \u003ccode\u003emigration add\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eFake interfaces: \u003ccode\u003eAuthManager\u003c/code\u003e, \u003ccode\u003eIdentityManager\u003c/code\u003e — not real\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eProtocol: gRPC = HTTP/2 (not 1.1); Ollama = http (not https)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ol\u003e"},{"heading":"Match-column patterns to expect","body_md":"Column A (concept) → Column B (canonical identifier):\n\n-   SK → `Kernel.CreateBuilder`\n-   MAF → `AIAgent`, `AIFunctionFactory`\n-   MCP → stdio / SSE transports\n-   ML.NET → `MLContext`, `LoadFromTextFile`, `Fit`\n-   Redis → `AddStackExchangeRedisCache`\n-   Cache tag → `\u003ccache vary-by-*\u003e`\n-   gRPC → `.proto`, `AddGrpc`, HTTP/2\n-   xUnit → `[Fact]`, `[Theory] [InlineData]`\n-   File-based → `#:package`, `#:sdk`\n-   Aspire → `AddProject`, `WithReference`\n-   Localization → `IViewLocalizer`, `Pages.Index.fr.resx`\n-   QuickGrid → `PropertyColumn`, `PaginationState`","body_html":"\u003cp\u003eColumn A (concept) → Column B (canonical identifier):\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eSK → \u003ccode\u003eKernel.CreateBuilder\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eMAF → \u003ccode\u003eAIAgent\u003c/code\u003e, \u003ccode\u003eAIFunctionFactory\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eMCP → stdio / SSE transports\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eML.NET → \u003ccode\u003eMLContext\u003c/code\u003e, \u003ccode\u003eLoadFromTextFile\u003c/code\u003e, \u003ccode\u003eFit\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eRedis → \u003ccode\u003eAddStackExchangeRedisCache\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eCache tag → \u003ccode\u003e&lt;cache vary-by-*&gt;\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003egRPC → \u003ccode\u003e.proto\u003c/code\u003e, \u003ccode\u003eAddGrpc\u003c/code\u003e, HTTP/2\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003exUnit → \u003ccode\u003e[Fact]\u003c/code\u003e, \u003ccode\u003e[Theory] [InlineData]\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eFile-based → \u003ccode\u003e#:package\u003c/code\u003e, \u003ccode\u003e#:sdk\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eAspire → \u003ccode\u003eAddProject\u003c/code\u003e, \u003ccode\u003eWithReference\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eLocalization → \u003ccode\u003eIViewLocalizer\u003c/code\u003e, \u003ccode\u003ePages.Index.fr.resx\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eQuickGrid → \u003ccode\u003ePropertyColumn\u003c/code\u003e, \u003ccode\u003ePaginationState\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e"},{"heading":"Time budget (60 min, 80 marks)","body_md":"MCQ (60): 30 min → 30 s each. If \u003e45s → skip, come back.\n\nMatch (10): 5 min — do LAST minus code.\n\nCode (10): 15 min — start with skeleton, get structure marks even if logic wrong.\n\nReview: 10 min — revisit skipped MCQs, double-check match column.\n\n**Don't**: spend \u003e2 min on any MCQ. 40 MCQ at 60% \u003e 20 MCQ at 90%.","body_html":"\u003cp\u003eMCQ (60): 30 min → 30 s each. If &gt;45s → skip, come back.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eMatch (10): 5 min — do LAST minus code.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eCode (10): 15 min — start with skeleton, get structure marks even if logic wrong.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eReview: 10 min — revisit skipped MCQs, double-check match column.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eDon&#39;t\u003c/strong\u003e: spend &gt;2 min on any MCQ. 40 MCQ at 60% &gt; 20 MCQ at 90%.\u003c/p\u003e"},{"heading":"Morning-of checklist","body_md":"-   Eat carbs + protein\n-   Hand-written cheat sheet: both sides filled, black pen\n-   Student ID + 2 pens + pencil + eraser\n-   No smartwatches, phones off\n-   Arrive 15 min early\n-   First: read ALL questions, answer easiest first, skip hard\n-   Match column → do when brain fatigues from MCQ (pattern matching is easier)\n-   Code question → read requirements TWICE, write skeleton first","body_html":"\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eEat carbs + protein\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eHand-written cheat sheet: both sides filled, black pen\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eStudent ID + 2 pens + pencil + eraser\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eNo smartwatches, phones off\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eArrive 15 min early\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eFirst: read ALL questions, answer easiest first, skip hard\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eMatch column → do when brain fatigues from MCQ (pattern matching is easier)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eCode question → read requirements TWICE, write skeleton first\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e"}]}};
